2698 * |SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_AUTOCLOSE |Yes |Yes |No |
2699 * |SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_STRRESET |Yes |Yes |No |
2700 * |SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_INPKILL |Yes |No |No |
2701 * |SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_ASOCKILL |Yes |Yes |No |
2702 * |SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_ADDR_WQ |No |No |No |
2703 * |SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_PRIM_DELETED |Yes |Yes |No |
2704 *
2705 */
2706
2707void
2708sctp_timer_stop(int t_type, struct sctp_inpcb *inp, struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
2709 struct sctp_nets *net, uint32_t from)
2710{
2711 struct sctp_timer *tmr;
2712
2713 KASSERT(stcb == NULL || stcb->sctp_ep == inp,
2714 ("sctp_timer_stop of type %d: inp = %p, stcb->sctp_ep %p",
2715 t_type, stcb, stcb->sctp_ep));
2716 if (stcb != NULL) {
2717 SCTP_TCB_LOCK_ASSERT(stcb);
2718 } else if (inp != NULL) {
2719 SCTP_INP_WLOCK_ASSERT(inp);
2720 } else {
2721 SCTP_WQ_ADDR_LOCK_ASSERT();
2722 }
2723 tmr = NULL;
2724 switch (t_type) {
2725 case SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SEND:
2726 if ((inp == NULL) || (stcb == NULL) || (net == NULL)) {
2727#ifdef INVARIANTS
2728 panic("sctp_timer_stop of type %d: inp = %p, stcb = %p, net = %p",
2729 t_type, inp, stcb, net);
2730#else
2731 return;
2732#endif
2733 }
2734 tmr = &net->rxt_timer;
2735 break;
2736 case SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_INIT:
2737 if ((inp == NULL) || (stcb == NULL) || (net == NULL)) {
2738#ifdef INVARIANTS
2739 panic("sctp_timer_stop of type %d: inp = %p, stcb = %p, net = %p",
2740 t_type, inp, stcb, net);
2741#else
2742 return;
2743#endif
2744 }
2745 tmr = &net->rxt_timer;
2746 break;
2747 case SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_RECV:
2748 if ((inp == NULL) || (stcb == NULL) || (net != NULL)) {
2749#ifdef INVARIANTS
2750 panic("sctp_timer_stop of type %d: inp = %p, stcb = %p, net = %p",
2751 t_type, inp, stcb, net);
2752#else
2753 return;
2754#endif
2755 }
2756 tmr = &stcb->asoc.dack_timer;
2757 break;
2758 case SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SHUTDOWN:
2759 if ((inp == NULL) || (stcb == NULL) || (net == NULL)) {
2760#ifdef INVARIANTS
2761 panic("sctp_timer_stop of type %d: inp = %p, stcb = %p, net = %p",
2762 t_type, inp, stcb, net);
2763#else
2764 return;
2765#endif
2766 }
2767 tmr = &net->rxt_timer;
2768 break;
2769 case SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_HEARTBEAT:
2770 if ((inp == NULL) || (stcb == NULL) || (net == NULL)) {
2771#ifdef INVARIANTS
2772 panic("sctp_timer_stop of type %d: inp = %p, stcb = %p, net = %p",
2773 t_type, inp, stcb, net);
2774#else
2775 return;
2776#endif
2777 }
2778 tmr = &net->hb_timer;
2779 break;
2780 case SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_COOKIE:
2781 if ((inp == NULL) || (stcb == NULL) || (net == NULL)) {
2782#ifdef INVARIANTS
2783 panic("sctp_timer_stop of type %d: inp = %p, stcb = %p, net = %p",
2784 t_type, inp, stcb, net);
2785#else
2786 return;
2787#endif
2788 }
2789 tmr = &net->rxt_timer;
2790 break;
2791 case SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_NEWCOOKIE:
2792 if ((inp == NULL) || (stcb != NULL) || (net != NULL)) {
2793#ifdef INVARIANTS
2794 panic("sctp_timer_stop of type %d: inp = %p, stcb = %p, net = %p",
2795 t_type, inp, stcb, net);
2796#else
2797 return;
2798#endif
2799 }
2800 tmr = &inp->sctp_ep.signature_change;
2801 break;
2802 case SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_PATHMTURAISE:
2803 if ((inp == NULL) || (stcb == NULL) || (net == NULL)) {
2804#ifdef INVARIANTS
2805 panic("sctp_timer_stop of type %d: inp = %p, stcb = %p, net = %p",
2806 t_type, inp, stcb, net);
2807#else
2808 return;
2809#endif
2810 }
2811 tmr = &net->pmtu_timer;
2812 break;
2813 case SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SHUTDOWNACK:
2814 if ((inp == NULL) || (stcb == NULL) || (net == NULL)) {
2815#ifdef INVARIANTS
2816 panic("sctp_timer_stop of type %d: inp = %p, stcb = %p, net = %p",
2817 t_type, inp, stcb, net);
2818#else
2819 return;
2820#endif
2821 }
2822 tmr = &net->rxt_timer;
2823 break;
2824 case SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_ASCONF:
2825 if ((inp == NULL) || (stcb == NULL) || (net != NULL)) {
2826#ifdef INVARIANTS
2827 panic("sctp_timer_stop of type %d: inp = %p, stcb = %p, net = %p",
2828 t_type, inp, stcb, net);
2829#else
2830 return;
2831#endif
2832 }
2833 tmr = &stcb->asoc.asconf_timer;
2834 break;
2835 case SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SHUTDOWNGUARD:
2836 if ((inp == NULL) || (stcb == NULL) || (net != NULL)) {
2837#ifdef INVARIANTS
2838 panic("sctp_timer_stop of type %d: inp = %p, stcb = %p, net = %p",
2839 t_type, inp, stcb, net);
2840#else
2841 return;
2842#endif
2843 }
2844 tmr = &stcb->asoc.shut_guard_timer;
2845 break;
2846 case SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_AUTOCLOSE:
2847 if ((inp == NULL) || (stcb == NULL) || (net != NULL)) {
2848#ifdef INVARIANTS
2849 panic("sctp_timer_stop of type %d: inp = %p, stcb = %p, net = %p",
2850 t_type, inp, stcb, net);
2851#else
2852 return;
2853#endif
2854 }
2855 tmr = &stcb->asoc.autoclose_timer;
2856 break;
2857 case SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_STRRESET:
2858 if ((inp == NULL) || (stcb == NULL) || (net != NULL)) {
2859#ifdef INVARIANTS
2860 panic("sctp_timer_stop of type %d: inp = %p, stcb = %p, net = %p",
2861 t_type, inp, stcb, net);
2862#else
2863 return;
2864#endif
2865 }
2866 tmr = &stcb->asoc.strreset_timer;
2867 break;
2868 case SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_INPKILL:
2869 /*
2870 * The inp is setup to die. We re-use the signature_chage
2871 * timer since that has stopped and we are in the GONE
2872 * state.
2873 */
2874 if ((inp == NULL) || (stcb != NULL) || (net != NULL)) {
2875#ifdef INVARIANTS
2876 panic("sctp_timer_stop of type %d: inp = %p, stcb = %p, net = %p",
2877 t_type, inp, stcb, net);
2878#else
2879 return;
2880#endif
2881 }
2882 tmr = &inp->sctp_ep.signature_change;
2883 break;
2884 case SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_ASOCKILL:
2885 if ((inp == NULL) || (stcb == NULL) || (net != NULL)) {
2886#ifdef INVARIANTS
2887 panic("sctp_timer_stop of type %d: inp = %p, stcb = %p, net = %p",
2888 t_type, inp, stcb, net);
2889#else
2890 return;
2891#endif
2892 }
2893 tmr = &stcb->asoc.strreset_timer;
2894 break;
2895 case SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_ADDR_WQ:
2896 if ((inp != NULL) || (stcb != NULL) || (net != NULL)) {
2897#ifdef INVARIANTS
2898 panic("sctp_timer_stop of type %d: inp = %p, stcb = %p, net = %p",
2899 t_type, inp, stcb, net);
2900#else
2901 return;
2902#endif
2903 }
2904 tmr = &SCTP_BASE_INFO(addr_wq_timer);
2905 break;
2906 case SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_PRIM_DELETED:
2907 if ((inp == NULL) || (stcb == NULL) || (net != NULL)) {
2908#ifdef INVARIANTS
2909 panic("sctp_timer_stop of type %d: inp = %p, stcb = %p, net = %p",
2910 t_type, inp, stcb, net);
2911#else
2912 return;
2913#endif
2914 }
2915 tmr = &stcb->asoc.delete_prim_timer;
2916 break;
2917 default:
2918#ifdef INVARIANTS
2919 panic("Unknown timer type %d", t_type);
2920#else
2921 return;
2922#endif
2923 }
2924 KASSERT(tmr != NULL, ("tmr is NULL for timer type %d", t_type));
2925 if ((tmr->type != SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_NONE) &&
2926 (tmr->type != t_type)) {
2927 /*
2928 * Ok we have a timer that is under joint use. Cookie timer
2929 * per chance with the SEND timer. We therefore are NOT
2930 * running the timer that the caller wants stopped. So just
2931 * return.
2932 */
2933 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_TIMER2,
2934 "Shared timer type %d not running: inp=%p, stcb=%p, net=%p.\n",
2935 t_type, inp, stcb, net);
2936 return;
2937 }
2938 if ((t_type == SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_SEND) && (stcb != NULL)) {
2939 stcb->asoc.num_send_timers_up--;
2940 if (stcb->asoc.num_send_timers_up < 0) {
2941 stcb->asoc.num_send_timers_up = 0;
2942 }
2943 }
2944 tmr->self = NULL;
2945 tmr->stopped_from = from;
2946 if (SCTP_OS_TIMER_STOP(&tmr->timer) == 1) {
2947 KASSERT(tmr->ep == inp,
2948 ("sctp_timer_stop of type %d: inp = %p, tmr->inp = %p",
2949 t_type, inp, tmr->ep));
2950 KASSERT(tmr->tcb == stcb,
2951 ("sctp_timer_stop of type %d: stcb = %p, tmr->stcb = %p",
2952 t_type, stcb, tmr->tcb));
2953 KASSERT(((t_type == SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_ASCONF) && (tmr->net != NULL)) ||
2954 ((t_type != SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_ASCONF) && (tmr->net == net)),
2955 ("sctp_timer_stop of type %d: net = %p, tmr->net = %p",
2956 t_type, net, tmr->net));
2957 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_TIMER2,
2958 "Timer type %d stopped: inp=%p, stcb=%p, net=%p.\n",
2959 t_type, inp, stcb, net);
2960 /*
2961 * If the timer was actually stopped, decrement reference counts
2962 * that were incremented in sctp_timer_start().
2963 */
2964 if (tmr->ep != NULL) {
2965 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
2966 tmr->ep = NULL;
2967 }
2968 if (tmr->tcb != NULL) {
2969 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, -1);
2970 tmr->tcb = NULL;
2971 }
2972 if (tmr->net != NULL) {
2973 /*
2974 * Can't use net, since it doesn't work for
2975 * SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_ASCONF.
2976 */
2977 sctp_free_remote_addr((struct sctp_nets *)tmr->net);
2978 tmr->net = NULL;
2979 }
2980 } else {
2981 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_TIMER2,
2982 "Timer type %d not stopped: inp=%p, stcb=%p, net=%p.\n",
2983 t_type, inp, stcb, net);
2984 }
2985 return;
2986}
2987
2988uint32_t
2989sctp_calculate_len(struct mbuf *m)
2990{
2991 uint32_t tlen = 0;
2992 struct mbuf *at;
2993
2994 at = m;
2995 while (at) {
2996 tlen += SCTP_BUF_LEN(at);
2997 at = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(at);
2998 }
2999 return (tlen);
3000}
3001
3002void
3003sctp_mtu_size_reset(struct sctp_inpcb *inp,
3004 struct sctp_association *asoc, uint32_t mtu)
3005{
3006 /*
3007 * Reset the P-MTU size on this association, this involves changing
3008 * the asoc MTU, going through ANY chunk+overhead larger than mtu to
3009 * allow the DF flag to be cleared.
3010 */
3011 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk;
3012 unsigned int eff_mtu, ovh;
3013
3014 asoc->smallest_mtu = mtu;
3015 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUND_V6) {
3016 ovh = SCTP_MIN_OVERHEAD;
3017 } else {
3018 ovh = SCTP_MIN_V4_OVERHEAD;
3019 }
3020 eff_mtu = mtu - ovh;
3021 TAILQ_FOREACH(chk, &asoc->send_queue, sctp_next) {
3022 if (chk->send_size > eff_mtu) {
3023 chk->flags |= CHUNK_FLAGS_FRAGMENT_OK;
3024 }
3025 }
3026 TAILQ_FOREACH(chk, &asoc->sent_queue, sctp_next) {
3027 if (chk->send_size > eff_mtu) {
3028 chk->flags |= CHUNK_FLAGS_FRAGMENT_OK;
3029 }
3030 }
3031}
3032
3033/*
3034 * Given an association and starting time of the current RTT period, update
3035 * RTO in number of msecs. net should point to the current network.
3036 * Return 1, if an RTO update was performed, return 0 if no update was
3037 * performed due to invalid starting point.
3038 */
3039
3040int
3041sctp_calculate_rto(struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
3042 struct sctp_association *asoc,
3043 struct sctp_nets *net,
3044 struct timeval *old,
3045 int rtt_from_sack)
3046{
3047 struct timeval now;
3048 uint64_t rtt_us; /* RTT in us */
3049 int32_t rtt; /* RTT in ms */
3050 uint32_t new_rto;
3051 int first_measure = 0;
3052
3053 /************************/
3054 /* 1. calculate new RTT */
3055 /************************/
3056 /* get the current time */
3057 if (stcb->asoc.use_precise_time) {
3058 (void)SCTP_GETPTIME_TIMEVAL(&now);
3059 } else {
3060 (void)SCTP_GETTIME_TIMEVAL(&now);
3061 }
3062 if ((old->tv_sec > now.tv_sec) ||
3063 ((old->tv_sec == now.tv_sec) && (old->tv_usec > now.tv_usec))) {
3064 /* The starting point is in the future. */
3065 return (0);
3066 }
3067 timevalsub(&now, old);
3068 rtt_us = (uint64_t)1000000 * (uint64_t)now.tv_sec + (uint64_t)now.tv_usec;
3069 if (rtt_us > SCTP_RTO_UPPER_BOUND * 1000) {
3070 /* The RTT is larger than a sane value. */
3071 return (0);
3072 }
3073 /* store the current RTT in us */
3074 net->rtt = rtt_us;
3075 /* compute rtt in ms */
3076 rtt = (int32_t)(net->rtt / 1000);
3077 if ((asoc->cc_functions.sctp_rtt_calculated) && (rtt_from_sack == SCTP_RTT_FROM_DATA)) {
3078 /* Tell the CC module that a new update has just occurred from a sack */
3079 (*asoc->cc_functions.sctp_rtt_calculated)(stcb, net, &now);
3080 }
3081 /* Do we need to determine the lan? We do this only
3082 * on sacks i.e. RTT being determined from data not
3083 * non-data (HB/INIT->INITACK).
3084 */
3085 if ((rtt_from_sack == SCTP_RTT_FROM_DATA) &&
3086 (net->lan_type == SCTP_LAN_UNKNOWN)) {
3087 if (net->rtt > SCTP_LOCAL_LAN_RTT) {
3088 net->lan_type = SCTP_LAN_INTERNET;
3089 } else {
3090 net->lan_type = SCTP_LAN_LOCAL;
3091 }
3092 }
3093
3094 /***************************/
3095 /* 2. update RTTVAR & SRTT */
3096 /***************************/
3097 /*-
3098 * Compute the scaled average lastsa and the
3099 * scaled variance lastsv as described in van Jacobson
3100 * Paper "Congestion Avoidance and Control", Annex A.
3101 *
3102 * (net->lastsa >> SCTP_RTT_SHIFT) is the srtt
3103 * (net->lastsv >> SCTP_RTT_VAR_SHIFT) is the rttvar
3104 */
3105 if (net->RTO_measured) {
3106 rtt -= (net->lastsa >> SCTP_RTT_SHIFT);
3107 net->lastsa += rtt;
3108 if (rtt < 0) {
3109 rtt = -rtt;
3110 }
3111 rtt -= (net->lastsv >> SCTP_RTT_VAR_SHIFT);
3112 net->lastsv += rtt;
3113 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_RTTVAR_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
3114 rto_logging(net, SCTP_LOG_RTTVAR);
3115 }
3116 } else {
3117 /* First RTO measurment */
3118 net->RTO_measured = 1;
3119 first_measure = 1;
3120 net->lastsa = rtt << SCTP_RTT_SHIFT;
3121 net->lastsv = (rtt / 2) << SCTP_RTT_VAR_SHIFT;
3122 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_RTTVAR_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
3123 rto_logging(net, SCTP_LOG_INITIAL_RTT);
3124 }
3125 }
3126 if (net->lastsv == 0) {
3127 net->lastsv = SCTP_CLOCK_GRANULARITY;
3128 }
3129 new_rto = (net->lastsa >> SCTP_RTT_SHIFT) + net->lastsv;
3130 if ((new_rto > SCTP_SAT_NETWORK_MIN) &&
3131 (stcb->asoc.sat_network_lockout == 0)) {
3132 stcb->asoc.sat_network = 1;
3133 } else if ((!first_measure) && stcb->asoc.sat_network) {
3134 stcb->asoc.sat_network = 0;
3135 stcb->asoc.sat_network_lockout = 1;
3136 }
3137 /* bound it, per C6/C7 in Section 5.3.1 */
3138 if (new_rto < stcb->asoc.minrto) {
3139 new_rto = stcb->asoc.minrto;
3140 }
3141 if (new_rto > stcb->asoc.maxrto) {
3142 new_rto = stcb->asoc.maxrto;
3143 }
3144 net->RTO = new_rto;
3145 return (1);
3146}
3147
3148/*
3149 * return a pointer to a contiguous piece of data from the given mbuf chain
3150 * starting at 'off' for 'len' bytes. If the desired piece spans more than
3151 * one mbuf, a copy is made at 'ptr'. caller must ensure that the buffer size
3152 * is >= 'len' returns NULL if there there isn't 'len' bytes in the chain.
3153 */
3154caddr_t
3155sctp_m_getptr(struct mbuf *m, int off, int len, uint8_t * in_ptr)
3156{
3157 uint32_t count;
3158 uint8_t *ptr;
3159
3160 ptr = in_ptr;
3161 if ((off < 0) || (len <= 0))
3162 return (NULL);
3163
3164 /* find the desired start location */
3165 while ((m != NULL) && (off > 0)) {
3166 if (off < SCTP_BUF_LEN(m))
3167 break;
3168 off -= SCTP_BUF_LEN(m);
3169 m = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m);
3170 }
3171 if (m == NULL)
3172 return (NULL);
3173
3174 /* is the current mbuf large enough (eg. contiguous)? */
3175 if ((SCTP_BUF_LEN(m) - off) >= len) {
3176 return (mtod(m, caddr_t) + off);
3177 } else {
3178 /* else, it spans more than one mbuf, so save a temp copy... */
3179 while ((m != NULL) && (len > 0)) {
3180 count = min(SCTP_BUF_LEN(m) - off, len);
3181 memcpy(ptr, mtod(m, caddr_t) + off, count);
3182 len -= count;
3183 ptr += count;
3184 off = 0;
3185 m = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m);
3186 }
3187 if ((m == NULL) && (len > 0))
3188 return (NULL);
3189 else
3190 return ((caddr_t)in_ptr);
3191 }
3192}
3193
3194struct sctp_paramhdr *
3195sctp_get_next_param(struct mbuf *m,
3196 int offset,
3197 struct sctp_paramhdr *pull,
3198 int pull_limit)
3199{
3200 /* This just provides a typed signature to Peter's Pull routine */
3201 return ((struct sctp_paramhdr *)sctp_m_getptr(m, offset, pull_limit,
3202 (uint8_t *) pull));
3203}
3204
3205struct mbuf *
3206sctp_add_pad_tombuf(struct mbuf *m, int padlen)
3207{
3208 struct mbuf *m_last;
3209 caddr_t dp;
3210
3211 if (padlen > 3) {
3212 return (NULL);
3213 }
3214 if (padlen <= M_TRAILINGSPACE(m)) {
3215 /*
3216 * The easy way. We hope the majority of the time we hit
3217 * here :)
3218 */
3219 m_last = m;
3220 } else {
3221 /* Hard way we must grow the mbuf chain */
3222 m_last = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(padlen, 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
3223 if (m_last == NULL) {
3224 return (NULL);
3225 }
3226 SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_last) = 0;
3227 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m_last) = NULL;
3228 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m) = m_last;
3229 }
3230 dp = mtod(m_last, caddr_t) + SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_last);
3231 SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_last) += padlen;
3232 memset(dp, 0, padlen);
3233 return (m_last);
3234}
3235
3236struct mbuf *
3237sctp_pad_lastmbuf(struct mbuf *m, int padval, struct mbuf *last_mbuf)
3238{
3239 /* find the last mbuf in chain and pad it */
3240 struct mbuf *m_at;
3241
3242 if (last_mbuf != NULL) {
3243 return (sctp_add_pad_tombuf(last_mbuf, padval));
3244 } else {
3245 for (m_at = m; m_at; m_at = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m_at)) {
3246 if (SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m_at) == NULL) {
3247 return (sctp_add_pad_tombuf(m_at, padval));
3248 }
3249 }
3250 }
3251 return (NULL);
3252}
3253
3254static void
3255sctp_notify_assoc_change(uint16_t state, struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
3256 uint16_t error, struct sctp_abort_chunk *abort, uint8_t from_peer, int so_locked)
3257{
3258 struct mbuf *m_notify;
3259 struct sctp_assoc_change *sac;
3260 struct sctp_queued_to_read *control;
3261 unsigned int notif_len;
3262 uint16_t abort_len;
3263 unsigned int i;
3264#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3265 struct socket *so;
3266#endif
3267
3268 if (stcb == NULL) {
3269 return;
3270 }
3271 if (sctp_stcb_is_feature_on(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_RECVASSOCEVNT)) {
3272 notif_len = (unsigned int)sizeof(struct sctp_assoc_change);
3273 if (abort != NULL) {
3274 abort_len = ntohs(abort->ch.chunk_length);
3275 /*
3276 * Only SCTP_CHUNK_BUFFER_SIZE are guaranteed to be
3277 * contiguous.
3278 */
3279 if (abort_len > SCTP_CHUNK_BUFFER_SIZE) {
3280 abort_len = SCTP_CHUNK_BUFFER_SIZE;
3281 }
3282 } else {
3283 abort_len = 0;
3284 }
3285 if ((state == SCTP_COMM_UP) || (state == SCTP_RESTART)) {
3286 notif_len += SCTP_ASSOC_SUPPORTS_MAX;
3287 } else if ((state == SCTP_COMM_LOST) || (state == SCTP_CANT_STR_ASSOC)) {
3288 notif_len += abort_len;
3289 }
3290 m_notify = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(notif_len, 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
3291 if (m_notify == NULL) {
3292 /* Retry with smaller value. */
3293 notif_len = (unsigned int)sizeof(struct sctp_assoc_change);
3294 m_notify = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(notif_len, 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
3295 if (m_notify == NULL) {
3296 goto set_error;
3297 }
3298 }
3299 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m_notify) = NULL;
3300 sac = mtod(m_notify, struct sctp_assoc_change *);
3301 memset(sac, 0, notif_len);
3302 sac->sac_type = SCTP_ASSOC_CHANGE;
3303 sac->sac_flags = 0;
3304 sac->sac_length = sizeof(struct sctp_assoc_change);
3305 sac->sac_state = state;
3306 sac->sac_error = error;
3307 /* XXX verify these stream counts */
3308 sac->sac_outbound_streams = stcb->asoc.streamoutcnt;
3309 sac->sac_inbound_streams = stcb->asoc.streamincnt;
3310 sac->sac_assoc_id = sctp_get_associd(stcb);
3311 if (notif_len > sizeof(struct sctp_assoc_change)) {
3312 if ((state == SCTP_COMM_UP) || (state == SCTP_RESTART)) {
3313 i = 0;
3314 if (stcb->asoc.prsctp_supported == 1) {
3315 sac->sac_info[i++] = SCTP_ASSOC_SUPPORTS_PR;
3316 }
3317 if (stcb->asoc.auth_supported == 1) {
3318 sac->sac_info[i++] = SCTP_ASSOC_SUPPORTS_AUTH;
3319 }
3320 if (stcb->asoc.asconf_supported == 1) {
3321 sac->sac_info[i++] = SCTP_ASSOC_SUPPORTS_ASCONF;
3322 }
3323 if (stcb->asoc.idata_supported == 1) {
3324 sac->sac_info[i++] = SCTP_ASSOC_SUPPORTS_INTERLEAVING;
3325 }
3326 sac->sac_info[i++] = SCTP_ASSOC_SUPPORTS_MULTIBUF;
3327 if (stcb->asoc.reconfig_supported == 1) {
3328 sac->sac_info[i++] = SCTP_ASSOC_SUPPORTS_RE_CONFIG;
3329 }
3330 sac->sac_length += i;
3331 } else if ((state == SCTP_COMM_LOST) || (state == SCTP_CANT_STR_ASSOC)) {
3332 memcpy(sac->sac_info, abort, abort_len);
3333 sac->sac_length += abort_len;
3334 }
3335 }
3336 SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_notify) = sac->sac_length;
3337 control = sctp_build_readq_entry(stcb, stcb->asoc.primary_destination,
3338 0, 0, stcb->asoc.context, 0, 0, 0,
3339 m_notify);
3340 if (control != NULL) {
3341 control->length = SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_notify);
3342 control->spec_flags = M_NOTIFICATION;
3343 /* not that we need this */
3344 control->tail_mbuf = m_notify;
3345 sctp_add_to_readq(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb,
3346 control,
3347 &stcb->sctp_socket->so_rcv, 1, SCTP_READ_LOCK_NOT_HELD,
3348 so_locked);
3349 } else {
3350 sctp_m_freem(m_notify);
3351 }
3352 }
3353 /*
3354 * For 1-to-1 style sockets, we send up and error when an ABORT
3355 * comes in.
3356 */
3357set_error:
3358 if (((stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) ||
3359 (stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL)) &&
3360 ((state == SCTP_COMM_LOST) || (state == SCTP_CANT_STR_ASSOC))) {
3361 SOCK_LOCK(stcb->sctp_socket);
3362 if (from_peer) {
3363 if (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_WAIT) {
3364 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, ECONNREFUSED);
3365 stcb->sctp_socket->so_error = ECONNREFUSED;
3366 } else {
3367 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, ECONNRESET);
3368 stcb->sctp_socket->so_error = ECONNRESET;
3369 }
3370 } else {
3371 if ((SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_WAIT) ||
3372 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_ECHOED)) {
3373 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, ETIMEDOUT);
3374 stcb->sctp_socket->so_error = ETIMEDOUT;
3375 } else {
3376 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, ECONNABORTED);
3377 stcb->sctp_socket->so_error = ECONNABORTED;
3378 }
3379 }
3380 SOCK_UNLOCK(stcb->sctp_socket);
3381 }
3382 /* Wake ANY sleepers */
3383#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3384 so = SCTP_INP_SO(stcb->sctp_ep);
3385 if (!so_locked) {
3386 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
3387 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
3388 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 1);
3389 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
3390 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
3391 if (stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_CLOSED_SOCKET) {
3392 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
3393 return;
3394 }
3395 }
3396#endif
3397 if (((stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) ||
3398 (stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL)) &&
3399 ((state == SCTP_COMM_LOST) || (state == SCTP_CANT_STR_ASSOC))) {
3400 socantrcvmore(stcb->sctp_socket);
3401 }
3402 sorwakeup(stcb->sctp_socket);
3403 sowwakeup(stcb->sctp_socket);
3404#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3405 if (!so_locked) {
3406 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
3407 }
3408#endif
3409}
3410
3411static void
3412sctp_notify_peer_addr_change(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, uint32_t state,
3413 struct sockaddr *sa, uint32_t error, int so_locked)
3414{
3415 struct mbuf *m_notify;
3416 struct sctp_paddr_change *spc;
3417 struct sctp_queued_to_read *control;
3418
3419 if ((stcb == NULL) ||
3420 sctp_stcb_is_feature_off(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_RECVPADDREVNT)) {
3421 /* event not enabled */
3422 return;
3423 }
3424 m_notify = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(sizeof(struct sctp_paddr_change), 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
3425 if (m_notify == NULL)
3426 return;
3427 SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_notify) = 0;
3428 spc = mtod(m_notify, struct sctp_paddr_change *);
3429 memset(spc, 0, sizeof(struct sctp_paddr_change));
3430 spc->spc_type = SCTP_PEER_ADDR_CHANGE;
3431 spc->spc_flags = 0;
3432 spc->spc_length = sizeof(struct sctp_paddr_change);
3433 switch (sa->sa_family) {
3434#ifdef INET
3435 case AF_INET:
3436#ifdef INET6
3437 if (sctp_is_feature_on(stcb->sctp_ep, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_NEEDS_MAPPED_V4)) {
3438 in6_sin_2_v4mapsin6((struct sockaddr_in *)sa,
3439 (struct sockaddr_in6 *)&spc->spc_aaddr);
3440 } else {
3441 memcpy(&spc->spc_aaddr, sa, sizeof(struct sockaddr_in));
3442 }
3443#else
3444 memcpy(&spc->spc_aaddr, sa, sizeof(struct sockaddr_in));
3445#endif
3446 break;
3447#endif
3448#ifdef INET6
3449 case AF_INET6:
3450 {
3451#ifdef SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE
3452 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6;
3453#endif /* SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE */
3454 memcpy(&spc->spc_aaddr, sa, sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6));
3455
3456#ifdef SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE
3457 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)&spc->spc_aaddr;
3458 if (IN6_IS_SCOPE_LINKLOCAL(&sin6->sin6_addr)) {
3459 if (sin6->sin6_scope_id == 0) {
3460 /* recover scope_id for user */
3461#ifdef SCTP_KAME
3462 (void)sa6_recoverscope(sin6);
3463#else
3464 (void)in6_recoverscope(sin6, &sin6->sin6_addr,
3465 NULL);
3466#endif
3467 } else {
3468 /* clear embedded scope_id for user */
3469 in6_clearscope(&sin6->sin6_addr);
3470 }
3471 }
3472#endif /* SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE */
3473 break;
3474 }
3475#endif
3476#if defined(__Userspace__)
3477 case AF_CONN:
3478 memcpy(&spc->spc_aaddr, sa, sizeof(struct sockaddr_conn));
3479 break;
3480#endif
3481 default:
3482 /* TSNH */
3483 break;
3484 }
3485 spc->spc_state = state;
3486 spc->spc_error = error;
3487 spc->spc_assoc_id = sctp_get_associd(stcb);
3488
3489 SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_notify) = sizeof(struct sctp_paddr_change);
3490 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m_notify) = NULL;
3491
3492 /* append to socket */
3493 control = sctp_build_readq_entry(stcb, stcb->asoc.primary_destination,
3494 0, 0, stcb->asoc.context, 0, 0, 0,
3495 m_notify);
3496 if (control == NULL) {
3497 /* no memory */
3498 sctp_m_freem(m_notify);
3499 return;
3500 }
3501 control->length = SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_notify);
3502 control->spec_flags = M_NOTIFICATION;
3503 /* not that we need this */
3504 control->tail_mbuf = m_notify;
3505 sctp_add_to_readq(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb,
3506 control,
3507 &stcb->sctp_socket->so_rcv, 1,
3508 SCTP_READ_LOCK_NOT_HELD,
3509 so_locked);
3510}
3511
3512static void
3513sctp_notify_send_failed(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, uint8_t sent, uint32_t error,
3514 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk, int so_locked)
3515{
3516 struct mbuf *m_notify;
3517 struct sctp_send_failed *ssf;
3518 struct sctp_send_failed_event *ssfe;
3519 struct sctp_queued_to_read *control;
3520 struct sctp_chunkhdr *chkhdr;
3521 int notifhdr_len, chk_len, chkhdr_len, padding_len, payload_len;
3522
3523 if ((stcb == NULL) ||
3524 (sctp_stcb_is_feature_off(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_RECVSENDFAILEVNT) &&
3525 sctp_stcb_is_feature_off(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_RECVNSENDFAILEVNT))) {
3526 /* event not enabled */
3527 return;
3528 }
3529
3530 if (sctp_stcb_is_feature_on(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_RECVNSENDFAILEVNT)) {
3531 notifhdr_len = sizeof(struct sctp_send_failed_event);
3532 } else {
3533 notifhdr_len = sizeof(struct sctp_send_failed);
3534 }
3535 m_notify = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(notifhdr_len, 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
3536 if (m_notify == NULL)
3537 /* no space left */
3538 return;
3539 SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_notify) = notifhdr_len;
3540 if (stcb->asoc.idata_supported) {
3541 chkhdr_len = sizeof(struct sctp_idata_chunk);
3542 } else {
3543 chkhdr_len = sizeof(struct sctp_data_chunk);
3544 }
3545 /* Use some defaults in case we can't access the chunk header */
3546 if (chk->send_size >= chkhdr_len) {
3547 payload_len = chk->send_size - chkhdr_len;
3548 } else {
3549 payload_len = 0;
3550 }
3551 padding_len = 0;
3552 if (chk->data != NULL) {
3553 chkhdr = mtod(chk->data, struct sctp_chunkhdr *);
3554 if (chkhdr != NULL) {
3555 chk_len = ntohs(chkhdr->chunk_length);
3556 if ((chk_len >= chkhdr_len) &&
3557 (chk->send_size >= chk_len) &&
3558 (chk->send_size - chk_len < 4)) {
3559 padding_len = chk->send_size - chk_len;
3560 payload_len = chk->send_size - chkhdr_len - padding_len;
3561 }
3562 }
3563 }
3564 if (sctp_stcb_is_feature_on(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_RECVNSENDFAILEVNT)) {
3565 ssfe = mtod(m_notify, struct sctp_send_failed_event *);
3566 memset(ssfe, 0, notifhdr_len);
3567 ssfe->ssfe_type = SCTP_SEND_FAILED_EVENT;
3568 if (sent) {
3569 ssfe->ssfe_flags = SCTP_DATA_SENT;
3570 } else {
3571 ssfe->ssfe_flags = SCTP_DATA_UNSENT;
3572 }
3573 ssfe->ssfe_length = (uint32_t)(notifhdr_len + payload_len);
3574 ssfe->ssfe_error = error;
3575 /* not exactly what the user sent in, but should be close :) */
3576 ssfe->ssfe_info.snd_sid = chk->rec.data.sid;
3577 ssfe->ssfe_info.snd_flags = chk->rec.data.rcv_flags;
3578 ssfe->ssfe_info.snd_ppid = chk->rec.data.ppid;
3579 ssfe->ssfe_info.snd_context = chk->rec.data.context;
3580 ssfe->ssfe_info.snd_assoc_id = sctp_get_associd(stcb);
3581 ssfe->ssfe_assoc_id = sctp_get_associd(stcb);
3582 } else {
3583 ssf = mtod(m_notify, struct sctp_send_failed *);
3584 memset(ssf, 0, notifhdr_len);
3585 ssf->ssf_type = SCTP_SEND_FAILED;
3586 if (sent) {
3587 ssf->ssf_flags = SCTP_DATA_SENT;
3588 } else {
3589 ssf->ssf_flags = SCTP_DATA_UNSENT;
3590 }
3591 ssf->ssf_length = (uint32_t)(notifhdr_len + payload_len);
3592 ssf->ssf_error = error;
3593 /* not exactly what the user sent in, but should be close :) */
3594 ssf->ssf_info.sinfo_stream = chk->rec.data.sid;
3595 ssf->ssf_info.sinfo_ssn = (uint16_t)chk->rec.data.mid;
3596 ssf->ssf_info.sinfo_flags = chk->rec.data.rcv_flags;
3597 ssf->ssf_info.sinfo_ppid = chk->rec.data.ppid;
3598 ssf->ssf_info.sinfo_context = chk->rec.data.context;
3599 ssf->ssf_info.sinfo_assoc_id = sctp_get_associd(stcb);
3600 ssf->ssf_assoc_id = sctp_get_associd(stcb);
3601 }
3602 if (chk->data != NULL) {
3603 /* Trim off the sctp chunk header (it should be there) */
3604 if (chk->send_size == chkhdr_len + payload_len + padding_len) {
3605 m_adj(chk->data, chkhdr_len);
3606 m_adj(chk->data, -padding_len);
3607 sctp_mbuf_crush(chk->data);
3608 chk->send_size -= (chkhdr_len + padding_len);
3609 }
3610 }
3611 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m_notify) = chk->data;
3612 /* Steal off the mbuf */
3613 chk->data = NULL;
3614 /*
3615 * For this case, we check the actual socket buffer, since the assoc
3616 * is going away we don't want to overfill the socket buffer for a
3617 * non-reader
3618 */
3619 if (sctp_sbspace_failedmsgs(&stcb->sctp_socket->so_rcv) < SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_notify)) {
3620 sctp_m_freem(m_notify);
3621 return;
3622 }
3623 /* append to socket */
3624 control = sctp_build_readq_entry(stcb, stcb->asoc.primary_destination,
3625 0, 0, stcb->asoc.context, 0, 0, 0,
3626 m_notify);
3627 if (control == NULL) {
3628 /* no memory */
3629 sctp_m_freem(m_notify);
3630 return;
3631 }
3632 control->length = SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_notify);
3633 control->spec_flags = M_NOTIFICATION;
3634 /* not that we need this */
3635 control->tail_mbuf = m_notify;
3636 sctp_add_to_readq(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb,
3637 control,
3638 &stcb->sctp_socket->so_rcv, 1,
3639 SCTP_READ_LOCK_NOT_HELD,
3640 so_locked);
3641}
3642
3643static void
3644sctp_notify_send_failed2(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, uint32_t error,
3645 struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *sp, int so_locked)
3646{
3647 struct mbuf *m_notify;
3648 struct sctp_send_failed *ssf;
3649 struct sctp_send_failed_event *ssfe;
3650 struct sctp_queued_to_read *control;
3651 int notifhdr_len;
3652
3653 if ((stcb == NULL) ||
3654 (sctp_stcb_is_feature_off(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_RECVSENDFAILEVNT) &&
3655 sctp_stcb_is_feature_off(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_RECVNSENDFAILEVNT))) {
3656 /* event not enabled */
3657 return;
3658 }
3659 if (sctp_stcb_is_feature_on(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_RECVNSENDFAILEVNT)) {
3660 notifhdr_len = sizeof(struct sctp_send_failed_event);
3661 } else {
3662 notifhdr_len = sizeof(struct sctp_send_failed);
3663 }
3664 m_notify = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(notifhdr_len, 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
3665 if (m_notify == NULL) {
3666 /* no space left */
3667 return;
3668 }
3669 SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_notify) = notifhdr_len;
3670 if (sctp_stcb_is_feature_on(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_RECVNSENDFAILEVNT)) {
3671 ssfe = mtod(m_notify, struct sctp_send_failed_event *);
3672 memset(ssfe, 0, notifhdr_len);
3673 ssfe->ssfe_type = SCTP_SEND_FAILED_EVENT;
3674 ssfe->ssfe_flags = SCTP_DATA_UNSENT;
3675 ssfe->ssfe_length = (uint32_t)(notifhdr_len + sp->length);
3676 ssfe->ssfe_error = error;
3677 /* not exactly what the user sent in, but should be close :) */
3678 ssfe->ssfe_info.snd_sid = sp->sid;
3679 if (sp->some_taken) {
3680 ssfe->ssfe_info.snd_flags = SCTP_DATA_LAST_FRAG;
3681 } else {
3682 ssfe->ssfe_info.snd_flags = SCTP_DATA_NOT_FRAG;
3683 }
3684 ssfe->ssfe_info.snd_ppid = sp->ppid;
3685 ssfe->ssfe_info.snd_context = sp->context;
3686 ssfe->ssfe_info.snd_assoc_id = sctp_get_associd(stcb);
3687 ssfe->ssfe_assoc_id = sctp_get_associd(stcb);
3688 } else {
3689 ssf = mtod(m_notify, struct sctp_send_failed *);
3690 memset(ssf, 0, notifhdr_len);
3691 ssf->ssf_type = SCTP_SEND_FAILED;
3692 ssf->ssf_flags = SCTP_DATA_UNSENT;
3693 ssf->ssf_length = (uint32_t)(notifhdr_len + sp->length);
3694 ssf->ssf_error = error;
3695 /* not exactly what the user sent in, but should be close :) */
3696 ssf->ssf_info.sinfo_stream = sp->sid;
3697 ssf->ssf_info.sinfo_ssn = 0;
3698 if (sp->some_taken) {
3699 ssf->ssf_info.sinfo_flags = SCTP_DATA_LAST_FRAG;
3700 } else {
3701 ssf->ssf_info.sinfo_flags = SCTP_DATA_NOT_FRAG;
3702 }
3703 ssf->ssf_info.sinfo_ppid = sp->ppid;
3704 ssf->ssf_info.sinfo_context = sp->context;
3705 ssf->ssf_info.sinfo_assoc_id = sctp_get_associd(stcb);
3706 ssf->ssf_assoc_id = sctp_get_associd(stcb);
3707 }
3708 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m_notify) = sp->data;
3709
3710 /* Steal off the mbuf */
3711 sp->data = NULL;
3712 /*
3713 * For this case, we check the actual socket buffer, since the assoc
3714 * is going away we don't want to overfill the socket buffer for a
3715 * non-reader
3716 */
3717 if (sctp_sbspace_failedmsgs(&stcb->sctp_socket->so_rcv) < SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_notify)) {
3718 sctp_m_freem(m_notify);
3719 return;
3720 }
3721 /* append to socket */
3722 control = sctp_build_readq_entry(stcb, stcb->asoc.primary_destination,
3723 0, 0, stcb->asoc.context, 0, 0, 0,
3724 m_notify);
3725 if (control == NULL) {
3726 /* no memory */
3727 sctp_m_freem(m_notify);
3728 return;
3729 }
3730 control->length = SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_notify);
3731 control->spec_flags = M_NOTIFICATION;
3732 /* not that we need this */
3733 control->tail_mbuf = m_notify;
3734 sctp_add_to_readq(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb,
3735 control,
3736 &stcb->sctp_socket->so_rcv, 1, SCTP_READ_LOCK_NOT_HELD, so_locked);
3737}

3739static void
3740sctp_notify_adaptation_layer(struct sctp_tcb *stcb)
3741{
3742 struct mbuf *m_notify;
3743 struct sctp_adaptation_event *sai;
3744 struct sctp_queued_to_read *control;
3745
3746 if ((stcb == NULL) ||
3747 sctp_stcb_is_feature_off(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_ADAPTATIONEVNT)) {
3748 /* event not enabled */
3749 return;
3750 }
3751
3752 m_notify = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(sizeof(struct sctp_adaption_event), 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
3753 if (m_notify == NULL)
3754 /* no space left */
3755 return;
3756 SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_notify) = 0;
3757 sai = mtod(m_notify, struct sctp_adaptation_event *);

3759 sai->sai_type = SCTP_ADAPTATION_INDICATION;
3760 sai->sai_flags = 0;
3761 sai->sai_length = sizeof(struct sctp_adaptation_event);
3762 sai->sai_adaptation_ind = stcb->asoc.peers_adaptation;
3763 sai->sai_assoc_id = sctp_get_associd(stcb);
3764
3765 SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_notify) = sizeof(struct sctp_adaptation_event);
3766 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m_notify) = NULL;
3767
3768 /* append to socket */
3769 control = sctp_build_readq_entry(stcb, stcb->asoc.primary_destination,
3770 0, 0, stcb->asoc.context, 0, 0, 0,
3771 m_notify);
3772 if (control == NULL) {
3773 /* no memory */
3774 sctp_m_freem(m_notify);
3775 return;
3776 }
3777 control->length = SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_notify);
3778 control->spec_flags = M_NOTIFICATION;
3779 /* not that we need this */
3780 control->tail_mbuf = m_notify;
3781 sctp_add_to_readq(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb,
3782 control,
3783 &stcb->sctp_socket->so_rcv, 1, SCTP_READ_LOCK_NOT_HELD, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
3784}
3785
3786/* This always must be called with the read-queue LOCKED in the INP */
3787static void
3788sctp_notify_partial_delivery_indication(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, uint32_t error,
3789 uint32_t val, int so_locked)
3790{
3791 struct mbuf *m_notify;
3792 struct sctp_pdapi_event *pdapi;
3793 struct sctp_queued_to_read *control;
3794 struct sockbuf *sb;
3795
3796 if ((stcb == NULL) ||
3797 sctp_stcb_is_feature_off(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_PDAPIEVNT)) {
3798 /* event not enabled */
3799 return;
3800 }
3801 if (stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_CANT_READ) {
3802 return;
3803 }
3804
3805 m_notify = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(sizeof(struct sctp_pdapi_event), 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
3806 if (m_notify == NULL)
3807 /* no space left */
3808 return;
3809 SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_notify) = 0;
3810 pdapi = mtod(m_notify, struct sctp_pdapi_event *);
3811 memset(pdapi, 0, sizeof(struct sctp_pdapi_event));
3812 pdapi->pdapi_type = SCTP_PARTIAL_DELIVERY_EVENT;
3813 pdapi->pdapi_flags = 0;
3814 pdapi->pdapi_length = sizeof(struct sctp_pdapi_event);
3815 pdapi->pdapi_indication = error;
3816 pdapi->pdapi_stream = (val >> 16);
3817 pdapi->pdapi_seq = (val & 0x0000ffff);
3818 pdapi->pdapi_assoc_id = sctp_get_associd(stcb);
3819
3820 SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_notify) = sizeof(struct sctp_pdapi_event);
3821 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m_notify) = NULL;
3822 control = sctp_build_readq_entry(stcb, stcb->asoc.primary_destination,
3823 0, 0, stcb->asoc.context, 0, 0, 0,
3824 m_notify);
3825 if (control == NULL) {
3826 /* no memory */
3827 sctp_m_freem(m_notify);
3828 return;
3829 }
3830 control->length = SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_notify);
3831 control->spec_flags = M_NOTIFICATION;
3832 /* not that we need this */
3833 control->tail_mbuf = m_notify;
3834 sb = &stcb->sctp_socket->so_rcv;
3835 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_SB_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
3836 sctp_sblog(sb, control->do_not_ref_stcb?NULL:stcb, SCTP_LOG_SBALLOC, SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_notify));
3837 }
3838 sctp_sballoc(stcb, sb, m_notify);
3839 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_SB_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
3840 sctp_sblog(sb, control->do_not_ref_stcb?NULL:stcb, SCTP_LOG_SBRESULT, 0);
3841 }
3842 control->end_added = 1;
3843 if (stcb->asoc.control_pdapi)
3844 TAILQ_INSERT_AFTER(&stcb->sctp_ep->read_queue, stcb->asoc.control_pdapi, control, next);
3845 else {
3846 /* we really should not see this case */
3847 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&stcb->sctp_ep->read_queue, control, next);
3848 }
3849 if (stcb->sctp_ep && stcb->sctp_socket) {
3850 /* This should always be the case */
3851#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3852 struct socket *so;
3853
3854 so = SCTP_INP_SO(stcb->sctp_ep);
3855 if (!so_locked) {
3856 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
3857 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
3858 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 1);
3859 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
3860 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
3861 if (stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE) {
3862 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
3863 return;
3864 }
3865 }
3866#endif
3867 sctp_sorwakeup(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb->sctp_socket);
3868#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3869 if (!so_locked) {
3870 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
3871 }
3872#endif
3873 }
3874}
3875
3876static void
3877sctp_notify_shutdown_event(struct sctp_tcb *stcb)
3878{
3879 struct mbuf *m_notify;
3880 struct sctp_shutdown_event *sse;
3881 struct sctp_queued_to_read *control;
3882
3883 /*
3884 * For TCP model AND UDP connected sockets we will send an error up
3885 * when an SHUTDOWN completes
3886 */
3887 if ((stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) ||
3888 (stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL)) {
3889 /* mark socket closed for read/write and wakeup! */
3890#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3891 struct socket *so;
3892
3893 so = SCTP_INP_SO(stcb->sctp_ep);
3894 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
3895 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
3896 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 1);
3897 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
3898 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
3899 if (stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_CLOSED_SOCKET) {
3900 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
3901 return;
3902 }
3903#endif
3904 socantsendmore(stcb->sctp_socket);
3905#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
3906 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
3907#endif
3908 }
3909 if (sctp_stcb_is_feature_off(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_RECVSHUTDOWNEVNT)) {
3910 /* event not enabled */
3911 return;
3912 }
3913
3914 m_notify = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(sizeof(struct sctp_shutdown_event), 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
3915 if (m_notify == NULL)
3916 /* no space left */
3917 return;
3918 sse = mtod(m_notify, struct sctp_shutdown_event *);
3919 memset(sse, 0, sizeof(struct sctp_shutdown_event));
3920 sse->sse_type = SCTP_SHUTDOWN_EVENT;
3921 sse->sse_flags = 0;
3922 sse->sse_length = sizeof(struct sctp_shutdown_event);
3923 sse->sse_assoc_id = sctp_get_associd(stcb);
3924
3925 SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_notify) = sizeof(struct sctp_shutdown_event);
3926 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m_notify) = NULL;
3927
3928 /* append to socket */
3929 control = sctp_build_readq_entry(stcb, stcb->asoc.primary_destination,
3930 0, 0, stcb->asoc.context, 0, 0, 0,
3931 m_notify);
3932 if (control == NULL) {
3933 /* no memory */
3934 sctp_m_freem(m_notify);
3935 return;
3936 }
3937 control->length = SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_notify);
3938 control->spec_flags = M_NOTIFICATION;
3939 /* not that we need this */
3940 control->tail_mbuf = m_notify;
3941 sctp_add_to_readq(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb,
3942 control,
3943 &stcb->sctp_socket->so_rcv, 1, SCTP_READ_LOCK_NOT_HELD, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
3944}

3993void
3994sctp_notify_stream_reset_add(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, uint16_t numberin, uint16_t numberout, int flag)
3995{
3996 struct mbuf *m_notify;
3997 struct sctp_queued_to_read *control;
3998 struct sctp_stream_change_event *stradd;
3999
4000 if ((stcb == NULL) ||
4001 (sctp_stcb_is_feature_off(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_STREAM_CHANGEEVNT))) {
4002 /* event not enabled */
4003 return;
4004 }
4005 if ((stcb->asoc.peer_req_out) && flag) {
4006 /* Peer made the request, don't tell the local user */
4007 stcb->asoc.peer_req_out = 0;
4008 return;
4009 }
4010 stcb->asoc.peer_req_out = 0;
4011 m_notify = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(sizeof(struct sctp_stream_change_event), 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
4012 if (m_notify == NULL)
4013 /* no space left */
4014 return;
4015 SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_notify) = 0;
4016 stradd = mtod(m_notify, struct sctp_stream_change_event *);
4017 memset(stradd, 0, sizeof(struct sctp_stream_change_event));
4018 stradd->strchange_type = SCTP_STREAM_CHANGE_EVENT;
4019 stradd->strchange_flags = flag;
4020 stradd->strchange_length = sizeof(struct sctp_stream_change_event);
4021 stradd->strchange_assoc_id = sctp_get_associd(stcb);
4022 stradd->strchange_instrms = numberin;
4023 stradd->strchange_outstrms = numberout;
4024 SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_notify) = sizeof(struct sctp_stream_change_event);
4025 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m_notify) = NULL;
4026 if (sctp_sbspace(&stcb->asoc, &stcb->sctp_socket->so_rcv) < SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_notify)) {
4027 /* no space */
4028 sctp_m_freem(m_notify);
4029 return;
4030 }
4031 /* append to socket */
4032 control = sctp_build_readq_entry(stcb, stcb->asoc.primary_destination,
4033 0, 0, stcb->asoc.context, 0, 0, 0,
4034 m_notify);
4035 if (control == NULL) {
4036 /* no memory */
4037 sctp_m_freem(m_notify);
4038 return;
4039 }
4040 control->length = SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_notify);
4041 control->spec_flags = M_NOTIFICATION;
4042 /* not that we need this */
4043 control->tail_mbuf = m_notify;
4044 sctp_add_to_readq(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb,
4045 control,
4046 &stcb->sctp_socket->so_rcv, 1, SCTP_READ_LOCK_NOT_HELD, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
4047}

4098
4099static void
4100sctp_notify_stream_reset(struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
4101 int number_entries, uint16_t * list, int flag)
4102{
4103 struct mbuf *m_notify;
4104 struct sctp_queued_to_read *control;
4105 struct sctp_stream_reset_event *strreset;
4106 int len;
4107
4108 if ((stcb == NULL) ||
4109 (sctp_stcb_is_feature_off(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_STREAM_RESETEVNT))) {
4110 /* event not enabled */
4111 return;
4112 }
4113
4114 m_notify = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(MCLBYTES, 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
4115 if (m_notify == NULL)
4116 /* no space left */
4117 return;
4118 SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_notify) = 0;
4119 len = sizeof(struct sctp_stream_reset_event) + (number_entries * sizeof(uint16_t));
4120 if (len > M_TRAILINGSPACE(m_notify)) {
4121 /* never enough room */
4122 sctp_m_freem(m_notify);
4123 return;
4124 }
4125 strreset = mtod(m_notify, struct sctp_stream_reset_event *);
4126 memset(strreset, 0, len);
4127 strreset->strreset_type = SCTP_STREAM_RESET_EVENT;
4128 strreset->strreset_flags = flag;
4129 strreset->strreset_length = len;
4130 strreset->strreset_assoc_id = sctp_get_associd(stcb);
4131 if (number_entries) {
4132 int i;
4133
4134 for (i = 0; i < number_entries; i++) {
4135 strreset->strreset_stream_list[i] = ntohs(list[i]);
4136 }
4137 }
4138 SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_notify) = len;
4139 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m_notify) = NULL;
4140 if (sctp_sbspace(&stcb->asoc, &stcb->sctp_socket->so_rcv) < SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_notify)) {
4141 /* no space */
4142 sctp_m_freem(m_notify);
4143 return;
4144 }
4145 /* append to socket */
4146 control = sctp_build_readq_entry(stcb, stcb->asoc.primary_destination,
4147 0, 0, stcb->asoc.context, 0, 0, 0,
4148 m_notify);
4149 if (control == NULL) {
4150 /* no memory */
4151 sctp_m_freem(m_notify);
4152 return;
4153 }
4154 control->length = SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_notify);
4155 control->spec_flags = M_NOTIFICATION;
4156 /* not that we need this */
4157 control->tail_mbuf = m_notify;
4158 sctp_add_to_readq(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb,
4159 control,
4160 &stcb->sctp_socket->so_rcv, 1, SCTP_READ_LOCK_NOT_HELD, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
4161}
4162
4163static void
4164sctp_notify_remote_error(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, uint16_t error, struct sctp_error_chunk *chunk)
4165{
4166 struct mbuf *m_notify;
4167 struct sctp_remote_error *sre;
4168 struct sctp_queued_to_read *control;
4169 unsigned int notif_len;
4170 uint16_t chunk_len;
4171
4172 if ((stcb == NULL) ||
4173 sctp_stcb_is_feature_off(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_RECVPEERERR)) {
4174 return;
4175 }
4176 if (chunk != NULL) {
4177 chunk_len = ntohs(chunk->ch.chunk_length);
4178 /*
4179 * Only SCTP_CHUNK_BUFFER_SIZE are guaranteed to be
4180 * contiguous.
4181 */
4182 if (chunk_len > SCTP_CHUNK_BUFFER_SIZE) {
4183 chunk_len = SCTP_CHUNK_BUFFER_SIZE;
4184 }
4185 } else {
4186 chunk_len = 0;
4187 }
4188 notif_len = (unsigned int)(sizeof(struct sctp_remote_error) + chunk_len);
4189 m_notify = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(notif_len, 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
4190 if (m_notify == NULL) {
4191 /* Retry with smaller value. */
4192 notif_len = (unsigned int)sizeof(struct sctp_remote_error);
4193 m_notify = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(notif_len, 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
4194 if (m_notify == NULL) {
4195 return;
4196 }
4197 }
4198 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m_notify) = NULL;
4199 sre = mtod(m_notify, struct sctp_remote_error *);
4200 memset(sre, 0, notif_len);
4201 sre->sre_type = SCTP_REMOTE_ERROR;
4202 sre->sre_flags = 0;
4203 sre->sre_length = sizeof(struct sctp_remote_error);
4204 sre->sre_error = error;
4205 sre->sre_assoc_id = sctp_get_associd(stcb);
4206 if (notif_len > sizeof(struct sctp_remote_error)) {
4207 memcpy(sre->sre_data, chunk, chunk_len);
4208 sre->sre_length += chunk_len;
4209 }
4210 SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_notify) = sre->sre_length;
4211 control = sctp_build_readq_entry(stcb, stcb->asoc.primary_destination,
4212 0, 0, stcb->asoc.context, 0, 0, 0,
4213 m_notify);
4214 if (control != NULL) {
4215 control->length = SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_notify);
4216 control->spec_flags = M_NOTIFICATION;
4217 /* not that we need this */
4218 control->tail_mbuf = m_notify;
4219 sctp_add_to_readq(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb,
4220 control,
4221 &stcb->sctp_socket->so_rcv, 1,
4222 SCTP_READ_LOCK_NOT_HELD, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
4223 } else {
4224 sctp_m_freem(m_notify);
4225 }
4226}
4227
4228void
4229sctp_ulp_notify(uint32_t notification, struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
4230 uint32_t error, void *data, int so_locked)
4231{
4232 if ((stcb == NULL) ||
4233 (stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE) ||
4234 (stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_ALLGONE) ||
4235 (stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_CLOSED_SOCKET)) {
4236 /* If the socket is gone we are out of here */
4237 return;
4238 }
4239#if (defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(_WIN32)) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4240 if (stcb->sctp_socket->so_rcv.sb_state & SBS_CANTRCVMORE) {
4241#else
4242 if (stcb->sctp_socket->so_state & SS_CANTRCVMORE) {
4243#endif
4244 return;
4245 }
4246#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4247 if (so_locked) {
4248 sctp_lock_assert(SCTP_INP_SO(stcb->sctp_ep));
4249 } else {
4250 sctp_unlock_assert(SCTP_INP_SO(stcb->sctp_ep));
4251 }
4252#endif
4253 if ((SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_WAIT) ||
4254 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_ECHOED)) {
4255 if ((notification == SCTP_NOTIFY_INTERFACE_DOWN) ||
4256 (notification == SCTP_NOTIFY_INTERFACE_UP) ||
4257 (notification == SCTP_NOTIFY_INTERFACE_CONFIRMED)) {
4258 /* Don't report these in front states */
4259 return;
4260 }
4261 }
4262 switch (notification) {
4263 case SCTP_NOTIFY_ASSOC_UP:
4264 if (stcb->asoc.assoc_up_sent == 0) {
4265 sctp_notify_assoc_change(SCTP_COMM_UP, stcb, error, NULL, 0, so_locked);
4266 stcb->asoc.assoc_up_sent = 1;
4267 }
4268 if (stcb->asoc.adaptation_needed && (stcb->asoc.adaptation_sent == 0)) {
4269 sctp_notify_adaptation_layer(stcb);
4270 }
4271 if (stcb->asoc.auth_supported == 0) {
4272 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_NO_PEER_AUTH, stcb, 0,
4273 NULL, so_locked);
4274 }
4275 break;
4276 case SCTP_NOTIFY_ASSOC_DOWN:
4277 sctp_notify_assoc_change(SCTP_SHUTDOWN_COMP, stcb, error, NULL, 0, so_locked);
4278#if defined(__Userspace__)
4279 if (stcb->sctp_ep->recv_callback) {
4280 if (stcb->sctp_socket) {
4281 union sctp_sockstore addr;
4282 struct sctp_rcvinfo rcv;
4283
4284 memset(&addr, 0, sizeof(union sctp_sockstore));
4285 memset(&rcv, 0, sizeof(struct sctp_rcvinfo));
4286 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
4287 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
4288 stcb->sctp_ep->recv_callback(stcb->sctp_socket, addr, NULL, 0, rcv, 0, stcb->sctp_ep->ulp_info);
4289 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
4290 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
4291 }
4292 }
4293#endif
4294 break;
4295 case SCTP_NOTIFY_INTERFACE_DOWN:
4296 {
4297 struct sctp_nets *net;
4298
4299 net = (struct sctp_nets *)data;
4300 sctp_notify_peer_addr_change(stcb, SCTP_ADDR_UNREACHABLE,
4301 (struct sockaddr *)&net->ro._l_addr, error, so_locked);
4302 break;
4303 }
4304 case SCTP_NOTIFY_INTERFACE_UP:
4305 {
4306 struct sctp_nets *net;
4307
4308 net = (struct sctp_nets *)data;
4309 sctp_notify_peer_addr_change(stcb, SCTP_ADDR_AVAILABLE,
4310 (struct sockaddr *)&net->ro._l_addr, error, so_locked);
4311 break;
4312 }
4313 case SCTP_NOTIFY_INTERFACE_CONFIRMED:
4314 {
4315 struct sctp_nets *net;
4316
4317 net = (struct sctp_nets *)data;
4318 sctp_notify_peer_addr_change(stcb, SCTP_ADDR_CONFIRMED,
4319 (struct sockaddr *)&net->ro._l_addr, error, so_locked);
4320 break;
4321 }
4322 case SCTP_NOTIFY_SPECIAL_SP_FAIL:
4323 sctp_notify_send_failed2(stcb, error,
4324 (struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *)data, so_locked);
4325 break;
4326 case SCTP_NOTIFY_SENT_DG_FAIL:
4327 sctp_notify_send_failed(stcb, 1, error,
4328 (struct sctp_tmit_chunk *)data, so_locked);
4329 break;
4330 case SCTP_NOTIFY_UNSENT_DG_FAIL:
4331 sctp_notify_send_failed(stcb, 0, error,
4332 (struct sctp_tmit_chunk *)data, so_locked);
4333 break;
4334 case SCTP_NOTIFY_PARTIAL_DELVIERY_INDICATION:
4335 {
4336 uint32_t val;
4337 val = *((uint32_t *)data);
4338
4339 sctp_notify_partial_delivery_indication(stcb, error, val, so_locked);
4340 break;
4341 }
4342 case SCTP_NOTIFY_ASSOC_LOC_ABORTED:
4343 if ((SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_WAIT) ||
4344 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_ECHOED)) {
4345 sctp_notify_assoc_change(SCTP_CANT_STR_ASSOC, stcb, error, data, 0, so_locked);
4346 } else {
4347 sctp_notify_assoc_change(SCTP_COMM_LOST, stcb, error, data, 0, so_locked);
4348 }
4349 break;
4350 case SCTP_NOTIFY_ASSOC_REM_ABORTED:
4351 if ((SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_WAIT) ||
4352 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_COOKIE_ECHOED)) {
4353 sctp_notify_assoc_change(SCTP_CANT_STR_ASSOC, stcb, error, data, 1, so_locked);
4354 } else {
4355 sctp_notify_assoc_change(SCTP_COMM_LOST, stcb, error, data, 1, so_locked);
4356 }
4357 break;
4358 case SCTP_NOTIFY_ASSOC_RESTART:
4359 sctp_notify_assoc_change(SCTP_RESTART, stcb, error, NULL, 0, so_locked);
4360 if (stcb->asoc.auth_supported == 0) {
4361 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_NO_PEER_AUTH, stcb, 0,
4362 NULL, so_locked);
4363 }
4364 break;
4365 case SCTP_NOTIFY_STR_RESET_SEND:
4366 sctp_notify_stream_reset(stcb, error, ((uint16_t *) data), SCTP_STREAM_RESET_OUTGOING_SSN);
4367 break;
4368 case SCTP_NOTIFY_STR_RESET_RECV:
4369 sctp_notify_stream_reset(stcb, error, ((uint16_t *) data), SCTP_STREAM_RESET_INCOMING);
4370 break;
4371 case SCTP_NOTIFY_STR_RESET_FAILED_OUT:
4372 sctp_notify_stream_reset(stcb, error, ((uint16_t *) data),
4373 (SCTP_STREAM_RESET_OUTGOING_SSN|SCTP_STREAM_RESET_FAILED));
4374 break;
4375 case SCTP_NOTIFY_STR_RESET_DENIED_OUT:
4376 sctp_notify_stream_reset(stcb, error, ((uint16_t *) data),
4377 (SCTP_STREAM_RESET_OUTGOING_SSN|SCTP_STREAM_RESET_DENIED));
4378 break;
4379 case SCTP_NOTIFY_STR_RESET_FAILED_IN:
4380 sctp_notify_stream_reset(stcb, error, ((uint16_t *) data),
4381 (SCTP_STREAM_RESET_INCOMING|SCTP_STREAM_RESET_FAILED));
4382 break;
4383 case SCTP_NOTIFY_STR_RESET_DENIED_IN:
4384 sctp_notify_stream_reset(stcb, error, ((uint16_t *) data),
4385 (SCTP_STREAM_RESET_INCOMING|SCTP_STREAM_RESET_DENIED));
4386 break;
4387 case SCTP_NOTIFY_ASCONF_ADD_IP:
4388 sctp_notify_peer_addr_change(stcb, SCTP_ADDR_ADDED, data,
4389 error, so_locked);
4390 break;
4391 case SCTP_NOTIFY_ASCONF_DELETE_IP:
4392 sctp_notify_peer_addr_change(stcb, SCTP_ADDR_REMOVED, data,
4393 error, so_locked);
4394 break;
4395 case SCTP_NOTIFY_ASCONF_SET_PRIMARY:
4396 sctp_notify_peer_addr_change(stcb, SCTP_ADDR_MADE_PRIM, data,
4397 error, so_locked);
4398 break;
4399 case SCTP_NOTIFY_PEER_SHUTDOWN:
4400 sctp_notify_shutdown_event(stcb);
4401 break;
4402 case SCTP_NOTIFY_AUTH_NEW_KEY:
4403 sctp_notify_authentication(stcb, SCTP_AUTH_NEW_KEY, error,
4404 (uint16_t)(uintptr_t)data,
4405 so_locked);
4406 break;
4407 case SCTP_NOTIFY_AUTH_FREE_KEY:
4408 sctp_notify_authentication(stcb, SCTP_AUTH_FREE_KEY, error,
4409 (uint16_t)(uintptr_t)data,
4410 so_locked);
4411 break;
4412 case SCTP_NOTIFY_NO_PEER_AUTH:
4413 sctp_notify_authentication(stcb, SCTP_AUTH_NO_AUTH, error,
4414 (uint16_t)(uintptr_t)data,
4415 so_locked);
4416 break;
4417 case SCTP_NOTIFY_SENDER_DRY:
4418 sctp_notify_sender_dry_event(stcb, so_locked);
4419 break;
4420 case SCTP_NOTIFY_REMOTE_ERROR:
4421 sctp_notify_remote_error(stcb, error, data);
4422 break;
4423 default:
4424 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_UTIL1, "%s: unknown notification %xh (%u)\n",
4425 __func__, notification, notification);
4426 break;
4427 } /* end switch */
4428}
4429
4430void
4431sctp_report_all_outbound(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, uint16_t error, int so_locked)
4432{
4433 struct sctp_association *asoc;
4434 struct sctp_stream_out *outs;
4435 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk, *nchk;
4436 struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *sp, *nsp;
4437 int i;
4438
4439 if (stcb == NULL) {
4440 return;
4441 }
4442 asoc = &stcb->asoc;
4443 if (asoc->state & SCTP_STATE_ABOUT_TO_BE_FREED) {
4444 /* already being freed */
4445 return;
4446 }
4447#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4448 if (so_locked) {
4449 sctp_lock_assert(SCTP_INP_SO(stcb->sctp_ep));
4450 } else {
4451 sctp_unlock_assert(SCTP_INP_SO(stcb->sctp_ep));
4452 }
4453#endif
4454 if ((stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE) ||
4455 (stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_ALLGONE) ||
4456 (asoc->state & SCTP_STATE_CLOSED_SOCKET)) {
4457 return;
4458 }
4459 /* now through all the gunk freeing chunks */
4460 /* sent queue SHOULD be empty */
4461 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(chk, &asoc->sent_queue, sctp_next, nchk) {
4462 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->sent_queue, chk, sctp_next);
4463 asoc->sent_queue_cnt--;
4464 if (chk->sent != SCTP_DATAGRAM_NR_ACKED) {
4465 if (asoc->strmout[chk->rec.data.sid].chunks_on_queues > 0) {
4466 asoc->strmout[chk->rec.data.sid].chunks_on_queues--;
4467#ifdef INVARIANTS
4468 } else {
4469 panic("No chunks on the queues for sid %u.", chk->rec.data.sid);
4470#endif
4471 }
4472 }
4473 if (chk->data != NULL) {
4474 sctp_free_bufspace(stcb, asoc, chk, 1);
4475 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_SENT_DG_FAIL, stcb,
4476 error, chk, so_locked);
4477 if (chk->data) {
4478 sctp_m_freem(chk->data);
4479 chk->data = NULL;
4480 }
4481 }
4482 sctp_free_a_chunk(stcb, chk, so_locked);
4483 /*sa_ignore FREED_MEMORY*/
4484 }
4485 /* pending send queue SHOULD be empty */
4486 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(chk, &asoc->send_queue, sctp_next, nchk) {
4487 TAILQ_REMOVE(&asoc->send_queue, chk, sctp_next);
4488 asoc->send_queue_cnt--;
4489 if (asoc->strmout[chk->rec.data.sid].chunks_on_queues > 0) {
4490 asoc->strmout[chk->rec.data.sid].chunks_on_queues--;
4491#ifdef INVARIANTS
4492 } else {
4493 panic("No chunks on the queues for sid %u.", chk->rec.data.sid);
4494#endif
4495 }
4496 if (chk->data != NULL) {
4497 sctp_free_bufspace(stcb, asoc, chk, 1);
4498 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_UNSENT_DG_FAIL, stcb,
4499 error, chk, so_locked);
4500 if (chk->data) {
4501 sctp_m_freem(chk->data);
4502 chk->data = NULL;
4503 }
4504 }
4505 sctp_free_a_chunk(stcb, chk, so_locked);
4506 /*sa_ignore FREED_MEMORY*/
4507 }
4508 for (i = 0; i < asoc->streamoutcnt; i++) {
4509 /* For each stream */
4510 outs = &asoc->strmout[i];
4511 /* clean up any sends there */
4512 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(sp, &outs->outqueue, next, nsp) {
4513 atomic_subtract_int(&asoc->stream_queue_cnt, 1);
4514 TAILQ_REMOVE(&outs->outqueue, sp, next);
4515 stcb->asoc.ss_functions.sctp_ss_remove_from_stream(stcb, asoc, outs, sp, 1);
4516 sctp_free_spbufspace(stcb, asoc, sp);
4517 if (sp->data) {
4518 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_SPECIAL_SP_FAIL, stcb,
4519 error, (void *)sp, so_locked);
4520 if (sp->data) {
4521 sctp_m_freem(sp->data);
4522 sp->data = NULL;
4523 sp->tail_mbuf = NULL;
4524 sp->length = 0;
4525 }
4526 }
4527 if (sp->net) {
4528 sctp_free_remote_addr(sp->net);
4529 sp->net = NULL;
4530 }
4531 /* Free the chunk */
4532 sctp_free_a_strmoq(stcb, sp, so_locked);
4533 /*sa_ignore FREED_MEMORY*/
4534 }
4535 }
4536}
4537
4538void
4539sctp_abort_notification(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, uint8_t from_peer, uint16_t error,
4540 struct sctp_abort_chunk *abort, int so_locked)
4541{
4542 if (stcb == NULL) {
4543 return;
4544 }
4545#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4546 if (so_locked) {
4547 sctp_lock_assert(SCTP_INP_SO(stcb->sctp_ep));
4548 } else {
4549 sctp_unlock_assert(SCTP_INP_SO(stcb->sctp_ep));
4550 }
4551#endif
4552 if ((stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL) ||
4553 ((stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) &&
4554 (stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_CONNECTED))) {
4555 stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags |= SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_WAS_ABORTED;
4556 }
4557 if ((stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE) ||
4558 (stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_ALLGONE) ||
4559 (stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_CLOSED_SOCKET)) {
4560 return;
4561 }
4562 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
4563 SCTP_ADD_SUBSTATE(stcb, SCTP_STATE_WAS_ABORTED);
4564 /* Tell them we lost the asoc */
4565 sctp_report_all_outbound(stcb, error, so_locked);
4566 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
4567 if (from_peer) {
4568 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_ASSOC_REM_ABORTED, stcb, error, abort, so_locked);
4569 } else {
4570 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_ASSOC_LOC_ABORTED, stcb, error, abort, so_locked);
4571 }
4572}
4573
4574void
4575sctp_abort_association(struct sctp_inpcb *inp, struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
4576 struct mbuf *m, int iphlen,
4577 struct sockaddr *src, struct sockaddr *dst,
4578 struct sctphdr *sh, struct mbuf *op_err,
4579#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4580 uint8_t mflowtype, uint32_t mflowid,
4581#endif
4582 uint32_t vrf_id, uint16_t port)
4583{
4584 uint32_t vtag;
4585#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4586 struct socket *so;
4587#endif
4588
4589 vtag = 0;
4590 if (stcb != NULL) {
4591 vtag = stcb->asoc.peer_vtag;
4592 vrf_id = stcb->asoc.vrf_id;
4593 }
4594 sctp_send_abort(m, iphlen, src, dst, sh, vtag, op_err,
4595#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4596 mflowtype, mflowid, inp->fibnum,
4597#endif
4598 vrf_id, port);
4599 if (stcb != NULL) {
4600 /* We have a TCB to abort, send notification too */
4601 sctp_abort_notification(stcb, 0, 0, NULL, SCTP_SO_NOT_LOCKED);
4602 /* Ok, now lets free it */
4603#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4604 so = SCTP_INP_SO(inp);
4605 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
4606 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
4607 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 1);
4608 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
4609 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
4610#endif
4611 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER32(sctps_aborted);
4612 if ((SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_OPEN) ||
4613 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_RECEIVED)) {
4614 SCTP_STAT_DECR_GAUGE32(sctps_currestab);
4615 }
4616 (void)sctp_free_assoc(inp, stcb, SCTP_NORMAL_PROC,
4617 SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL + SCTP_LOC_4);
4618#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4619 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
4620#endif
4621 }
4622}
4623#ifdef SCTP_ASOCLOG_OF_TSNS
4624void
4625sctp_print_out_track_log(struct sctp_tcb *stcb)
4626{
4627#ifdef NOSIY_PRINTS

4632 SCTP_PRINTF("None rcvd\n");

4635 if (stcb->asoc.tsn_in_wrapped) {
4636 for (i = stcb->asoc.tsn_in_at; i < SCTP_TSN_LOG_SIZE; i++) {
4637 SCTP_PRINTF("TSN:%x strm:%d seq:%d flags:%x sz:%d\n",
4638 stcb->asoc.in_tsnlog[i].tsn,
4639 stcb->asoc.in_tsnlog[i].strm,
4640 stcb->asoc.in_tsnlog[i].seq,
4641 stcb->asoc.in_tsnlog[i].flgs,
4642 stcb->asoc.in_tsnlog[i].sz);
4643 }
4644 }
4645 if (stcb->asoc.tsn_in_at) {
