4647 SCTP_PRINTF("TSN:%x strm:%d seq:%d flags:%x sz:%d\n",
4648 stcb->asoc.in_tsnlog[i].tsn,
4649 stcb->asoc.in_tsnlog[i].strm,
4650 stcb->asoc.in_tsnlog[i].seq,
4651 stcb->asoc.in_tsnlog[i].flgs,
4652 stcb->asoc.in_tsnlog[i].sz);
4653 }
4654 }
4655 none_in:
4656 SCTP_PRINTF("OUT bound TSN log-aaa\n");
4657 if ((stcb->asoc.tsn_out_at == 0) &&
4658 (stcb->asoc.tsn_out_wrapped == 0)) {
4659 SCTP_PRINTF("None sent\n");
4660 }
4661 if (stcb->asoc.tsn_out_wrapped) {
4662 for (i = stcb->asoc.tsn_out_at; i < SCTP_TSN_LOG_SIZE; i++) {
4663 SCTP_PRINTF("TSN:%x strm:%d seq:%d flags:%x sz:%d\n",
4664 stcb->asoc.out_tsnlog[i].tsn,
4665 stcb->asoc.out_tsnlog[i].strm,
4666 stcb->asoc.out_tsnlog[i].seq,
4667 stcb->asoc.out_tsnlog[i].flgs,
4668 stcb->asoc.out_tsnlog[i].sz);
4669 }
4670 }
4671 if (stcb->asoc.tsn_out_at) {
4672 for (i = 0; i < stcb->asoc.tsn_out_at; i++) {
4673 SCTP_PRINTF("TSN:%x strm:%d seq:%d flags:%x sz:%d\n",
4674 stcb->asoc.out_tsnlog[i].tsn,
4675 stcb->asoc.out_tsnlog[i].strm,
4676 stcb->asoc.out_tsnlog[i].seq,
4677 stcb->asoc.out_tsnlog[i].flgs,
4678 stcb->asoc.out_tsnlog[i].sz);
4679 }
4680 }
4681#endif
4682}
4683#endif
4684
4685void
4686sctp_abort_an_association(struct sctp_inpcb *inp, struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
4687 struct mbuf *op_err,
4688 int so_locked)
4689{
4690#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4691 struct socket *so;
4692#endif
4693
4694#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4695 so = SCTP_INP_SO(inp);
4696#endif
4697#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4698 if (so_locked) {
4699 sctp_lock_assert(SCTP_INP_SO(inp));
4700 } else {
4701 sctp_unlock_assert(SCTP_INP_SO(inp));
4702 }
4703#endif
4704 if (stcb == NULL) {
4705 /* Got to have a TCB */
4706 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE) {
4707 if (LIST_EMPTY(&inp->sctp_asoc_list)) {
4708#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4709 if (!so_locked) {
4710 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 1);
4711 }
4712#endif
4713 sctp_inpcb_free(inp, SCTP_FREE_SHOULD_USE_ABORT,
4714 SCTP_CALLED_DIRECTLY_NOCMPSET);
4715#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4716 if (!so_locked) {
4717 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
4718 }
4719#endif
4720 }
4721 }
4722 return;
4723 }
4724 /* notify the peer */
4725 sctp_send_abort_tcb(stcb, op_err, so_locked);
4726 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER32(sctps_aborted);
4727 if ((SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_OPEN) ||
4728 (SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_RECEIVED)) {
4729 SCTP_STAT_DECR_GAUGE32(sctps_currestab);
4730 }
4731 /* notify the ulp */
4732 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE) == 0) {
4733 sctp_abort_notification(stcb, 0, 0, NULL, so_locked);
4734 }
4735 /* now free the asoc */
4736#ifdef SCTP_ASOCLOG_OF_TSNS
4737 sctp_print_out_track_log(stcb);
4738#endif
4739#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4740 if (!so_locked) {
4741 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
4742 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
4743 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 1);
4744 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
4745 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
4746 }
4747#endif
4748 (void)sctp_free_assoc(inp, stcb, SCTP_NORMAL_PROC,
4749 SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL + SCTP_LOC_5);
4750#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4751 if (!so_locked) {
4752 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
4753 }
4754#endif
4755}
4756
4757void
4758sctp_handle_ootb(struct mbuf *m, int iphlen, int offset,
4759 struct sockaddr *src, struct sockaddr *dst,
4760 struct sctphdr *sh, struct sctp_inpcb *inp,
4761 struct mbuf *cause,
4762#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4763 uint8_t mflowtype, uint32_t mflowid, uint16_t fibnum,
4764#endif
4765 uint32_t vrf_id, uint16_t port)
4766{
4767 struct sctp_chunkhdr *ch, chunk_buf;
4768 unsigned int chk_length;
4769 int contains_init_chunk;
4770
4771 SCTP_STAT_INCR_COUNTER32(sctps_outoftheblue);
4772 /* Generate a TO address for future reference */
4773 if (inp && (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE)) {
4774 if (LIST_EMPTY(&inp->sctp_asoc_list)) {
4775#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4776 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(SCTP_INP_SO(inp), 1);
4777#endif
4778 sctp_inpcb_free(inp, SCTP_FREE_SHOULD_USE_ABORT,
4779 SCTP_CALLED_DIRECTLY_NOCMPSET);
4780#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4781 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(SCTP_INP_SO(inp), 1);
4782#endif
4783 }
4784 }
4785 contains_init_chunk = 0;
4786 ch = (struct sctp_chunkhdr *)sctp_m_getptr(m, offset,
4787 sizeof(*ch), (uint8_t *) & chunk_buf);
4788 while (ch != NULL) {
4789 chk_length = ntohs(ch->chunk_length);
4790 if (chk_length < sizeof(*ch)) {
4791 /* break to abort land */
4792 break;
4793 }
4794 switch (ch->chunk_type) {
4795 case SCTP_INIT:
4796 contains_init_chunk = 1;
4797 break;
4798 case SCTP_PACKET_DROPPED:
4799 /* we don't respond to pkt-dropped */
4800 return;
4801 case SCTP_ABORT_ASSOCIATION:
4802 /* we don't respond with an ABORT to an ABORT */
4803 return;
4804 case SCTP_SHUTDOWN_COMPLETE:
4805 /*
4806 * we ignore it since we are not waiting for it and
4807 * peer is gone
4808 */
4809 return;
4810 case SCTP_SHUTDOWN_ACK:
4811 sctp_send_shutdown_complete2(src, dst, sh,
4812#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4813 mflowtype, mflowid, fibnum,
4814#endif
4815 vrf_id, port);
4816 return;
4817 default:
4818 break;
4819 }
4820 offset += SCTP_SIZE32(chk_length);
4821 ch = (struct sctp_chunkhdr *)sctp_m_getptr(m, offset,
4822 sizeof(*ch), (uint8_t *) & chunk_buf);
4823 }
4824 if ((SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_blackhole) == 0) ||
4825 ((SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_blackhole) == 1) &&
4826 (contains_init_chunk == 0))) {
4827 sctp_send_abort(m, iphlen, src, dst, sh, 0, cause,
4828#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
4829 mflowtype, mflowid, fibnum,
4830#endif
4831 vrf_id, port);
4832 }
4833}
4834
4835/*
4836 * check the inbound datagram to make sure there is not an abort inside it,
4837 * if there is return 1, else return 0.
4838 */
4839int
4840sctp_is_there_an_abort_here(struct mbuf *m, int iphlen, uint32_t *vtag)
4841{
4842 struct sctp_chunkhdr *ch;
4843 struct sctp_init_chunk *init_chk, chunk_buf;
4844 int offset;
4845 unsigned int chk_length;
4846
4847 offset = iphlen + sizeof(struct sctphdr);
4848 ch = (struct sctp_chunkhdr *)sctp_m_getptr(m, offset, sizeof(*ch),
4849 (uint8_t *) & chunk_buf);
4850 while (ch != NULL) {
4851 chk_length = ntohs(ch->chunk_length);
4852 if (chk_length < sizeof(*ch)) {
4853 /* packet is probably corrupt */
4854 break;
4855 }
4856 /* we seem to be ok, is it an abort? */
4857 if (ch->chunk_type == SCTP_ABORT_ASSOCIATION) {
4858 /* yep, tell them */
4859 return (1);
4860 }
4861 if ((ch->chunk_type == SCTP_INITIATION) ||
4862 (ch->chunk_type == SCTP_INITIATION_ACK)) {
4863 /* need to update the Vtag */
4864 init_chk = (struct sctp_init_chunk *)sctp_m_getptr(m,
4865 offset, sizeof(struct sctp_init_chunk), (uint8_t *) & chunk_buf);
4866 if (init_chk != NULL) {
4867 *vtag = ntohl(init_chk->init.initiate_tag);
4868 }
4869 }
4870 /* Nope, move to the next chunk */
4871 offset += SCTP_SIZE32(chk_length);
4872 ch = (struct sctp_chunkhdr *)sctp_m_getptr(m, offset,
4873 sizeof(*ch), (uint8_t *) & chunk_buf);
4874 }
4875 return (0);
4876}
4877
4878/*
4879 * currently (2/02), ifa_addr embeds scope_id's and don't have sin6_scope_id
4880 * set (i.e. it's 0) so, create this function to compare link local scopes
4881 */
4882#ifdef INET6
4883uint32_t
4884sctp_is_same_scope(struct sockaddr_in6 *addr1, struct sockaddr_in6 *addr2)
4885{
4886#if defined(__Userspace__)
4887 /*__Userspace__ Returning 1 here always */
4888#endif
4889#if defined(SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE)
4890 struct sockaddr_in6 a, b;
4891
4892 /* save copies */
4893 a = *addr1;
4894 b = *addr2;
4895
4896 if (a.sin6_scope_id == 0)
4897#ifdef SCTP_KAME
4898 if (sa6_recoverscope(&a)) {
4899#else
4900 if (in6_recoverscope(&a, &a.sin6_addr, NULL)) {
4901#endif /* SCTP_KAME */
4902 /* can't get scope, so can't match */
4903 return (0);
4904 }
4905 if (b.sin6_scope_id == 0)
4906#ifdef SCTP_KAME
4907 if (sa6_recoverscope(&b)) {
4908#else
4909 if (in6_recoverscope(&b, &b.sin6_addr, NULL)) {
4910#endif /* SCTP_KAME */
4911 /* can't get scope, so can't match */
4912 return (0);
4913 }
4914 if (a.sin6_scope_id != b.sin6_scope_id)
4915 return (0);
4916#else
4917 if (addr1->sin6_scope_id != addr2->sin6_scope_id)
4918 return (0);
4919#endif /* SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE */
4920
4921 return (1);
4922}
4923
4924#if defined(SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE)
4925/*
4926 * returns a sockaddr_in6 with embedded scope recovered and removed
4927 */
4928struct sockaddr_in6 *
4929sctp_recover_scope(struct sockaddr_in6 *addr, struct sockaddr_in6 *store)
4930{
4931 /* check and strip embedded scope junk */
4932 if (addr->sin6_family == AF_INET6) {
4933 if (IN6_IS_SCOPE_LINKLOCAL(&addr->sin6_addr)) {
4934 if (addr->sin6_scope_id == 0) {
4935 *store = *addr;
4936#ifdef SCTP_KAME
4937 if (!sa6_recoverscope(store)) {
4938#else
4939 if (!in6_recoverscope(store, &store->sin6_addr,
4940 NULL)) {
4941#endif /* SCTP_KAME */
4942 /* use the recovered scope */
4943 addr = store;
4944 }
4945 } else {
4946 /* else, return the original "to" addr */
4947 in6_clearscope(&addr->sin6_addr);
4948 }
4949 }
4950 }
4951 return (addr);
4952}
4953#endif /* SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE */
4954#endif
4955
4956/*
4957 * are the two addresses the same? currently a "scopeless" check returns: 1
4958 * if same, 0 if not
4959 */
4960int
4961sctp_cmpaddr(struct sockaddr *sa1, struct sockaddr *sa2)
4962{
4963
4964 /* must be valid */
4965 if (sa1 == NULL || sa2 == NULL)
4966 return (0);
4967
4968 /* must be the same family */
4969 if (sa1->sa_family != sa2->sa_family)
4970 return (0);
4971
4972 switch (sa1->sa_family) {
4973#ifdef INET6
4974 case AF_INET6:
4975 {
4976 /* IPv6 addresses */
4977 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6_1, *sin6_2;
4978
4979 sin6_1 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)sa1;
4980 sin6_2 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)sa2;
4981 return (SCTP6_ARE_ADDR_EQUAL(sin6_1,
4982 sin6_2));
4983 }
4984#endif
4985#ifdef INET
4986 case AF_INET:
4987 {
4988 /* IPv4 addresses */
4989 struct sockaddr_in *sin_1, *sin_2;
4990
4991 sin_1 = (struct sockaddr_in *)sa1;
4992 sin_2 = (struct sockaddr_in *)sa2;
4993 return (sin_1->sin_addr.s_addr == sin_2->sin_addr.s_addr);
4994 }
4995#endif
4996#if defined(__Userspace__)
4997 case AF_CONN:
4998 {
4999 struct sockaddr_conn *sconn_1, *sconn_2;
5000
5001 sconn_1 = (struct sockaddr_conn *)sa1;
5002 sconn_2 = (struct sockaddr_conn *)sa2;
5003 return (sconn_1->sconn_addr == sconn_2->sconn_addr);
5004 }
5005#endif
5006 default:
5007 /* we don't do these... */
5008 return (0);
5009 }
5010}
5011
5012void
5013sctp_print_address(struct sockaddr *sa)
5014{
5015#ifdef INET6
5016#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5017 char ip6buf[INET6_ADDRSTRLEN];
5018#endif
5019#endif
5020
5021 switch (sa->sa_family) {
5022#ifdef INET6
5023 case AF_INET6:
5024 {
5025 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6;
5026
5027 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)sa;
5028#if defined(__Userspace__)
5029 SCTP_PRINTF("IPv6 address: %x:%x:%x:%x:%x:%x:%x:%x:port:%d scope:%u\n",
5030 ntohs(sin6->sin6_addr.s6_addr16[0]),
5031 ntohs(sin6->sin6_addr.s6_addr16[1]),
5032 ntohs(sin6->sin6_addr.s6_addr16[2]),
5033 ntohs(sin6->sin6_addr.s6_addr16[3]),
5034 ntohs(sin6->sin6_addr.s6_addr16[4]),
5035 ntohs(sin6->sin6_addr.s6_addr16[5]),
5036 ntohs(sin6->sin6_addr.s6_addr16[6]),
5037 ntohs(sin6->sin6_addr.s6_addr16[7]),
5038 ntohs(sin6->sin6_port),
5039 sin6->sin6_scope_id);
5040#else
5041#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5042 SCTP_PRINTF("IPv6 address: %s:port:%d scope:%u\n",
5043 ip6_sprintf(ip6buf, &sin6->sin6_addr),
5044 ntohs(sin6->sin6_port),
5045 sin6->sin6_scope_id);
5046#else
5047 SCTP_PRINTF("IPv6 address: %s:port:%d scope:%u\n",
5048 ip6_sprintf(&sin6->sin6_addr),
5049 ntohs(sin6->sin6_port),
5050 sin6->sin6_scope_id);
5051#endif
5052#endif
5053 break;
5054 }
5055#endif
5056#ifdef INET
5057 case AF_INET:
5058 {
5059 struct sockaddr_in *sin;
5060 unsigned char *p;
5061
5062 sin = (struct sockaddr_in *)sa;
5063 p = (unsigned char *)&sin->sin_addr;
5064 SCTP_PRINTF("IPv4 address: %u.%u.%u.%u:%d\n",
5065 p[0], p[1], p[2], p[3], ntohs(sin->sin_port));
5066 break;
5067 }
5068#endif
5069#if defined(__Userspace__)
5070 case AF_CONN:
5071 {
5072 struct sockaddr_conn *sconn;
5073
5074 sconn = (struct sockaddr_conn *)sa;
5075 SCTP_PRINTF("AF_CONN address: %p\n", sconn->sconn_addr);
5076 break;
5077 }
5078#endif
5079 default:
5080 SCTP_PRINTF("?\n");
5081 break;
5082 }
5083}
5084
5085void
5086sctp_pull_off_control_to_new_inp(struct sctp_inpcb *old_inp,
5087 struct sctp_inpcb *new_inp,
5088 struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
5089 int waitflags)
5090{
5091 /*
5092 * go through our old INP and pull off any control structures that
5093 * belong to stcb and move then to the new inp.
5094 */
5095 struct socket *old_so, *new_so;
5096 struct sctp_queued_to_read *control, *nctl;
5097 struct sctp_readhead tmp_queue;
5098 struct mbuf *m;
5099#if (defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(__APPLE__)) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5100 int error = 0;
5101#endif
5102
5103 old_so = old_inp->sctp_socket;
5104 new_so = new_inp->sctp_socket;
5105 TAILQ_INIT(&tmp_queue);
5106#if (defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(__APPLE__)) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5107 error = sblock(&old_so->so_rcv, waitflags);
5108 if (error) {
5109 /* Gak, can't get sblock, we have a problem.
5110 * data will be left stranded.. and we
5111 * don't dare look at it since the
5112 * other thread may be reading something.
5113 * Oh well, its a screwed up app that does
5114 * a peeloff OR a accept while reading
5115 * from the main socket... actually its
5116 * only the peeloff() case, since I think
5117 * read will fail on a listening socket..
5118 */
5119 return;
5120 }
5121#endif
5122 /* lock the socket buffers */
5123 SCTP_INP_READ_LOCK(old_inp);
5124 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(control, &old_inp->read_queue, next, nctl) {
5125 /* Pull off all for out target stcb */
5126 if (control->stcb == stcb) {
5127 /* remove it we want it */
5128 TAILQ_REMOVE(&old_inp->read_queue, control, next);
5129 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&tmp_queue, control, next);
5130 m = control->data;
5131 while (m) {
5132 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_SB_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
5133 sctp_sblog(&old_so->so_rcv, control->do_not_ref_stcb?NULL:stcb, SCTP_LOG_SBFREE,SCTP_BUF_LEN(m));
5134 }
5135 sctp_sbfree(control, stcb, &old_so->so_rcv, m);
5136 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_SB_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
5137 sctp_sblog(&old_so->so_rcv, control->do_not_ref_stcb?NULL:stcb, SCTP_LOG_SBRESULT, 0);
5138 }
5139 m = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m);
5140 }
5141 }
5142 }
5143 SCTP_INP_READ_UNLOCK(old_inp);
5144 /* Remove the sb-lock on the old socket */
5145#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5146 sbunlock(&old_so->so_rcv, 1);
5147#endif
5148
5149#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5150 sbunlock(&old_so->so_rcv);
5151#endif
5152 /* Now we move them over to the new socket buffer */
5153 SCTP_INP_READ_LOCK(new_inp);
5154 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(control, &tmp_queue, next, nctl) {
5155 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&new_inp->read_queue, control, next);
5156 m = control->data;
5157 while (m) {
5158 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_SB_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
5159 sctp_sblog(&new_so->so_rcv, control->do_not_ref_stcb?NULL:stcb, SCTP_LOG_SBALLOC, SCTP_BUF_LEN(m));
5160 }
5161 sctp_sballoc(stcb, &new_so->so_rcv, m);
5162 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_SB_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
5163 sctp_sblog(&new_so->so_rcv, control->do_not_ref_stcb?NULL:stcb, SCTP_LOG_SBRESULT, 0);
5164 }
5165 m = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m);
5166 }
5167 }
5168 SCTP_INP_READ_UNLOCK(new_inp);
5169}
5170
5171void
5172sctp_wakeup_the_read_socket(struct sctp_inpcb *inp,
5173 struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
5174 int so_locked
5175#if !(defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__))
5176 SCTP_UNUSED
5177#endif
5178)
5179{
5180 if ((inp != NULL) && (inp->sctp_socket != NULL)) {
5181#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5182 struct socket *so;
5183
5184 so = SCTP_INP_SO(inp);
5185 if (!so_locked) {
5186 if (stcb) {
5187 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
5188 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
5189 }
5190 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 1);
5191 if (stcb) {
5192 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
5193 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
5194 }
5195 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE) {
5196 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
5197 return;
5198 }
5199 }
5200#endif
5201 sctp_sorwakeup(inp, inp->sctp_socket);
5202#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5203 if (!so_locked) {
5204 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
5205 }
5206#endif
5207 }
5208}
5209#if defined(__Userspace__)
5210
5211void
5212sctp_invoke_recv_callback(struct sctp_inpcb *inp,
5213 struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
5214 struct sctp_queued_to_read *control,
5215 int inp_read_lock_held)
5216{
5217 uint32_t pd_point, length;
5218
5219 if ((inp->recv_callback == NULL) ||
5220 (stcb == NULL) ||
5221 (stcb->sctp_socket == NULL)) {
5222 return;
5223 }
5224
5225 length = control->length;
5226 if (stcb != NULL && stcb->sctp_socket != NULL) {
5227 pd_point = min(SCTP_SB_LIMIT_RCV(stcb->sctp_socket) >> SCTP_PARTIAL_DELIVERY_SHIFT,
5228 stcb->sctp_ep->partial_delivery_point);
5229 } else {
5230 pd_point = inp->partial_delivery_point;
5231 }
5232 if ((control->end_added == 1) || (length >= pd_point)) {
5233 struct socket *so;
5234 struct mbuf *m;
5235 char *buffer;
5236 struct sctp_rcvinfo rcv;
5237 union sctp_sockstore addr;
5238 int flags;
5239
5240 if ((buffer = malloc(length)) == NULL) {
5241 return;
5242 }
5243 if (inp_read_lock_held == 0) {
5244 SCTP_INP_READ_LOCK(inp);
5245 }
5246 so = stcb->sctp_socket;
5247 for (m = control->data; m; m = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m)) {
5248 sctp_sbfree(control, control->stcb, &so->so_rcv, m);
5249 }
5250 m_copydata(control->data, 0, length, buffer);
5251 memset(&rcv, 0, sizeof(struct sctp_rcvinfo));
5252 rcv.rcv_sid = control->sinfo_stream;
5253 rcv.rcv_ssn = (uint16_t)control->mid;
5254 rcv.rcv_flags = control->sinfo_flags;
5255 rcv.rcv_ppid = control->sinfo_ppid;
5256 rcv.rcv_tsn = control->sinfo_tsn;
5257 rcv.rcv_cumtsn = control->sinfo_cumtsn;
5258 rcv.rcv_context = control->sinfo_context;
5259 rcv.rcv_assoc_id = control->sinfo_assoc_id;
5260 memset(&addr, 0, sizeof(union sctp_sockstore));
5261 switch (control->whoFrom->ro._l_addr.sa.sa_family) {
5262#ifdef INET
5263 case AF_INET:
5264 addr.sin = control->whoFrom->ro._l_addr.sin;
5265 break;
5266#endif
5267#ifdef INET6
5268 case AF_INET6:
5269 addr.sin6 = control->whoFrom->ro._l_addr.sin6;
5270 break;
5271#endif
5272 case AF_CONN:
5273 addr.sconn = control->whoFrom->ro._l_addr.sconn;
5274 break;
5275 default:
5276 addr.sa = control->whoFrom->ro._l_addr.sa;
5277 break;
5278 }
5279 flags = 0;
5280 if (control->end_added == 1) {
5281 flags |= MSG_EOR;
5282 }
5283 if (control->spec_flags & M_NOTIFICATION) {
5284 flags |= MSG_NOTIFICATION;
5285 }
5286 sctp_m_freem(control->data);
5287 control->data = NULL;
5288 control->tail_mbuf = NULL;
5289 control->length = 0;
5290 if (control->end_added) {
5291 TAILQ_REMOVE(&stcb->sctp_ep->read_queue, control, next);
5292 control->on_read_q = 0;
5293 sctp_free_remote_addr(control->whoFrom);
5294 control->whoFrom = NULL;
5295 sctp_free_a_readq(stcb, control);
5296 }
5297 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
5298 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
5299 if (inp_read_lock_held == 0) {
5300 SCTP_INP_READ_UNLOCK(inp);
5301 }
5302 inp->recv_callback(so, addr, buffer, length, rcv, flags, inp->ulp_info);
5303 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
5304 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
5305 }
5306}
5307#endif
5308
5309void
5310sctp_add_to_readq(struct sctp_inpcb *inp,
5311 struct sctp_tcb *stcb,
5312 struct sctp_queued_to_read *control,
5313 struct sockbuf *sb,
5314 int end,
5315 int inp_read_lock_held,
5316 int so_locked)
5317{
5318 /*
5319 * Here we must place the control on the end of the socket read
5320 * queue AND increment sb_cc so that select will work properly on
5321 * read.
5322 */
5323 struct mbuf *m, *prev = NULL;
5324
5325 if (inp == NULL) {
5326 /* Gak, TSNH!! */
5327#ifdef INVARIANTS
5328 panic("Gak, inp NULL on add_to_readq");
5329#endif
5330 return;
5331 }
5332#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5333 if (so_locked) {
5334 sctp_lock_assert(SCTP_INP_SO(inp));
5335 } else {
5336 sctp_unlock_assert(SCTP_INP_SO(inp));
5337 }
5338#endif
5339 if (inp_read_lock_held == 0)
5340 SCTP_INP_READ_LOCK(inp);
5341 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_CANT_READ) {
5342 if (!control->on_strm_q) {
5343 sctp_free_remote_addr(control->whoFrom);
5344 if (control->data) {
5345 sctp_m_freem(control->data);
5346 control->data = NULL;
5347 }
5348 sctp_free_a_readq(stcb, control);
5349 }
5350 if (inp_read_lock_held == 0)
5351 SCTP_INP_READ_UNLOCK(inp);
5352 return;
5353 }
5354 if (!(control->spec_flags & M_NOTIFICATION)) {
5355 atomic_add_int(&inp->total_recvs, 1);
5356 if (!control->do_not_ref_stcb) {
5357 atomic_add_int(&stcb->total_recvs, 1);
5358 }
5359 }
5360 m = control->data;
5361 control->held_length = 0;
5362 control->length = 0;
5363 while (m) {
5364 if (SCTP_BUF_LEN(m) == 0) {
5365 /* Skip mbufs with NO length */
5366 if (prev == NULL) {
5367 /* First one */
5368 control->data = sctp_m_free(m);
5369 m = control->data;
5370 } else {
5371 SCTP_BUF_NEXT(prev) = sctp_m_free(m);
5372 m = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(prev);
5373 }
5374 if (m == NULL) {
5375 control->tail_mbuf = prev;
5376 }
5377 continue;
5378 }
5379 prev = m;
5380 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_SB_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
5381 sctp_sblog(sb, control->do_not_ref_stcb?NULL:stcb, SCTP_LOG_SBALLOC, SCTP_BUF_LEN(m));
5382 }
5383 sctp_sballoc(stcb, sb, m);
5384 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_SB_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
5385 sctp_sblog(sb, control->do_not_ref_stcb?NULL:stcb, SCTP_LOG_SBRESULT, 0);
5386 }
5387 atomic_add_int(&control->length, SCTP_BUF_LEN(m));
5388 m = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m);
5389 }
5390 if (prev != NULL) {
5391 control->tail_mbuf = prev;
5392 } else {
5393 /* Everything got collapsed out?? */
5394 if (!control->on_strm_q) {
5395 sctp_free_remote_addr(control->whoFrom);
5396 sctp_free_a_readq(stcb, control);
5397 }
5398 if (inp_read_lock_held == 0)
5399 SCTP_INP_READ_UNLOCK(inp);
5400 return;
5401 }
5402 if (end) {
5403 control->end_added = 1;
5404 }
5405 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&inp->read_queue, control, next);
5406 control->on_read_q = 1;
5407 if (inp_read_lock_held == 0)
5408 SCTP_INP_READ_UNLOCK(inp);
5409#if defined(__Userspace__)
5410 sctp_invoke_recv_callback(inp, stcb, control, inp_read_lock_held);
5411#endif
5412 if (inp && inp->sctp_socket) {
5413 sctp_wakeup_the_read_socket(inp, stcb, so_locked);
5414 }
5415}
5416
5417/*************HOLD THIS COMMENT FOR PATCH FILE OF
5418 *************ALTERNATE ROUTING CODE
5419 */
5420
5421/*************HOLD THIS COMMENT FOR END OF PATCH FILE OF
5422 *************ALTERNATE ROUTING CODE
5423 */
5424
5425struct mbuf *
5426sctp_generate_cause(uint16_t code, char *info)
5427{
5428 struct mbuf *m;
5429 struct sctp_gen_error_cause *cause;
5430 size_t info_len;
5431 uint16_t len;
5432
5433 if ((code == 0) || (info == NULL)) {
5434 return (NULL);
5435 }
5436 info_len = strlen(info);
5437 if (info_len > (SCTP_MAX_CAUSE_LENGTH - sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr))) {
5438 return (NULL);
5439 }
5440 len = (uint16_t)(sizeof(struct sctp_paramhdr) + info_len);
5441 m = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(len, 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
5442 if (m != NULL) {
5443 SCTP_BUF_LEN(m) = len;
5444 cause = mtod(m, struct sctp_gen_error_cause *);
5445 cause->code = htons(code);
5446 cause->length = htons(len);
5447 memcpy(cause->info, info, info_len);
5448 }
5449 return (m);
5450}
5451
5452struct mbuf *
5453sctp_generate_no_user_data_cause(uint32_t tsn)
5454{
5455 struct mbuf *m;
5456 struct sctp_error_no_user_data *no_user_data_cause;
5457 uint16_t len;
5458
5459 len = (uint16_t)sizeof(struct sctp_error_no_user_data);
5460 m = sctp_get_mbuf_for_msg(len, 0, M_NOWAIT, 1, MT_DATA);
5461 if (m != NULL) {
5462 SCTP_BUF_LEN(m) = len;
5463 no_user_data_cause = mtod(m, struct sctp_error_no_user_data *);
5464 no_user_data_cause->cause.code = htons(SCTP_CAUSE_NO_USER_DATA);
5465 no_user_data_cause->cause.length = htons(len);
5466 no_user_data_cause->tsn = htonl(tsn);
5467 }
5468 return (m);
5469}

5471#ifdef SCTP_MBCNT_LOGGING
5472void
5473sctp_free_bufspace(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_association *asoc,
5474 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *tp1, int chk_cnt)
5475{
5476 if (tp1->data == NULL) {
5477 return;
5478 }
5479 asoc->chunks_on_out_queue -= chk_cnt;
5480 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_MBCNT_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
5481 sctp_log_mbcnt(SCTP_LOG_MBCNT_DECREASE,
5482 asoc->total_output_queue_size,
5483 tp1->book_size,
5484 0,
5485 tp1->mbcnt);
5486 }
5487 if (asoc->total_output_queue_size >= tp1->book_size) {
5488 atomic_add_int(&asoc->total_output_queue_size, -tp1->book_size);
5489 } else {
5490 asoc->total_output_queue_size = 0;
5491 }
5492
5493 if (stcb->sctp_socket && (((stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL)) ||
5494 ((stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE)))) {
5495 if (stcb->sctp_socket->so_snd.sb_cc >= tp1->book_size) {
5496 stcb->sctp_socket->so_snd.sb_cc -= tp1->book_size;
5497 } else {
5498 stcb->sctp_socket->so_snd.sb_cc = 0;
5499 }
5500 }
5501}
5502
5503#endif
5504
5505int
5506sctp_release_pr_sctp_chunk(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sctp_tmit_chunk *tp1,
5507 uint8_t sent, int so_locked)
5508{
5509 struct sctp_stream_out *strq;
5510 struct sctp_tmit_chunk *chk = NULL, *tp2;
5511 struct sctp_stream_queue_pending *sp;
5512 uint32_t mid;
5513 uint16_t sid;
5514 uint8_t foundeom = 0;
5515 int ret_sz = 0;
5516 int notdone;
5517 int do_wakeup_routine = 0;
5518
5519#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5520 if (so_locked) {
5521 sctp_lock_assert(SCTP_INP_SO(stcb->sctp_ep));
5522 } else {
5523 sctp_unlock_assert(SCTP_INP_SO(stcb->sctp_ep));
5524 }
5525#endif
5526 sid = tp1->rec.data.sid;
5527 mid = tp1->rec.data.mid;
5528 if (sent || !(tp1->rec.data.rcv_flags & SCTP_DATA_FIRST_FRAG)) {
5529 stcb->asoc.abandoned_sent[0]++;
5530 stcb->asoc.abandoned_sent[PR_SCTP_POLICY(tp1->flags)]++;
5531 stcb->asoc.strmout[sid].abandoned_sent[0]++;
5532#if defined(SCTP_DETAILED_STR_STATS)
5533 stcb->asoc.strmout[sid].abandoned_sent[PR_SCTP_POLICY(tp1->flags)]++;
5534#endif
5535 } else {
5536 stcb->asoc.abandoned_unsent[0]++;
5537 stcb->asoc.abandoned_unsent[PR_SCTP_POLICY(tp1->flags)]++;
5538 stcb->asoc.strmout[sid].abandoned_unsent[0]++;
5539#if defined(SCTP_DETAILED_STR_STATS)
5540 stcb->asoc.strmout[sid].abandoned_unsent[PR_SCTP_POLICY(tp1->flags)]++;
5541#endif
5542 }
5543 do {
5544 ret_sz += tp1->book_size;
5545 if (tp1->data != NULL) {
5546 if (tp1->sent < SCTP_DATAGRAM_RESEND) {
5547 sctp_flight_size_decrease(tp1);
5548 sctp_total_flight_decrease(stcb, tp1);
5549 }
5550 sctp_free_bufspace(stcb, &stcb->asoc, tp1, 1);
5551 stcb->asoc.peers_rwnd += tp1->send_size;
5552 stcb->asoc.peers_rwnd += SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_peer_chunk_oh);
5553 if (sent) {
5554 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_SENT_DG_FAIL, stcb, 0, tp1, so_locked);
5555 } else {
5556 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_UNSENT_DG_FAIL, stcb, 0, tp1, so_locked);
5557 }
5558 if (tp1->data) {
5559 sctp_m_freem(tp1->data);
5560 tp1->data = NULL;
5561 }
5562 do_wakeup_routine = 1;
5563 if (PR_SCTP_BUF_ENABLED(tp1->flags)) {
5564 stcb->asoc.sent_queue_cnt_removeable--;
5565 }
5566 }
5567 tp1->sent = SCTP_FORWARD_TSN_SKIP;
5568 if ((tp1->rec.data.rcv_flags & SCTP_DATA_NOT_FRAG) ==
5569 SCTP_DATA_NOT_FRAG) {
5570 /* not frag'ed we ae done */
5571 notdone = 0;
5572 foundeom = 1;
5573 } else if (tp1->rec.data.rcv_flags & SCTP_DATA_LAST_FRAG) {
5574 /* end of frag, we are done */
5575 notdone = 0;
5576 foundeom = 1;
5577 } else {
5578 /*
5579 * Its a begin or middle piece, we must mark all of
5580 * it
5581 */
5582 notdone = 1;
5583 tp1 = TAILQ_NEXT(tp1, sctp_next);
5584 }
5585 } while (tp1 && notdone);
5586 if (foundeom == 0) {
5587 /*
5588 * The multi-part message was scattered across the send and
5589 * sent queue.
5590 */
5591 TAILQ_FOREACH_SAFE(tp1, &stcb->asoc.send_queue, sctp_next, tp2) {
5592 if ((tp1->rec.data.sid != sid) ||
5593 (!SCTP_MID_EQ(stcb->asoc.idata_supported, tp1->rec.data.mid, mid))) {
5594 break;
5595 }
5596 /* save to chk in case we have some on stream out
5597 * queue. If so and we have an un-transmitted one
5598 * we don't have to fudge the TSN.
5599 */
5600 chk = tp1;
5601 ret_sz += tp1->book_size;
5602 sctp_free_bufspace(stcb, &stcb->asoc, tp1, 1);
5603 if (sent) {
5604 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_SENT_DG_FAIL, stcb, 0, tp1, so_locked);
5605 } else {
5606 sctp_ulp_notify(SCTP_NOTIFY_UNSENT_DG_FAIL, stcb, 0, tp1, so_locked);
5607 }
5608 if (tp1->data) {
5609 sctp_m_freem(tp1->data);
5610 tp1->data = NULL;
5611 }
5612 /* No flight involved here book the size to 0 */
5613 tp1->book_size = 0;
5614 if (tp1->rec.data.rcv_flags & SCTP_DATA_LAST_FRAG) {
5615 foundeom = 1;
5616 }
5617 do_wakeup_routine = 1;
5618 tp1->sent = SCTP_FORWARD_TSN_SKIP;
5619 TAILQ_REMOVE(&stcb->asoc.send_queue, tp1, sctp_next);
5620 /* on to the sent queue so we can wait for it to be passed by. */
5621 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&stcb->asoc.sent_queue, tp1,
5622 sctp_next);
5623 stcb->asoc.send_queue_cnt--;
5624 stcb->asoc.sent_queue_cnt++;
5625 }
5626 }
5627 if (foundeom == 0) {
5628 /*
5629 * Still no eom found. That means there
5630 * is stuff left on the stream out queue.. yuck.
5631 */
5632 SCTP_TCB_SEND_LOCK(stcb);
5633 strq = &stcb->asoc.strmout[sid];
5634 sp = TAILQ_FIRST(&strq->outqueue);
5635 if (sp != NULL) {
5636 sp->discard_rest = 1;
5637 /*
5638 * We may need to put a chunk on the
5639 * queue that holds the TSN that
5640 * would have been sent with the LAST
5641 * bit.
5642 */
5643 if (chk == NULL) {
5644 /* Yep, we have to */
5645 sctp_alloc_a_chunk(stcb, chk);
5646 if (chk == NULL) {
5647 /* we are hosed. All we can
5648 * do is nothing.. which will
5649 * cause an abort if the peer is
5650 * paying attention.
5651 */
5652 goto oh_well;
5653 }
5654 memset(chk, 0, sizeof(*chk));
5655 chk->rec.data.rcv_flags = 0;
5656 chk->sent = SCTP_FORWARD_TSN_SKIP;
5657 chk->asoc = &stcb->asoc;
5658 if (stcb->asoc.idata_supported == 0) {
5659 if (sp->sinfo_flags & SCTP_UNORDERED) {
5660 chk->rec.data.mid = 0;
5661 } else {
5662 chk->rec.data.mid = strq->next_mid_ordered;
5663 }
5664 } else {
5665 if (sp->sinfo_flags & SCTP_UNORDERED) {
5666 chk->rec.data.mid = strq->next_mid_unordered;
5667 } else {
5668 chk->rec.data.mid = strq->next_mid_ordered;
5669 }
5670 }
5671 chk->rec.data.sid = sp->sid;
5672 chk->rec.data.ppid = sp->ppid;
5673 chk->rec.data.context = sp->context;
5674 chk->flags = sp->act_flags;
5675 chk->whoTo = NULL;
5676#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5677 chk->rec.data.tsn = atomic_fetchadd_int(&stcb->asoc.sending_seq, 1);
5678#else
5679 chk->rec.data.tsn = stcb->asoc.sending_seq++;
5680#endif
5681 strq->chunks_on_queues++;
5682 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&stcb->asoc.sent_queue, chk, sctp_next);
5683 stcb->asoc.sent_queue_cnt++;
5684 stcb->asoc.pr_sctp_cnt++;
5685 }
5686 chk->rec.data.rcv_flags |= SCTP_DATA_LAST_FRAG;
5687 if (sp->sinfo_flags & SCTP_UNORDERED) {
5688 chk->rec.data.rcv_flags |= SCTP_DATA_UNORDERED;
5689 }
5690 if (stcb->asoc.idata_supported == 0) {
5691 if ((sp->sinfo_flags & SCTP_UNORDERED) == 0) {
5692 strq->next_mid_ordered++;
5693 }
5694 } else {
5695 if (sp->sinfo_flags & SCTP_UNORDERED) {
5696 strq->next_mid_unordered++;
5697 } else {
5698 strq->next_mid_ordered++;
5699 }
5700 }
5701 oh_well:
5702 if (sp->data) {
5703 /* Pull any data to free up the SB and
5704 * allow sender to "add more" while we
5705 * will throw away :-)
5706 */
5707 sctp_free_spbufspace(stcb, &stcb->asoc, sp);
5708 ret_sz += sp->length;
5709 do_wakeup_routine = 1;
5710 sp->some_taken = 1;
5711 sctp_m_freem(sp->data);
5712 sp->data = NULL;
5713 sp->tail_mbuf = NULL;
5714 sp->length = 0;
5715 }
5716 }
5717 SCTP_TCB_SEND_UNLOCK(stcb);
5718 }
5719 if (do_wakeup_routine) {
5720#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5721 struct socket *so;
5722
5723 so = SCTP_INP_SO(stcb->sctp_ep);
5724 if (!so_locked) {
5725 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
5726 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
5727 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 1);
5728 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
5729 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
5730 if (stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_CLOSED_SOCKET) {
5731 /* assoc was freed while we were unlocked */
5732 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
5733 return (ret_sz);
5734 }
5735 }
5736#endif
5737 sctp_sowwakeup(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb->sctp_socket);
5738#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5739 if (!so_locked) {
5740 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
5741 }
5742#endif
5743 }
5744 return (ret_sz);
5745}
5746
5747/*
5748 * checks to see if the given address, sa, is one that is currently known by
5749 * the kernel note: can't distinguish the same address on multiple interfaces
5750 * and doesn't handle multiple addresses with different zone/scope id's note:
5751 * ifa_ifwithaddr() compares the entire sockaddr struct
5752 */
5753struct sctp_ifa *
5754sctp_find_ifa_in_ep(struct sctp_inpcb *inp, struct sockaddr *addr,
5755 int holds_lock)
5756{
5757 struct sctp_laddr *laddr;
5758
5759 if (holds_lock == 0) {
5760 SCTP_INP_RLOCK(inp);
5761 }
5762
5763 LIST_FOREACH(laddr, &inp->sctp_addr_list, sctp_nxt_addr) {
5764 if (laddr->ifa == NULL)
5765 continue;
5766 if (addr->sa_family != laddr->ifa->address.sa.sa_family)
5767 continue;
5768#ifdef INET
5769 if (addr->sa_family == AF_INET) {
5770 if (((struct sockaddr_in *)addr)->sin_addr.s_addr ==
5771 laddr->ifa->address.sin.sin_addr.s_addr) {
5772 /* found him. */
5773 break;
5774 }
5775 }
5776#endif
5777#ifdef INET6
5778 if (addr->sa_family == AF_INET6) {
5779 if (SCTP6_ARE_ADDR_EQUAL((struct sockaddr_in6 *)addr,
5780 &laddr->ifa->address.sin6)) {
5781 /* found him. */
5782 break;
5783 }
5784 }
5785#endif
5786#if defined(__Userspace__)
5787 if (addr->sa_family == AF_CONN) {
5788 if (((struct sockaddr_conn *)addr)->sconn_addr == laddr->ifa->address.sconn.sconn_addr) {
5789 /* found him. */
5790 break;
5791 }
5792 }
5793#endif
5794 }
5795 if (holds_lock == 0) {
5796 SCTP_INP_RUNLOCK(inp);
5797 }
5798 if (laddr != NULL) {
5799 return (laddr->ifa);
5800 } else {
5801 return (NULL);
5802 }
5803}
5804
5805uint32_t
5806sctp_get_ifa_hash_val(struct sockaddr *addr)
5807{
5808 switch (addr->sa_family) {
5809#ifdef INET
5810 case AF_INET:
5811 {
5812 struct sockaddr_in *sin;
5813
5814 sin = (struct sockaddr_in *)addr;
5815 return (sin->sin_addr.s_addr ^ (sin->sin_addr.s_addr >> 16));
5816 }
5817#endif
5818#ifdef INET6
5819 case AF_INET6:
5820 {
5821 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6;
5822 uint32_t hash_of_addr;
5823
5824 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)addr;
5825#if !defined(_WIN32) && !(defined(__FreeBSD__) && defined(__Userspace__)) && !defined(__APPLE__)
5826 hash_of_addr = (sin6->sin6_addr.s6_addr32[0] +
5827 sin6->sin6_addr.s6_addr32[1] +
5828 sin6->sin6_addr.s6_addr32[2] +
5829 sin6->sin6_addr.s6_addr32[3]);
5830#else
5831 hash_of_addr = (((uint32_t *)&sin6->sin6_addr)[0] +
5832 ((uint32_t *)&sin6->sin6_addr)[1] +
5833 ((uint32_t *)&sin6->sin6_addr)[2] +
5834 ((uint32_t *)&sin6->sin6_addr)[3]);
5835#endif
5836 hash_of_addr = (hash_of_addr ^ (hash_of_addr >> 16));
5837 return (hash_of_addr);
5838 }
5839#endif
5840#if defined(__Userspace__)
5841 case AF_CONN:
5842 {
5843 struct sockaddr_conn *sconn;
5844 uintptr_t temp;
5845
5846 sconn = (struct sockaddr_conn *)addr;
5847 temp = (uintptr_t)sconn->sconn_addr;
5848 return ((uint32_t)(temp ^ (temp >> 16)));
5849 }
5850#endif
5851 default:
5852 break;
5853 }
5854 return (0);
5855}
5856
5857struct sctp_ifa *
5858sctp_find_ifa_by_addr(struct sockaddr *addr, uint32_t vrf_id, int holds_lock)
5859{
5860 struct sctp_ifa *sctp_ifap;
5861 struct sctp_vrf *vrf;
5862 struct sctp_ifalist *hash_head;
5863 uint32_t hash_of_addr;
5864
5865 if (holds_lock == 0) {
5866 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_RLOCK();
5867 } else {
5868 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_LOCK_ASSERT();
5869 }
5870
5871 vrf = sctp_find_vrf(vrf_id);
5872 if (vrf == NULL) {
5873 if (holds_lock == 0)
5874 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_RUNLOCK();
5875 return (NULL);
5876 }
5877
5878 hash_of_addr = sctp_get_ifa_hash_val(addr);
5879
5880 hash_head = &vrf->vrf_addr_hash[(hash_of_addr & vrf->vrf_addr_hashmark)];
5881 if (hash_head == NULL) {
5882 SCTP_PRINTF("hash_of_addr:%x mask:%x table:%x - ",
5883 hash_of_addr, (uint32_t)vrf->vrf_addr_hashmark,
5884 (uint32_t)(hash_of_addr & vrf->vrf_addr_hashmark));
5885 sctp_print_address(addr);
5886 SCTP_PRINTF("No such bucket for address\n");
5887 if (holds_lock == 0)
5888 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_RUNLOCK();
5889
5890 return (NULL);
5891 }
5892 LIST_FOREACH(sctp_ifap, hash_head, next_bucket) {
5893 if (addr->sa_family != sctp_ifap->address.sa.sa_family)
5894 continue;
5895#ifdef INET
5896 if (addr->sa_family == AF_INET) {
5897 if (((struct sockaddr_in *)addr)->sin_addr.s_addr ==
5898 sctp_ifap->address.sin.sin_addr.s_addr) {
5899 /* found him. */
5900 break;
5901 }
5902 }
5903#endif
5904#ifdef INET6
5905 if (addr->sa_family == AF_INET6) {
5906 if (SCTP6_ARE_ADDR_EQUAL((struct sockaddr_in6 *)addr,
5907 &sctp_ifap->address.sin6)) {
5908 /* found him. */
5909 break;
5910 }
5911 }
5912#endif
5913#if defined(__Userspace__)
5914 if (addr->sa_family == AF_CONN) {
5915 if (((struct sockaddr_conn *)addr)->sconn_addr == sctp_ifap->address.sconn.sconn_addr) {
5916 /* found him. */
5917 break;
5918 }
5919 }
5920#endif
5921 }
5922 if (holds_lock == 0)
5923 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_RUNLOCK();
5924 return (sctp_ifap);
5925}
5926
5927static void
5928sctp_user_rcvd(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, uint32_t *freed_so_far, int hold_rlock,
5929 uint32_t rwnd_req)
5930{
5931 /* User pulled some data, do we need a rwnd update? */
5932#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5933 struct epoch_tracker et;
5934#endif
5935 int r_unlocked = 0;
5936 uint32_t dif, rwnd;
5937 struct socket *so = NULL;
5938
5939 if (stcb == NULL)
5940 return;
5941
5942 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
5943
5944 if ((SCTP_GET_STATE(stcb) == SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_ACK_SENT) ||
5945 (stcb->asoc.state & (SCTP_STATE_ABOUT_TO_BE_FREED | SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_RECEIVED))) {
5946 /* Pre-check If we are freeing no update */
5947 goto no_lock;
5948 }
5949 SCTP_INP_INCR_REF(stcb->sctp_ep);
5950 if ((stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE) ||
5951 (stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_ALLGONE)) {
5952 goto out;
5953 }
5954 so = stcb->sctp_socket;
5955 if (so == NULL) {
5956 goto out;
5957 }
5958 atomic_add_int(&stcb->freed_by_sorcv_sincelast, *freed_so_far);
5959 /* Have you have freed enough to look */
5960 *freed_so_far = 0;
5961 /* Yep, its worth a look and the lock overhead */
5962
5963 /* Figure out what the rwnd would be */
5964 rwnd = sctp_calc_rwnd(stcb, &stcb->asoc);
5965 if (rwnd >= stcb->asoc.my_last_reported_rwnd) {
5966 dif = rwnd - stcb->asoc.my_last_reported_rwnd;
5967 } else {
5968 dif = 0;
5969 }
5970 if (dif >= rwnd_req) {
5971 if (hold_rlock) {
5972 SCTP_INP_READ_UNLOCK(stcb->sctp_ep);
5973 r_unlocked = 1;
5974 }
5975 if (stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_ABOUT_TO_BE_FREED) {
5976 /*
5977 * One last check before we allow the guy possibly
5978 * to get in. There is a race, where the guy has not
5979 * reached the gate. In that case
5980 */
5981 goto out;
5982 }
5983 SCTP_TCB_LOCK(stcb);
5984 if (stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_ABOUT_TO_BE_FREED) {
5985 /* No reports here */
5986 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
5987 goto out;
5988 }
5989 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_wu_sacks_sent);
5990#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5991 NET_EPOCH_ENTER(et);
5992#endif
5993 sctp_send_sack(stcb, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
5994
5995 sctp_chunk_output(stcb->sctp_ep, stcb,
5996 SCTP_OUTPUT_FROM_USR_RCVD, SCTP_SO_LOCKED);
5997 /* make sure no timer is running */
5998#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
5999 NET_EPOCH_EXIT(et);
6000#endif
6001 sctp_timer_stop(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_RECV, stcb->sctp_ep, stcb, NULL,
6002 SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL + SCTP_LOC_6);
6003 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
6004 } else {
6005 /* Update how much we have pending */
6006 stcb->freed_by_sorcv_sincelast = dif;
6007 }
6008 out:
6009 if (so && r_unlocked && hold_rlock) {
6010 SCTP_INP_READ_LOCK(stcb->sctp_ep);
6011 }
6012
6013 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(stcb->sctp_ep);
6014 no_lock:
6015 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, -1);
6016 return;
6017}
6018
6019int
6020sctp_sorecvmsg(struct socket *so,
6021 struct uio *uio,
6022 struct mbuf **mp,
6023 struct sockaddr *from,
6024 int fromlen,
6025 int *msg_flags,
6026 struct sctp_sndrcvinfo *sinfo,
6027 int filling_sinfo)
6028{
6029 /*
6030 * MSG flags we will look at MSG_DONTWAIT - non-blocking IO.
6031 * MSG_PEEK - Look don't touch :-D (only valid with OUT mbuf copy
6032 * mp=NULL thus uio is the copy method to userland) MSG_WAITALL - ??
6033 * On the way out we may send out any combination of:
6034 * MSG_NOTIFICATION MSG_EOR
6035 *
6036 */
6037 struct sctp_inpcb *inp = NULL;
6038 ssize_t my_len = 0;
6039 ssize_t cp_len = 0;
6040 int error = 0;
6041 struct sctp_queued_to_read *control = NULL, *ctl = NULL, *nxt = NULL;
6042 struct mbuf *m = NULL;
6043 struct sctp_tcb *stcb = NULL;
6044 int wakeup_read_socket = 0;
6045 int freecnt_applied = 0;
6046 int out_flags = 0, in_flags = 0;
6047 int block_allowed = 1;
6048 uint32_t freed_so_far = 0;
6049 ssize_t copied_so_far = 0;
6050 int in_eeor_mode = 0;
6051 int no_rcv_needed = 0;
6052 uint32_t rwnd_req = 0;
6053 int hold_sblock = 0;
6054 int hold_rlock = 0;
6055 ssize_t slen = 0;
6056 uint32_t held_length = 0;
6057#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6058 int sockbuf_lock = 0;
6059#endif
6060
6061 if (uio == NULL) {
6062 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, EINVAL);
6063 return (EINVAL);
6064 }
6065
6066 if (msg_flags) {
6067 in_flags = *msg_flags;
6068 if (in_flags & MSG_PEEK)
6069 SCTP_STAT_INCR(sctps_read_peeks);
6070 } else {
6071 in_flags = 0;
6072 }
6073#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6074#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD)
6075 slen = uio->uio_resid;
6076#else
6077 slen = uio_resid(uio);
6078#endif
6079#else
6080 slen = uio->uio_resid;
6081#endif
6082
6083 /* Pull in and set up our int flags */
6084 if (in_flags & MSG_OOB) {
6085 /* Out of band's NOT supported */
6086 return (EOPNOTSUPP);
6087 }
6088 if ((in_flags & MSG_PEEK) && (mp != NULL)) {
6089 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, EINVAL);
6090 return (EINVAL);
6091 }
6092 if ((in_flags & (MSG_DONTWAIT
6093#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6094 | MSG_NBIO
6095#endif
6096 )) ||
6097 SCTP_SO_IS_NBIO(so)) {
6098 block_allowed = 0;
6099 }
6100 /* setup the endpoint */
6101 inp = (struct sctp_inpcb *)so->so_pcb;
6102 if (inp == NULL) {
6103 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, EFAULT);
6104 return (EFAULT);
6105 }
6106 rwnd_req = (SCTP_SB_LIMIT_RCV(so) >> SCTP_RWND_HIWAT_SHIFT);
6107 /* Must be at least a MTU's worth */
6108 if (rwnd_req < SCTP_MIN_RWND)
6109 rwnd_req = SCTP_MIN_RWND;
6110 in_eeor_mode = sctp_is_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_EXPLICIT_EOR);
6111 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_RECV_RWND_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
6112#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6113#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD)
6114 sctp_misc_ints(SCTP_SORECV_ENTER,
6115 rwnd_req, in_eeor_mode, so->so_rcv.sb_cc, uio->uio_resid);
6116#else
6117 sctp_misc_ints(SCTP_SORECV_ENTER,
6118 rwnd_req, in_eeor_mode, so->so_rcv.sb_cc, uio_resid(uio));
6119#endif
6120#else
6121 sctp_misc_ints(SCTP_SORECV_ENTER,
6122 rwnd_req, in_eeor_mode, so->so_rcv.sb_cc, (uint32_t)uio->uio_resid);
6123#endif
6124 }
6125#if defined(__Userspace__)
6126 SOCKBUF_LOCK(&so->so_rcv);
6127 hold_sblock = 1;
6128#endif
6129 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) &SCTP_RECV_RWND_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
6130#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6131#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD)
6132 sctp_misc_ints(SCTP_SORECV_ENTERPL,
6133 rwnd_req, block_allowed, so->so_rcv.sb_cc, uio->uio_resid);
6134#else
6135 sctp_misc_ints(SCTP_SORECV_ENTERPL,
6136 rwnd_req, block_allowed, so->so_rcv.sb_cc, uio_resid(uio));
6137#endif
6138#else
6139 sctp_misc_ints(SCTP_SORECV_ENTERPL,
6140 rwnd_req, block_allowed, so->so_rcv.sb_cc, (uint32_t)uio->uio_resid);
6141#endif
6142 }
6143
6144#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6145 error = sblock(&so->so_rcv, SBLOCKWAIT(in_flags));
6146#endif
6147#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6148 error = sblock(&so->so_rcv, (block_allowed ? SBL_WAIT : 0));
6149#endif
6150 if (error) {
6151 goto release_unlocked;
6152 }
6153#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6154 sockbuf_lock = 1;
6155#endif
6156 restart:
6157#if defined(__Userspace__)
6158 if (hold_sblock == 0) {
6159 SOCKBUF_LOCK(&so->so_rcv);
6160 hold_sblock = 1;
6161 }
6162#endif
6163#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6164 sbunlock(&so->so_rcv, 1);
6165#endif
6166
6167 restart_nosblocks:
6168 if (hold_sblock == 0) {
6169 SOCKBUF_LOCK(&so->so_rcv);
6170 hold_sblock = 1;
6171 }
6172 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE) ||
6173 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_ALLGONE)) {
6174 goto out;
6175 }
6176#if (defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(_WIN32)) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6177 if ((so->so_rcv.sb_state & SBS_CANTRCVMORE) && (so->so_rcv.sb_cc == 0)) {
6178#else
6179 if ((so->so_state & SS_CANTRCVMORE) && (so->so_rcv.sb_cc == 0)) {
6180#endif
6181 if (so->so_error) {
6182 error = so->so_error;
6183 if ((in_flags & MSG_PEEK) == 0)
6184 so->so_error = 0;
6185 goto out;
6186 } else {
6187 if (so->so_rcv.sb_cc == 0) {
6188 /* indicate EOF */
6189 error = 0;
6190 goto out;
6191 }
6192 }
6193 }
6194 if (so->so_rcv.sb_cc <= held_length) {
6195 if (so->so_error) {
6196 error = so->so_error;
6197 if ((in_flags & MSG_PEEK) == 0) {
6198 so->so_error = 0;
6199 }
6200 goto out;
6201 }
6202 if ((so->so_rcv.sb_cc == 0) &&
6203 ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_TCPTYPE) ||
6204 (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_IN_TCPPOOL))) {
6205 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_CONNECTED) == 0) {
6206 /* For active open side clear flags for re-use
6207 * passive open is blocked by connect.
6208 */
6209 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_WAS_ABORTED) {
6210 /* You were aborted, passive side always hits here */
6211 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, ECONNRESET);
6212 error = ECONNRESET;
6213 }
6214 so->so_state &= ~(SS_ISCONNECTING |
6215 SS_ISDISCONNECTING |
6216 SS_ISCONFIRMING |
6217 SS_ISCONNECTED);
6218 if (error == 0) {
6219 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_WAS_CONNECTED) == 0) {
6220 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, ENOTCONN);
6221 error = ENOTCONN;
6222 }
6223 }
6224 goto out;
6225 }
6226 }
6227 if (block_allowed) {
6228 error = sbwait(&so->so_rcv);
6229 if (error) {
6230 goto out;
6231 }
6232 held_length = 0;
6233 goto restart_nosblocks;
6234 } else {
6235 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, EWOULDBLOCK);
6236 error = EWOULDBLOCK;
6237 goto out;
6238 }
6239 }
6240 if (hold_sblock == 1) {
6241 SOCKBUF_UNLOCK(&so->so_rcv);
6242 hold_sblock = 0;
6243 }
6244#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6245 error = sblock(&so->so_rcv, SBLOCKWAIT(in_flags));
6246#endif
6247 /* we possibly have data we can read */
6248 /*sa_ignore FREED_MEMORY*/
6249 control = TAILQ_FIRST(&inp->read_queue);
6250 if (control == NULL) {
6251 /* This could be happening since
6252 * the appender did the increment but as not
6253 * yet did the tailq insert onto the read_queue
6254 */
6255 if (hold_rlock == 0) {
6256 SCTP_INP_READ_LOCK(inp);
6257 }
6258 control = TAILQ_FIRST(&inp->read_queue);
6259 if ((control == NULL) && (so->so_rcv.sb_cc != 0)) {
6260#ifdef INVARIANTS
6261 panic("Huh, its non zero and nothing on control?");
6262#endif
6263 so->so_rcv.sb_cc = 0;
6264 }
6265 SCTP_INP_READ_UNLOCK(inp);
6266 hold_rlock = 0;
6267 goto restart;
6268 }
6269
6270 if ((control->length == 0) &&
6271 (control->do_not_ref_stcb)) {
6272 /* Clean up code for freeing assoc that left behind a pdapi..
6273 * maybe a peer in EEOR that just closed after sending and
6274 * never indicated a EOR.
6275 */
6276 if (hold_rlock == 0) {
6277 hold_rlock = 1;
6278 SCTP_INP_READ_LOCK(inp);
6279 }
6280 control->held_length = 0;
6281 if (control->data) {
6282 /* Hmm there is data here .. fix */
6283 struct mbuf *m_tmp;
6284 int cnt = 0;
6285 m_tmp = control->data;
6286 while (m_tmp) {
6287 cnt += SCTP_BUF_LEN(m_tmp);
6288 if (SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m_tmp) == NULL) {
6289 control->tail_mbuf = m_tmp;
6290 control->end_added = 1;
6291 }
6292 m_tmp = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m_tmp);
6293 }
6294 control->length = cnt;
6295 } else {
6296 /* remove it */
6297 TAILQ_REMOVE(&inp->read_queue, control, next);
6298 /* Add back any hiddend data */
6299 sctp_free_remote_addr(control->whoFrom);
6300 sctp_free_a_readq(stcb, control);
6301 }
6302 if (hold_rlock) {
6303 hold_rlock = 0;
6304 SCTP_INP_READ_UNLOCK(inp);
6305 }
6306 goto restart;
6307 }
6308 if ((control->length == 0) &&
6309 (control->end_added == 1)) {
6310 /* Do we also need to check for (control->pdapi_aborted == 1)? */
6311 if (hold_rlock == 0) {
6312 hold_rlock = 1;
6313 SCTP_INP_READ_LOCK(inp);
6314 }
6315 TAILQ_REMOVE(&inp->read_queue, control, next);
6316 if (control->data) {
6317#ifdef INVARIANTS
6318 panic("control->data not null but control->length == 0");
6319#else
6320 SCTP_PRINTF("Strange, data left in the control buffer. Cleaning up.\n");
6321 sctp_m_freem(control->data);
6322 control->data = NULL;
6323#endif
6324 }
6325 if (control->aux_data) {
6326 sctp_m_free (control->aux_data);
6327 control->aux_data = NULL;
6328 }
6329#ifdef INVARIANTS
6330 if (control->on_strm_q) {
6331 panic("About to free ctl:%p so:%p and its in %d",
6332 control, so, control->on_strm_q);
6333 }
6334#endif
6335 sctp_free_remote_addr(control->whoFrom);
6336 sctp_free_a_readq(stcb, control);
6337 if (hold_rlock) {
6338 hold_rlock = 0;
6339 SCTP_INP_READ_UNLOCK(inp);
6340 }
6341 goto restart;
6342 }
6343 if (control->length == 0) {
6344 if ((sctp_is_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_FRAG_INTERLEAVE)) &&
6345 (filling_sinfo)) {
6346 /* find a more suitable one then this */
6347 ctl = TAILQ_NEXT(control, next);
6348 while (ctl) {
6349 if ((ctl->stcb != control->stcb) && (ctl->length) &&
6350 (ctl->some_taken ||
6351 (ctl->spec_flags & M_NOTIFICATION) ||
6352 ((ctl->do_not_ref_stcb == 0) &&
6353 (ctl->stcb->asoc.strmin[ctl->sinfo_stream].delivery_started == 0)))
6354 ) {
6355 /*-
6356 * If we have a different TCB next, and there is data
6357 * present. If we have already taken some (pdapi), OR we can
6358 * ref the tcb and no delivery as started on this stream, we
6359 * take it. Note we allow a notification on a different
6360 * assoc to be delivered..
6361 */
6362 control = ctl;
6363 goto found_one;
6364 } else if ((sctp_is_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_INTERLEAVE_STRMS)) &&
6365 (ctl->length) &&
6366 ((ctl->some_taken) ||
6367 ((ctl->do_not_ref_stcb == 0) &&
6368 ((ctl->spec_flags & M_NOTIFICATION) == 0) &&
6369 (ctl->stcb->asoc.strmin[ctl->sinfo_stream].delivery_started == 0)))) {
6370 /*-
6371 * If we have the same tcb, and there is data present, and we
6372 * have the strm interleave feature present. Then if we have
6373 * taken some (pdapi) or we can refer to tht tcb AND we have
6374 * not started a delivery for this stream, we can take it.
6375 * Note we do NOT allow a notificaiton on the same assoc to
6376 * be delivered.
6377 */
6378 control = ctl;
6379 goto found_one;
6380 }
6381 ctl = TAILQ_NEXT(ctl, next);
6382 }
6383 }
6384 /*
6385 * if we reach here, not suitable replacement is available
6386 * <or> fragment interleave is NOT on. So stuff the sb_cc
6387 * into the our held count, and its time to sleep again.
6388 */
6389 held_length = so->so_rcv.sb_cc;
6390 control->held_length = so->so_rcv.sb_cc;
6391 goto restart;
6392 }
6393 /* Clear the held length since there is something to read */
6394 control->held_length = 0;
6395 found_one:
6396 /*
6397 * If we reach here, control has a some data for us to read off.
6398 * Note that stcb COULD be NULL.
6399 */
6400 if (hold_rlock == 0) {
6401 hold_rlock = 1;
6402 SCTP_INP_READ_LOCK(inp);
6403 }
6404 control->some_taken++;
6405 stcb = control->stcb;
6406 if (stcb) {
6407 if ((control->do_not_ref_stcb == 0) &&
6408 (stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_ABOUT_TO_BE_FREED)) {
6409 if (freecnt_applied == 0)
6410 stcb = NULL;
6411 } else if (control->do_not_ref_stcb == 0) {
6412 /* you can't free it on me please */
6413 /*
6414 * The lock on the socket buffer protects us so the
6415 * free code will stop. But since we used the socketbuf
6416 * lock and the sender uses the tcb_lock to increment,
6417 * we need to use the atomic add to the refcnt
6418 */
6419 if (freecnt_applied) {
6420#ifdef INVARIANTS
6421 panic("refcnt already incremented");
6422#else
6423 SCTP_PRINTF("refcnt already incremented?\n");
6424#endif
6425 } else {
6426 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, 1);
6427 freecnt_applied = 1;
6428 }
6429 /*
6430 * Setup to remember how much we have not yet told
6431 * the peer our rwnd has opened up. Note we grab
6432 * the value from the tcb from last time.
6433 * Note too that sack sending clears this when a sack
6434 * is sent, which is fine. Once we hit the rwnd_req,
6435 * we then will go to the sctp_user_rcvd() that will
6436 * not lock until it KNOWs it MUST send a WUP-SACK.
6437 */
6438 freed_so_far = (uint32_t)stcb->freed_by_sorcv_sincelast;
6439 stcb->freed_by_sorcv_sincelast = 0;
6440 }
6441 }
6442 if (stcb &&
6443 ((control->spec_flags & M_NOTIFICATION) == 0) &&
6444 control->do_not_ref_stcb == 0) {
6445 stcb->asoc.strmin[control->sinfo_stream].delivery_started = 1;
6446 }
6447
6448 /* First lets get off the sinfo and sockaddr info */
6449 if ((sinfo != NULL) && (filling_sinfo != 0)) {
6450 sinfo->sinfo_stream = control->sinfo_stream;
6451 sinfo->sinfo_ssn = (uint16_t)control->mid;
6452 sinfo->sinfo_flags = control->sinfo_flags;
6453 sinfo->sinfo_ppid = control->sinfo_ppid;
6454 sinfo->sinfo_context =control->sinfo_context;
6455 sinfo->sinfo_timetolive = control->sinfo_timetolive;
6456 sinfo->sinfo_tsn = control->sinfo_tsn;
6457 sinfo->sinfo_cumtsn = control->sinfo_cumtsn;
6458 sinfo->sinfo_assoc_id = control->sinfo_assoc_id;
6459 nxt = TAILQ_NEXT(control, next);
6460 if (sctp_is_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_EXT_RCVINFO) ||
6461 sctp_is_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_RECVNXTINFO)) {
6462 struct sctp_extrcvinfo *s_extra;
6463 s_extra = (struct sctp_extrcvinfo *)sinfo;
6464 if ((nxt) &&
6465 (nxt->length)) {
6466 s_extra->serinfo_next_flags = SCTP_NEXT_MSG_AVAIL;
6467 if (nxt->sinfo_flags & SCTP_UNORDERED) {
6468 s_extra->serinfo_next_flags |= SCTP_NEXT_MSG_IS_UNORDERED;
6469 }
6470 if (nxt->spec_flags & M_NOTIFICATION) {
6471 s_extra->serinfo_next_flags |= SCTP_NEXT_MSG_IS_NOTIFICATION;
6472 }
6473 s_extra->serinfo_next_aid = nxt->sinfo_assoc_id;
6474 s_extra->serinfo_next_length = nxt->length;
6475 s_extra->serinfo_next_ppid = nxt->sinfo_ppid;
6476 s_extra->serinfo_next_stream = nxt->sinfo_stream;
6477 if (nxt->tail_mbuf != NULL) {
6478 if (nxt->end_added) {
6479 s_extra->serinfo_next_flags |= SCTP_NEXT_MSG_ISCOMPLETE;
6480 }
6481 }
6482 } else {
6483 /* we explicitly 0 this, since the memcpy got
6484 * some other things beyond the older sinfo_
6485 * that is on the control's structure :-D
6486 */
6487 nxt = NULL;
6488 s_extra->serinfo_next_flags = SCTP_NO_NEXT_MSG;
6489 s_extra->serinfo_next_aid = 0;
6490 s_extra->serinfo_next_length = 0;
6491 s_extra->serinfo_next_ppid = 0;
6492 s_extra->serinfo_next_stream = 0;
6493 }
6494 }
6495 /*
6496 * update off the real current cum-ack, if we have an stcb.
6497 */
6498 if ((control->do_not_ref_stcb == 0) && stcb)
6499 sinfo->sinfo_cumtsn = stcb->asoc.cumulative_tsn;
6500 /*
6501 * mask off the high bits, we keep the actual chunk bits in
6502 * there.
6503 */
6504 sinfo->sinfo_flags &= 0x00ff;
6505 if ((control->sinfo_flags >> 8) & SCTP_DATA_UNORDERED) {
6506 sinfo->sinfo_flags |= SCTP_UNORDERED;
6507 }
6508 }
6509#ifdef SCTP_ASOCLOG_OF_TSNS
6510 {
6511 int index, newindex;
6512 struct sctp_pcbtsn_rlog *entry;
6513 do {
6514 index = inp->readlog_index;
6515 newindex = index + 1;
6516 if (newindex >= SCTP_READ_LOG_SIZE) {
6517 newindex = 0;
6518 }
6519 } while (atomic_cmpset_int(&inp->readlog_index, index, newindex) == 0);
6520 entry = &inp->readlog[index];
6521 entry->vtag = control->sinfo_assoc_id;
6522 entry->strm = control->sinfo_stream;
6523 entry->seq = (uint16_t)control->mid;
6524 entry->sz = control->length;
6525 entry->flgs = control->sinfo_flags;
6526 }
6527#endif
6528 if ((fromlen > 0) && (from != NULL)) {
6529 union sctp_sockstore store;
6530 size_t len;
6531
6532 switch (control->whoFrom->ro._l_addr.sa.sa_family) {
6533#ifdef INET6
6534 case AF_INET6:
6535 len = sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6);
6536 store.sin6 = control->whoFrom->ro._l_addr.sin6;
6537 store.sin6.sin6_port = control->port_from;
6538 break;
6539#endif
6540#ifdef INET
6541 case AF_INET:
6542#ifdef INET6
6543 if (sctp_is_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_NEEDS_MAPPED_V4)) {
6544 len = sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6);
6545 in6_sin_2_v4mapsin6(&control->whoFrom->ro._l_addr.sin,
6546 &store.sin6);
6547 store.sin6.sin6_port = control->port_from;
6548 } else {
6549 len = sizeof(struct sockaddr_in);
6550 store.sin = control->whoFrom->ro._l_addr.sin;
6551 store.sin.sin_port = control->port_from;
6552 }
6553#else
6554 len = sizeof(struct sockaddr_in);
6555 store.sin = control->whoFrom->ro._l_addr.sin;
6556 store.sin.sin_port = control->port_from;
6557#endif
6558 break;
6559#endif
6560#if defined(__Userspace__)
6561 case AF_CONN:
6562 len = sizeof(struct sockaddr_conn);
6563 store.sconn = control->whoFrom->ro._l_addr.sconn;
6564 store.sconn.sconn_port = control->port_from;
6565 break;
6566#endif
6567 default:
6568 len = 0;
6569 break;
6570 }
6571 memcpy(from, &store, min((size_t)fromlen, len));
6572#if defined(SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE)
6573#ifdef INET6
6574 {
6575 struct sockaddr_in6 lsa6, *from6;
6576
6577 from6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)from;
6578 sctp_recover_scope_mac(from6, (&lsa6));
6579 }
6580#endif
6581#endif
6582 }
6583 if (hold_rlock) {
6584 SCTP_INP_READ_UNLOCK(inp);
6585 hold_rlock = 0;
6586 }
6587 if (hold_sblock) {
6588 SOCKBUF_UNLOCK(&so->so_rcv);
6589 hold_sblock = 0;
6590 }
6591 /* now copy out what data we can */
6592 if (mp == NULL) {
6593 /* copy out each mbuf in the chain up to length */
6594 get_more_data:
6595 m = control->data;
6596 while (m) {
6597 /* Move out all we can */
6598#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6599#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD)
6600 cp_len = uio->uio_resid;
6601#else
6602 cp_len = uio_resid(uio);
6603#endif
6604#else
6605 cp_len = uio->uio_resid;
6606#endif
6607 my_len = SCTP_BUF_LEN(m);
6608 if (cp_len > my_len) {
6609 /* not enough in this buf */
6610 cp_len = my_len;
6611 }
6612 if (hold_rlock) {
6613 SCTP_INP_READ_UNLOCK(inp);
6614 hold_rlock = 0;
6615 }
6616#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6617 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 0);
6618#endif
6619 if (cp_len > 0)
6620 error = uiomove(mtod(m, char *), (int)cp_len, uio);
6621#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6622 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 0);
6623#endif
6624 /* re-read */
6625 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE) {
6626 goto release;
6627 }
6628
6629 if ((control->do_not_ref_stcb == 0) && stcb &&
6630 stcb->asoc.state & SCTP_STATE_ABOUT_TO_BE_FREED) {
6631 no_rcv_needed = 1;
6632 }
6633 if (error) {
6634 /* error we are out of here */
6635 goto release;
6636 }
6637 SCTP_INP_READ_LOCK(inp);
6638 hold_rlock = 1;
6639 if (cp_len == SCTP_BUF_LEN(m)) {
6640 if ((SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m)== NULL) &&
6641 (control->end_added)) {
6642 out_flags |= MSG_EOR;
6643 if ((control->do_not_ref_stcb == 0) &&
6644 (control->stcb != NULL) &&
6645 ((control->spec_flags & M_NOTIFICATION) == 0))
6646 control->stcb->asoc.strmin[control->sinfo_stream].delivery_started = 0;
6647 }
6648 if (control->spec_flags & M_NOTIFICATION) {
6649 out_flags |= MSG_NOTIFICATION;
6650 }
6651 /* we ate up the mbuf */
6652 if (in_flags & MSG_PEEK) {
6653 /* just looking */
6654 m = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m);
6655 copied_so_far += cp_len;
6656 } else {
6657 /* dispose of the mbuf */
6658 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_SB_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
6659 sctp_sblog(&so->so_rcv,
6660 control->do_not_ref_stcb?NULL:stcb, SCTP_LOG_SBFREE, SCTP_BUF_LEN(m));
6661 }
6662 sctp_sbfree(control, stcb, &so->so_rcv, m);
6663 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_SB_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
6664 sctp_sblog(&so->so_rcv,
6665 control->do_not_ref_stcb?NULL:stcb, SCTP_LOG_SBRESULT, 0);
6666 }
6667 copied_so_far += cp_len;
6668 freed_so_far += (uint32_t)cp_len;
6669 freed_so_far += MSIZE;
6670 atomic_subtract_int(&control->length, cp_len);
6671 control->data = sctp_m_free(m);
6672 m = control->data;
6673 /* been through it all, must hold sb lock ok to null tail */
6674 if (control->data == NULL) {
6675#ifdef INVARIANTS
6676#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6677 if ((control->end_added == 0) ||
6678 (TAILQ_NEXT(control, next) == NULL)) {
6679 /* If the end is not added, OR the
6680 * next is NOT null we MUST have the lock.
6681 */
6682 if (mtx_owned(&inp->inp_rdata_mtx) == 0) {
6683 panic("Hmm we don't own the lock?");
6684 }
6685 }
6686#endif
6687#endif
6688 control->tail_mbuf = NULL;
6689#ifdef INVARIANTS
6690 if ((control->end_added) && ((out_flags & MSG_EOR) == 0)) {
6691 panic("end_added, nothing left and no MSG_EOR");
6692 }
6693#endif
6694 }
6695 }
6696 } else {
6697 /* Do we need to trim the mbuf? */
6698 if (control->spec_flags & M_NOTIFICATION) {
6699 out_flags |= MSG_NOTIFICATION;
6700 }
6701 if ((in_flags & MSG_PEEK) == 0) {
6702 SCTP_BUF_RESV_UF(m, cp_len);
6703 SCTP_BUF_LEN(m) -= (int)cp_len;
6704 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_SB_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
6705 sctp_sblog(&so->so_rcv, control->do_not_ref_stcb?NULL:stcb, SCTP_LOG_SBFREE, (int)cp_len);
6706 }
6707 atomic_subtract_int(&so->so_rcv.sb_cc, cp_len);
6708 if ((control->do_not_ref_stcb == 0) &&
6709 stcb) {
6710 atomic_subtract_int(&stcb->asoc.sb_cc, cp_len);
6711 }
6712 copied_so_far += cp_len;
6713 freed_so_far += (uint32_t)cp_len;
6714 freed_so_far += MSIZE;
6715 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_SB_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
6716 sctp_sblog(&so->so_rcv, control->do_not_ref_stcb?NULL:stcb,
6717 SCTP_LOG_SBRESULT, 0);
6718 }
6719 atomic_subtract_int(&control->length, cp_len);
6720 } else {
6721 copied_so_far += cp_len;
6722 }
6723 }
6724#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6725#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD)
6726 if ((out_flags & MSG_EOR) || (uio->uio_resid == 0)) {
6727#else
6728 if ((out_flags & MSG_EOR) || (uio_resid(uio) == 0)) {
6729#endif
6730#else
6731 if ((out_flags & MSG_EOR) || (uio->uio_resid == 0)) {
6732#endif
6733 break;
6734 }
6735 if (((stcb) && (in_flags & MSG_PEEK) == 0) &&
6736 (control->do_not_ref_stcb == 0) &&
6737 (freed_so_far >= rwnd_req)) {
6738 sctp_user_rcvd(stcb, &freed_so_far, hold_rlock, rwnd_req);
6739 }
6740 } /* end while(m) */
6741 /*
6742 * At this point we have looked at it all and we either have
6743 * a MSG_EOR/or read all the user wants... <OR>
6744 * control->length == 0.
6745 */
6746 if ((out_flags & MSG_EOR) && ((in_flags & MSG_PEEK) == 0)) {
6747 /* we are done with this control */
6748 if (control->length == 0) {
6749 if (control->data) {
6750#ifdef INVARIANTS
6751 panic("control->data not null at read eor?");
6752#else
6753 SCTP_PRINTF("Strange, data left in the control buffer .. invarients would panic?\n");
6754 sctp_m_freem(control->data);
6755 control->data = NULL;
6756#endif
6757 }
6758 done_with_control:
6759 if (hold_rlock == 0) {
6760 SCTP_INP_READ_LOCK(inp);
6761 hold_rlock = 1;
6762 }
6763 TAILQ_REMOVE(&inp->read_queue, control, next);
6764 /* Add back any hiddend data */
6765 if (control->held_length) {
6766 held_length = 0;
6767 control->held_length = 0;
6768 wakeup_read_socket = 1;
6769 }
6770 if (control->aux_data) {
6771 sctp_m_free (control->aux_data);
6772 control->aux_data = NULL;
6773 }
6774 no_rcv_needed = control->do_not_ref_stcb;
6775 sctp_free_remote_addr(control->whoFrom);
6776 control->data = NULL;
6777#ifdef INVARIANTS
6778 if (control->on_strm_q) {
6779 panic("About to free ctl:%p so:%p and its in %d",
6780 control, so, control->on_strm_q);
6781 }
6782#endif
6783 sctp_free_a_readq(stcb, control);
6784 control = NULL;
6785 if ((freed_so_far >= rwnd_req) &&
6786 (no_rcv_needed == 0))
6787 sctp_user_rcvd(stcb, &freed_so_far, hold_rlock, rwnd_req);
6788
6789 } else {
6790 /*
6791 * The user did not read all of this
6792 * message, turn off the returned MSG_EOR
6793 * since we are leaving more behind on the
6794 * control to read.
6795 */
6796#ifdef INVARIANTS
6797 if (control->end_added &&
6798 (control->data == NULL) &&
6799 (control->tail_mbuf == NULL)) {
6800 panic("Gak, control->length is corrupt?");
6801 }
6802#endif
6803 no_rcv_needed = control->do_not_ref_stcb;
6804 out_flags &= ~MSG_EOR;
6805 }
6806 }
6807 if (out_flags & MSG_EOR) {
6808 goto release;
6809 }
6810#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6811#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD)
6812 if ((uio->uio_resid == 0) ||
6813#else
6814 if ((uio_resid(uio) == 0) ||
6815#endif
6816#else
6817 if ((uio->uio_resid == 0) ||
6818#endif
6819 ((in_eeor_mode) &&
6820 (copied_so_far >= max(so->so_rcv.sb_lowat, 1)))) {
6821 goto release;
6822 }
6823 /*
6824 * If I hit here the receiver wants more and this message is
6825 * NOT done (pd-api). So two questions. Can we block? if not
6826 * we are done. Did the user NOT set MSG_WAITALL?
6827 */
6828 if (block_allowed == 0) {
6829 goto release;
6830 }
6831 /*
6832 * We need to wait for more data a few things: - We don't
6833 * sbunlock() so we don't get someone else reading. - We
6834 * must be sure to account for the case where what is added
6835 * is NOT to our control when we wakeup.
6836 */
6837
6838 /* Do we need to tell the transport a rwnd update might be
6839 * needed before we go to sleep?
6840 */
6841 if (((stcb) && (in_flags & MSG_PEEK) == 0) &&
6842 ((freed_so_far >= rwnd_req) &&
6843 (control->do_not_ref_stcb == 0) &&
6844 (no_rcv_needed == 0))) {
6845 sctp_user_rcvd(stcb, &freed_so_far, hold_rlock, rwnd_req);
6846 }
6847 wait_some_more:
6848#if (defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(_WIN32)) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6849 if (so->so_rcv.sb_state & SBS_CANTRCVMORE) {
6850 goto release;
6851 }
6852#else
6853 if (so->so_state & SS_CANTRCVMORE) {
6854 goto release;
6855 }
6856#endif
6857
6858 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE)
6859 goto release;
6860
6861 if (hold_rlock == 1) {
6862 SCTP_INP_READ_UNLOCK(inp);
6863 hold_rlock = 0;
6864 }
6865 if (hold_sblock == 0) {
6866 SOCKBUF_LOCK(&so->so_rcv);
6867 hold_sblock = 1;
6868 }
6869 if ((copied_so_far) && (control->length == 0) &&
6870 (sctp_is_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_FRAG_INTERLEAVE))) {
6871 goto release;
6872 }
6873#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6874 sbunlock(&so->so_rcv, 1);
6875#endif
6876 if (so->so_rcv.sb_cc <= control->held_length) {
6877 error = sbwait(&so->so_rcv);
6878 if (error) {
6879#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6880 goto release;
6881#else
6882 goto release_unlocked;
6883#endif
6884 }
6885 control->held_length = 0;
6886 }
6887#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6888 error = sblock(&so->so_rcv, SBLOCKWAIT(in_flags));
6889#endif
6890 if (hold_sblock) {
6891 SOCKBUF_UNLOCK(&so->so_rcv);
6892 hold_sblock = 0;
6893 }
6894 if (control->length == 0) {
6895 /* still nothing here */
6896 if (control->end_added == 1) {
6897 /* he aborted, or is done i.e.did a shutdown */
6898 out_flags |= MSG_EOR;
6899 if (control->pdapi_aborted) {
6900 if ((control->do_not_ref_stcb == 0) && ((control->spec_flags & M_NOTIFICATION) == 0))
6901 control->stcb->asoc.strmin[control->sinfo_stream].delivery_started = 0;
6902
6903 out_flags |= MSG_TRUNC;
6904 } else {
6905 if ((control->do_not_ref_stcb == 0) && ((control->spec_flags & M_NOTIFICATION) == 0))
6906 control->stcb->asoc.strmin[control->sinfo_stream].delivery_started = 0;
6907 }
6908 goto done_with_control;
6909 }
6910 if (so->so_rcv.sb_cc > held_length) {
6911 control->held_length = so->so_rcv.sb_cc;
6912 held_length = 0;
6913 }
6914 goto wait_some_more;
6915 } else if (control->data == NULL) {
6916 /* we must re-sync since data
6917 * is probably being added
6918 */
6919 SCTP_INP_READ_LOCK(inp);
6920 if ((control->length > 0) && (control->data == NULL)) {
6921 /* big trouble.. we have the lock and its corrupt? */
6922#ifdef INVARIANTS
6923 panic ("Impossible data==NULL length !=0");
6924#endif
6925 out_flags |= MSG_EOR;
6926 out_flags |= MSG_TRUNC;
6927 control->length = 0;
6928 SCTP_INP_READ_UNLOCK(inp);
6929 goto done_with_control;
6930 }
6931 SCTP_INP_READ_UNLOCK(inp);
6932 /* We will fall around to get more data */
6933 }
6934 goto get_more_data;
6935 } else {
6936 /*-
6937 * Give caller back the mbuf chain,
6938 * store in uio_resid the length
6939 */
6940 wakeup_read_socket = 0;
6941 if ((control->end_added == 0) ||
6942 (TAILQ_NEXT(control, next) == NULL)) {
6943 /* Need to get rlock */
6944 if (hold_rlock == 0) {
6945 SCTP_INP_READ_LOCK(inp);
6946 hold_rlock = 1;
6947 }
6948 }
6949 if (control->end_added) {
6950 out_flags |= MSG_EOR;
6951 if ((control->do_not_ref_stcb == 0) &&
6952 (control->stcb != NULL) &&
6953 ((control->spec_flags & M_NOTIFICATION) == 0))
6954 control->stcb->asoc.strmin[control->sinfo_stream].delivery_started = 0;
6955 }
6956 if (control->spec_flags & M_NOTIFICATION) {
6957 out_flags |= MSG_NOTIFICATION;
6958 }
6959#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
6960#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD)
6961 uio->uio_resid = control->length;
6962#else
6963 uio_setresid(uio, control->length);
6964#endif
6965#else
6966 uio->uio_resid = control->length;
6967#endif
6968 *mp = control->data;
6969 m = control->data;
6970 while (m) {
6971 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_SB_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
6972 sctp_sblog(&so->so_rcv,
6973 control->do_not_ref_stcb?NULL:stcb, SCTP_LOG_SBFREE, SCTP_BUF_LEN(m));
6974 }
6975 sctp_sbfree(control, stcb, &so->so_rcv, m);
6976 freed_so_far += (uint32_t)SCTP_BUF_LEN(m);
6977 freed_so_far += MSIZE;
6978 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_SB_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
6979 sctp_sblog(&so->so_rcv,
6980 control->do_not_ref_stcb?NULL:stcb, SCTP_LOG_SBRESULT, 0);
6981 }
6982 m = SCTP_BUF_NEXT(m);
6983 }
6984 control->data = control->tail_mbuf = NULL;
6985 control->length = 0;
6986 if (out_flags & MSG_EOR) {
6987 /* Done with this control */
6988 goto done_with_control;
6989 }
6990 }
6991 release:
6992 if (hold_rlock == 1) {
6993 SCTP_INP_READ_UNLOCK(inp);
6994 hold_rlock = 0;
6995 }
6996#if defined(__Userspace__)
6997 if (hold_sblock == 0) {
6998 SOCKBUF_LOCK(&so->so_rcv);
6999 hold_sblock = 1;
7000 }
7001#else
7002 if (hold_sblock == 1) {
7003 SOCKBUF_UNLOCK(&so->so_rcv);
7004 hold_sblock = 0;
7005 }
7006#endif
7007#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
7008 sbunlock(&so->so_rcv, 1);
7009#endif
7010
7011#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
7012 sbunlock(&so->so_rcv);
7013 sockbuf_lock = 0;
7014#endif
7015
7016 release_unlocked:
7017 if (hold_sblock) {
7018 SOCKBUF_UNLOCK(&so->so_rcv);
7019 hold_sblock = 0;
7020 }
7021 if ((stcb) && (in_flags & MSG_PEEK) == 0) {
7022 if ((freed_so_far >= rwnd_req) &&
7023 (control && (control->do_not_ref_stcb == 0)) &&
7024 (no_rcv_needed == 0))
7025 sctp_user_rcvd(stcb, &freed_so_far, hold_rlock, rwnd_req);
7026 }
7027 out:
7028 if (msg_flags) {
7029 *msg_flags = out_flags;
7030 }
7031 if (((out_flags & MSG_EOR) == 0) &&
7032 ((in_flags & MSG_PEEK) == 0) &&
7033 (sinfo) &&
7034 (sctp_is_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_EXT_RCVINFO) ||
7035 sctp_is_feature_on(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_RECVNXTINFO))) {
7036 struct sctp_extrcvinfo *s_extra;
7037 s_extra = (struct sctp_extrcvinfo *)sinfo;
7038 s_extra->serinfo_next_flags = SCTP_NO_NEXT_MSG;
7039 }
7040 if (hold_rlock == 1) {
7041 SCTP_INP_READ_UNLOCK(inp);
7042 }
7043 if (hold_sblock) {
7044 SOCKBUF_UNLOCK(&so->so_rcv);
7045 }
7046#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
7047 if (sockbuf_lock) {
7048 sbunlock(&so->so_rcv);
7049 }
7050#endif
7051
7052 if (freecnt_applied) {
7053 /*
7054 * The lock on the socket buffer protects us so the free
7055 * code will stop. But since we used the socketbuf lock and
7056 * the sender uses the tcb_lock to increment, we need to use
7057 * the atomic add to the refcnt.
7058 */
7059 if (stcb == NULL) {
7060#ifdef INVARIANTS
7061 panic("stcb for refcnt has gone NULL?");
7062 goto stage_left;
7063#else
7064 goto stage_left;
7065#endif
7066 }
7067 /* Save the value back for next time */
7068 stcb->freed_by_sorcv_sincelast = freed_so_far;
7069 atomic_add_int(&stcb->asoc.refcnt, -1);
7070 }
7071 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) &SCTP_RECV_RWND_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
7072 if (stcb) {
7073 sctp_misc_ints(SCTP_SORECV_DONE,
7074 freed_so_far,
7075#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
7076#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD)
7077 ((uio) ? (slen - uio->uio_resid) : slen),
7078#else
7079 ((uio) ? (slen - uio_resid(uio)) : slen),
7080#endif
7081#else
7082 (uint32_t)((uio) ? (slen - uio->uio_resid) : slen),
7083#endif
7084 stcb->asoc.my_rwnd,
7085 so->so_rcv.sb_cc);
7086 } else {
7087 sctp_misc_ints(SCTP_SORECV_DONE,
7088 freed_so_far,
7089#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
7090#if defined(APPLE_LEOPARD)
7091 ((uio) ? (slen - uio->uio_resid) : slen),
7092#else
7093 ((uio) ? (slen - uio_resid(uio)) : slen),
7094#endif
7095#else
7096 (uint32_t)((uio) ? (slen - uio->uio_resid) : slen),
7097#endif
7098 0,
7099 so->so_rcv.sb_cc);
7100 }
7101 }
7102 stage_left:
7103 if (wakeup_read_socket) {
7104 sctp_sorwakeup(inp, so);
7105 }
7106 return (error);
7107}
7108
7109#ifdef SCTP_MBUF_LOGGING
7110struct mbuf *
7111sctp_m_free(struct mbuf *m)
7112{
7113 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_logging_level) & SCTP_MBUF_LOGGING_ENABLE) {
7114 sctp_log_mb(m, SCTP_MBUF_IFREE);
7115 }
7116 return (m_free(m));
7117}
7118
7119void
7120sctp_m_freem(struct mbuf *mb)
7121{
7122 while (mb != NULL)
7123 mb = sctp_m_free(mb);
7124}
