7127
7128int
7129sctp_dynamic_set_primary(struct sockaddr *sa, uint32_t vrf_id)
7130{
7131 /* Given a local address. For all associations
7132 * that holds the address, request a peer-set-primary.
7133 */
7134 struct sctp_ifa *ifa;
7135 struct sctp_laddr *wi;
7136
7137 ifa = sctp_find_ifa_by_addr(sa, vrf_id, SCTP_ADDR_NOT_LOCKED);
7138 if (ifa == NULL) {
7139 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, EADDRNOTAVAIL);
7140 return (EADDRNOTAVAIL);
7141 }
7142 /* Now that we have the ifa we must awaken the
7143 * iterator with this message.
7144 */
7145 wi = SCTP_ZONE_GET(SCTP_BASE_INFO(ipi_zone_laddr), struct sctp_laddr);
7146 if (wi == NULL) {
7147 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, ENOMEM);
7148 return (ENOMEM);
7149 }
7150 /* Now incr the count and int wi structure */
7151 SCTP_INCR_LADDR_COUNT();
7152 memset(wi, 0, sizeof(*wi));
7153 (void)SCTP_GETTIME_TIMEVAL(&wi->start_time);
7154 wi->ifa = ifa;
7155 wi->action = SCTP_SET_PRIM_ADDR;
7156 atomic_add_int(&ifa->refcount, 1);
7157
7158 /* Now add it to the work queue */
7159 SCTP_WQ_ADDR_LOCK();
7160 /*
7161 * Should this really be a tailq? As it is we will process the
7162 * newest first :-0
7163 */
7164 LIST_INSERT_HEAD(&SCTP_BASE_INFO(addr_wq), wi, sctp_nxt_addr);
7165 sctp_timer_start(SCTP_TIMER_TYPE_ADDR_WQ,
7166 (struct sctp_inpcb *)NULL,
7167 (struct sctp_tcb *)NULL,
7168 (struct sctp_nets *)NULL);
7169 SCTP_WQ_ADDR_UNLOCK();
7170 return (0);
7171}
7172
7173#if defined(__Userspace__)
7174/* no sctp_soreceive for __Userspace__ now */
7175#endif
7176#if !defined(__Userspace__)
7177int
7178sctp_soreceive( struct socket *so,
7179 struct sockaddr **psa,
7180 struct uio *uio,
7181 struct mbuf **mp0,
7182 struct mbuf **controlp,
7183 int *flagsp)
7184{
7185 int error, fromlen;
7186 uint8_t sockbuf[256];
7187 struct sockaddr *from;
7188 struct sctp_extrcvinfo sinfo;
7189 int filling_sinfo = 1;
7190 int flags;
7191 struct sctp_inpcb *inp;
7192
7193 inp = (struct sctp_inpcb *)so->so_pcb;
7194 /* pickup the assoc we are reading from */
7195 if (inp == NULL) {
7196 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, EINVAL);
7197 return (EINVAL);
7198 }
7199 if ((sctp_is_feature_off(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_RECVDATAIOEVNT) &&
7200 sctp_is_feature_off(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_RECVRCVINFO) &&
7201 sctp_is_feature_off(inp, SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_RECVNXTINFO)) ||
7202 (controlp == NULL)) {
7203 /* user does not want the sndrcv ctl */
7204 filling_sinfo = 0;
7205 }
7206 if (psa) {
7207 from = (struct sockaddr *)sockbuf;
7208 fromlen = sizeof(sockbuf);
7209#ifdef HAVE_SA_LEN
7210 from->sa_len = 0;
7211#endif
7212 } else {
7213 from = NULL;
7214 fromlen = 0;
7215 }
7216
7217#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
7218 SCTP_SOCKET_LOCK(so, 1);
7219#endif
7220 if (filling_sinfo) {
7221 memset(&sinfo, 0, sizeof(struct sctp_extrcvinfo));
7222 }
7223 if (flagsp != NULL) {
7224 flags = *flagsp;
7225 } else {
7226 flags = 0;
7227 }
7228 error = sctp_sorecvmsg(so, uio, mp0, from, fromlen, &flags,
7229 (struct sctp_sndrcvinfo *)&sinfo, filling_sinfo);
7230 if (flagsp != NULL) {
7231 *flagsp = flags;
7232 }
7233 if (controlp != NULL) {
7234 /* copy back the sinfo in a CMSG format */
7235 if (filling_sinfo && ((flags & MSG_NOTIFICATION) == 0)) {
7236 *controlp = sctp_build_ctl_nchunk(inp,
7237 (struct sctp_sndrcvinfo *)&sinfo);
7238 } else {
7239 *controlp = NULL;
7240 }
7241 }
7242 if (psa) {
7243 /* copy back the address info */
7244#ifdef HAVE_SA_LEN
7245 if (from && from->sa_len) {
7246#else
7247 if (from) {
7248#endif
7249#if (defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(_WIN32)) && !defined(__Userspace__)
7250 *psa = sodupsockaddr(from, M_NOWAIT);
7251#else
7252 *psa = dup_sockaddr(from, mp0 == 0);
7253#endif
7254 } else {
7255 *psa = NULL;
7256 }
7257 }
7258#if defined(__APPLE__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
7259 SCTP_SOCKET_UNLOCK(so, 1);
7260#endif
7261 return (error);
7262}
7263
7264#if defined(_WIN32) && !defined(__Userspace__)
7265/*
7266 * General routine to allocate a hash table with control of memory flags.
7267 * is in 7.0 and beyond for sure :-)
7268 */
7269void *
7270sctp_hashinit_flags(int elements, struct malloc_type *type,
7271 u_long *hashmask, int flags)
7272{
7273 long hashsize;
7274 LIST_HEAD(generic, generic) *hashtbl;
7275 int i;
7276
7277
7278 if (elements <= 0) {
7279#ifdef INVARIANTS
7280 panic("hashinit: bad elements");
7281#else
7282 SCTP_PRINTF("hashinit: bad elements?");
7283 elements = 1;
7284#endif
7285 }
7286 for (hashsize = 1; hashsize <= elements; hashsize <<= 1)
7287 continue;
7288 hashsize >>= 1;
7289 if (flags & HASH_WAITOK)
7290 hashtbl = malloc((u_long)hashsize * sizeof(*hashtbl), type, M_WAITOK);
7291 else if (flags & HASH_NOWAIT)
7292 hashtbl = malloc((u_long)hashsize * sizeof(*hashtbl), type, M_NOWAIT);
7293 else {
7294#ifdef INVARIANTS
7295 panic("flag incorrect in hashinit_flags");
7296#else
7297 return (NULL);
7298#endif
7299 }
7300
7301 /* no memory? */
7302 if (hashtbl == NULL)
7303 return (NULL);
7304
7305 for (i = 0; i < hashsize; i++)
7306 LIST_INIT(&hashtbl[i]);
7307 *hashmask = hashsize - 1;
7308 return (hashtbl);
7309}
7310#endif
7311#else /* __Userspace__ ifdef above sctp_soreceive */
7312/*
7313 * __Userspace__ Defining sctp_hashinit_flags() and sctp_hashdestroy() for userland.
7314 * NOTE: We don't want multiple definitions here. So sctp_hashinit_flags() above for
7315 *__FreeBSD__ must be excluded.
7316 *
7317 */
7318
7319void *
7320sctp_hashinit_flags(int elements, struct malloc_type *type,
7321 u_long *hashmask, int flags)
7322{
7323 long hashsize;
7324 LIST_HEAD(generic, generic) *hashtbl;
7325 int i;
7326
7327 if (elements <= 0) {
7328 SCTP_PRINTF("hashinit: bad elements?");
7329#ifdef INVARIANTS
7330 return (NULL);
7331#else
7332 elements = 1;
7333#endif
7334 }
7335 for (hashsize = 1; hashsize <= elements; hashsize <<= 1)
7336 continue;
7337 hashsize >>= 1;
7338 /*cannot use MALLOC here because it has to be declared or defined
7339 using MALLOC_DECLARE or MALLOC_DEFINE first. */
7340 if (flags & HASH_WAITOK)
7341 hashtbl = malloc((u_long)hashsize * sizeof(*hashtbl));
7342 else if (flags & HASH_NOWAIT)
7343 hashtbl = malloc((u_long)hashsize * sizeof(*hashtbl));
7344 else {
7345#ifdef INVARIANTS
7346 SCTP_PRINTF("flag incorrect in hashinit_flags.\n");
7347#endif
7348 return (NULL);
7349 }
7350
7351 /* no memory? */
7352 if (hashtbl == NULL)
7353 return (NULL);
7354
7355 for (i = 0; i < hashsize; i++)
7356 LIST_INIT(&hashtbl[i]);
7357 *hashmask = hashsize - 1;
7358 return (hashtbl);
7359}
7360
7361void
7362sctp_hashdestroy(void *vhashtbl, struct malloc_type *type, u_long hashmask)
7363{
7364 LIST_HEAD(generic, generic) *hashtbl, *hp;
7365
7366 hashtbl = vhashtbl;
7367 for (hp = hashtbl; hp <= &hashtbl[hashmask]; hp++)
7368 if (!LIST_EMPTY(hp)) {
7369 SCTP_PRINTF("hashdestroy: hash not empty.\n");
7370 return;
7371 }
7372 FREE(hashtbl, type);
7373}
7374
7375void
7376sctp_hashfreedestroy(void *vhashtbl, struct malloc_type *type, u_long hashmask)
7377{
7378 LIST_HEAD(generic, generic) *hashtbl/*, *hp*/;
7379 /*
7380 LIST_ENTRY(type) *start, *temp;
7381 */
7382 hashtbl = vhashtbl;
7383 /* Apparently temp is not dynamically allocated, so attempts to
7384 free it results in error.
7385 for (hp = hashtbl; hp <= &hashtbl[hashmask]; hp++)
7386 if (!LIST_EMPTY(hp)) {
7387 start = LIST_FIRST(hp);
7388 while (start != NULL) {
7389 temp = start;
7390 start = start->le_next;
7391 SCTP_PRINTF("%s: %p \n", __func__, (void *)temp);
7392 FREE(temp, type);
7393 }
7394 }
7395 */
7396 FREE(hashtbl, type);
7397}
7398
7399#endif
7400int
7401sctp_connectx_helper_add(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, struct sockaddr *addr,
7402 int totaddr, int *error)
7403{
7404 int added = 0;
7405 int i;
7406 struct sctp_inpcb *inp;
7407 struct sockaddr *sa;
7408 size_t incr = 0;
7409#ifdef INET
7410 struct sockaddr_in *sin;
7411#endif
7412#ifdef INET6
7413 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6;
7414#endif
7415
7416 sa = addr;
7417 inp = stcb->sctp_ep;
7418 *error = 0;
7419 for (i = 0; i < totaddr; i++) {
7420 switch (sa->sa_family) {
7421#ifdef INET
7422 case AF_INET:
7423 incr = sizeof(struct sockaddr_in);
7424 sin = (struct sockaddr_in *)sa;
7425 if ((sin->sin_addr.s_addr == INADDR_ANY) ||
7426 (sin->sin_addr.s_addr == INADDR_BROADCAST) ||
7427 IN_MULTICAST(ntohl(sin->sin_addr.s_addr))) {
7428 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, EINVAL);
7429 (void)sctp_free_assoc(inp, stcb, SCTP_NORMAL_PROC,
7430 SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL + SCTP_LOC_7);
7431 *error = EINVAL;
7432 goto out_now;
7433 }
7434 if (sctp_add_remote_addr(stcb, sa, NULL, stcb->asoc.port,
7435 SCTP_DONOT_SETSCOPE,
7436 SCTP_ADDR_IS_CONFIRMED)) {
7437 /* assoc gone no un-lock */
7438 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, ENOBUFS);
7439 (void)sctp_free_assoc(inp, stcb, SCTP_NORMAL_PROC,
7440 SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL + SCTP_LOC_8);
7441 *error = ENOBUFS;
7442 goto out_now;
7443 }
7444 added++;
7445 break;
7446#endif
7447#ifdef INET6
7448 case AF_INET6:
7449 incr = sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6);
7450 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)sa;
7451 if (IN6_IS_ADDR_UNSPECIFIED(&sin6->sin6_addr) ||
7452 IN6_IS_ADDR_MULTICAST(&sin6->sin6_addr)) {
7453 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, EINVAL);
7454 (void)sctp_free_assoc(inp, stcb, SCTP_NORMAL_PROC,
7455 SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL + SCTP_LOC_9);
7456 *error = EINVAL;
7457 goto out_now;
7458 }
7459 if (sctp_add_remote_addr(stcb, sa, NULL, stcb->asoc.port,
7460 SCTP_DONOT_SETSCOPE,
7461 SCTP_ADDR_IS_CONFIRMED)) {
7462 /* assoc gone no un-lock */
7463 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, ENOBUFS);
7464 (void)sctp_free_assoc(inp, stcb, SCTP_NORMAL_PROC,
7465 SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL + SCTP_LOC_10);
7466 *error = ENOBUFS;
7467 goto out_now;
7468 }
7469 added++;
7470 break;
7471#endif
7472#if defined(__Userspace__)
7473 case AF_CONN:
7474 incr = sizeof(struct sockaddr_conn);
7475 if (sctp_add_remote_addr(stcb, sa, NULL, stcb->asoc.port,
7476 SCTP_DONOT_SETSCOPE,
7477 SCTP_ADDR_IS_CONFIRMED)) {
7478 /* assoc gone no un-lock */
7479 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(NULL, stcb, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, ENOBUFS);
7480 (void)sctp_free_assoc(inp, stcb, SCTP_NORMAL_PROC,
7481 SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL + SCTP_LOC_11);
7482 *error = ENOBUFS;
7483 goto out_now;
7484 }
7485 added++;
7486 break;
7487#endif
7488 default:
7489 break;
7490 }
7491 sa = (struct sockaddr *)((caddr_t)sa + incr);
7492 }
7493 out_now:
7494 return (added);
7495}
7496
7497int
7498sctp_connectx_helper_find(struct sctp_inpcb *inp, struct sockaddr *addr,
7499 unsigned int totaddr,
7500 unsigned int *num_v4, unsigned int *num_v6,
7501 unsigned int limit)
7502{
7503 struct sockaddr *sa;
7504 struct sctp_tcb *stcb;
7505 unsigned int incr, at, i;
7506
7507 at = 0;
7508 sa = addr;
7509 *num_v6 = *num_v4 = 0;
7510 /* account and validate addresses */
7511 if (totaddr == 0) {
7512 return (EINVAL);
7513 }
7514 for (i = 0; i < totaddr; i++) {
7515 if (at + sizeof(struct sockaddr) > limit) {
7516 return (EINVAL);
7517 }
7518 switch (sa->sa_family) {
7519#ifdef INET
7520 case AF_INET:
7521 incr = (unsigned int)sizeof(struct sockaddr_in);
7522#ifdef HAVE_SA_LEN
7523 if (sa->sa_len != incr) {
7524 return (EINVAL);
7525 }
7526#endif
7527 (*num_v4) += 1;
7528 break;
7529#endif
7530#ifdef INET6
7531 case AF_INET6:
7532 {
7533 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6;
7534
7535 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)sa;
7536 if (IN6_IS_ADDR_V4MAPPED(&sin6->sin6_addr)) {
7537 /* Must be non-mapped for connectx */
7538 return (EINVAL);
7539 }
7540 incr = (unsigned int)sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6);
7541#ifdef HAVE_SA_LEN
7542 if (sa->sa_len != incr) {
7543 return (EINVAL);
7544 }
7545#endif
7546 (*num_v6) += 1;
7547 break;
7548 }
7549#endif
7550 default:
7551 return (EINVAL);
7552 }
7553 if ((at + incr) > limit) {
7554 return (EINVAL);
7555 }
7556 SCTP_INP_INCR_REF(inp);
7557 stcb = sctp_findassociation_ep_addr(&inp, sa, NULL, NULL, NULL);
7558 if (stcb != NULL) {
7559 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
7560 return (EALREADY);
7561 } else {
7562 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
7563 }
7564 at += incr;
7565 sa = (struct sockaddr *)((caddr_t)sa + incr);
7566 }
7567 return (0);
7568}
7569
7570/*
7571 * sctp_bindx(ADD) for one address.
7572 * assumes all arguments are valid/checked by caller.
7573 */
7574void
7575sctp_bindx_add_address(struct socket *so, struct sctp_inpcb *inp,
7576 struct sockaddr *sa, uint32_t vrf_id, int *error,
7577 void *p)
7578{
7579#if defined(INET) && defined(INET6)
7580 struct sockaddr_in sin;
7581#endif
7582#ifdef INET6
7583 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6;
7584#endif
7585#ifdef INET
7586 struct sockaddr_in *sinp;
7587#endif
7588 struct sockaddr *addr_to_use;
7589 struct sctp_inpcb *lep;
7590#ifdef SCTP_MVRF
7591 int i;
7592#endif
7593 uint16_t port;
7594
7595 /* see if we're bound all already! */
7596 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUNDALL) {
7597 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, EINVAL);
7598 *error = EINVAL;
7599 return;
7600 }
7601#ifdef SCTP_MVRF
7602 /* Is the VRF one we have */
7603 for (i = 0; i < inp->num_vrfs; i++) {
7604 if (vrf_id == inp->m_vrf_ids[i]) {
7605 break;
7606 }
7607 }
7608 if (i == inp->num_vrfs) {
7609 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, EINVAL);
7610 *error = EINVAL;
7611 return;
7612 }
7613#endif
7614 switch (sa->sa_family) {
7615#ifdef INET6
7616 case AF_INET6:
7617#ifdef HAVE_SA_LEN
7618 if (sa->sa_len != sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6)) {
7619 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, EINVAL);
7620 *error = EINVAL;
7621 return;
7622 }
7623#endif
7624 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUND_V6) == 0) {
7625 /* can only bind v6 on PF_INET6 sockets */
7626 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, EINVAL);
7627 *error = EINVAL;
7628 return;
7629 }
7630 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)sa;
7631 port = sin6->sin6_port;
7632#ifdef INET
7633 if (IN6_IS_ADDR_V4MAPPED(&sin6->sin6_addr)) {
7634 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUND_V6) &&
7635 SCTP_IPV6_V6ONLY(inp)) {
7636 /* can't bind v4-mapped on PF_INET sockets */
7637 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, EINVAL);
7638 *error = EINVAL;
7639 return;
7640 }
7641 in6_sin6_2_sin(&sin, sin6);
7642 addr_to_use = (struct sockaddr *)&sin;
7643 } else {
7644 addr_to_use = sa;
7645 }
7646#else
7647 addr_to_use = sa;
7648#endif
7649 break;
7650#endif
7651#ifdef INET
7652 case AF_INET:
7653#ifdef HAVE_SA_LEN
7654 if (sa->sa_len != sizeof(struct sockaddr_in)) {
7655 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, EINVAL);
7656 *error = EINVAL;
7657 return;
7658 }
7659#endif
7660 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUND_V6) &&
7661 SCTP_IPV6_V6ONLY(inp)) {
7662 /* can't bind v4 on PF_INET sockets */
7663 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, EINVAL);
7664 *error = EINVAL;
7665 return;
7666 }
7667 sinp = (struct sockaddr_in *)sa;
7668 port = sinp->sin_port;
7669 addr_to_use = sa;
7670 break;
7671#endif
7672 default:
7673 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, EINVAL);
7674 *error = EINVAL;
7675 return;
7676 }
7677 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_UNBOUND) {
7678#if !(defined(_WIN32) || defined(__Userspace__))
7679 if (p == NULL) {
7680 /* Can't get proc for Net/Open BSD */
7681 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, EINVAL);
7682 *error = EINVAL;
7683 return;
7684 }
7685#endif
7686 *error = sctp_inpcb_bind(so, addr_to_use, NULL, p);
7687 return;
7688 }
7689 /* Validate the incoming port. */
7690 if ((port != 0) && (port != inp->sctp_lport)) {
7691 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, EINVAL);
7692 *error = EINVAL;
7693 return;
7694 }
7695 lep = sctp_pcb_findep(addr_to_use, 1, 0, vrf_id);
7696 if (lep == NULL) {
7697 /* add the address */
7698 *error = sctp_addr_mgmt_ep_sa(inp, addr_to_use,
7699 SCTP_ADD_IP_ADDRESS, vrf_id);
7700 } else {
7701 if (lep != inp) {
7702 *error = EADDRINUSE;
7703 }
7704 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(lep);
7705 }
7706}
7707
7708/*
7709 * sctp_bindx(DELETE) for one address.
7710 * assumes all arguments are valid/checked by caller.
7711 */
7712void
7713sctp_bindx_delete_address(struct sctp_inpcb *inp,
7714 struct sockaddr *sa, uint32_t vrf_id, int *error)
7715{
7716 struct sockaddr *addr_to_use;
7717#if defined(INET) && defined(INET6)
7718 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6;
7719 struct sockaddr_in sin;
7720#endif
7721#ifdef SCTP_MVRF
7722 int i;
7723#endif
7724
7725 /* see if we're bound all already! */
7726 if (inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUNDALL) {
7727 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, EINVAL);
7728 *error = EINVAL;
7729 return;
7730 }
7731#ifdef SCTP_MVRF
7732 /* Is the VRF one we have */
7733 for (i = 0; i < inp->num_vrfs; i++) {
7734 if (vrf_id == inp->m_vrf_ids[i]) {
7735 break;
7736 }
7737 }
7738 if (i == inp->num_vrfs) {
7739 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, EINVAL);
7740 *error = EINVAL;
7741 return;
7742 }
7743#endif
7744 switch (sa->sa_family) {
7745#ifdef INET6
7746 case AF_INET6:
7747#ifdef HAVE_SA_LEN
7748 if (sa->sa_len != sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6)) {
7749 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, EINVAL);
7750 *error = EINVAL;
7751 return;
7752 }
7753#endif
7754 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUND_V6) == 0) {
7755 /* can only bind v6 on PF_INET6 sockets */
7756 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, EINVAL);
7757 *error = EINVAL;
7758 return;
7759 }
7760#ifdef INET
7761 sin6 = (struct sockaddr_in6 *)sa;
7762 if (IN6_IS_ADDR_V4MAPPED(&sin6->sin6_addr)) {
7763 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUND_V6) &&
7764 SCTP_IPV6_V6ONLY(inp)) {
7765 /* can't bind mapped-v4 on PF_INET sockets */
7766 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, EINVAL);
7767 *error = EINVAL;
7768 return;
7769 }
7770 in6_sin6_2_sin(&sin, sin6);
7771 addr_to_use = (struct sockaddr *)&sin;
7772 } else {
7773 addr_to_use = sa;
7774 }
7775#else
7776 addr_to_use = sa;
7777#endif
7778 break;
7779#endif
7780#ifdef INET
7781 case AF_INET:
7782#ifdef HAVE_SA_LEN
7783 if (sa->sa_len != sizeof(struct sockaddr_in)) {
7784 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, EINVAL);
7785 *error = EINVAL;
7786 return;
7787 }
7788#endif
7789 if ((inp->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUND_V6) &&
7790 SCTP_IPV6_V6ONLY(inp)) {
7791 /* can't bind v4 on PF_INET sockets */
7792 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, EINVAL);
7793 *error = EINVAL;
7794 return;
7795 }
7796 addr_to_use = sa;
7797 break;
7798#endif
7799 default:
7800 SCTP_LTRACE_ERR_RET(inp, NULL, NULL, SCTP_FROM_SCTPUTIL, EINVAL);
7801 *error = EINVAL;
7802 return;
7803 }
7804 /* No lock required mgmt_ep_sa does its own locking. */
7805 *error = sctp_addr_mgmt_ep_sa(inp, addr_to_use, SCTP_DEL_IP_ADDRESS,
7806 vrf_id);
7807}
7808
7809/*
7810 * returns the valid local address count for an assoc, taking into account
7811 * all scoping rules
7812 */
7813int
7814sctp_local_addr_count(struct sctp_tcb *stcb)
7815{
7816 int loopback_scope;
7817#if defined(INET)
7818 int ipv4_local_scope, ipv4_addr_legal;
7819#endif
7820#if defined(INET6)
7821 int local_scope, site_scope, ipv6_addr_legal;
7822#endif
7823#if defined(__Userspace__)
7824 int conn_addr_legal;
7825#endif
7826 struct sctp_vrf *vrf;
7827 struct sctp_ifn *sctp_ifn;
7828 struct sctp_ifa *sctp_ifa;
7829 int count = 0;
7830
7831 /* Turn on all the appropriate scopes */
7832 loopback_scope = stcb->asoc.scope.loopback_scope;
7833#if defined(INET)
7834 ipv4_local_scope = stcb->asoc.scope.ipv4_local_scope;
7835 ipv4_addr_legal = stcb->asoc.scope.ipv4_addr_legal;
7836#endif
7837#if defined(INET6)
7838 local_scope = stcb->asoc.scope.local_scope;
7839 site_scope = stcb->asoc.scope.site_scope;
7840 ipv6_addr_legal = stcb->asoc.scope.ipv6_addr_legal;
7841#endif
7842#if defined(__Userspace__)
7843 conn_addr_legal = stcb->asoc.scope.conn_addr_legal;
7844#endif
7845 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_RLOCK();
7846 vrf = sctp_find_vrf(stcb->asoc.vrf_id);
7847 if (vrf == NULL) {
7848 /* no vrf, no addresses */
7849 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_RUNLOCK();
7850 return (0);
7851 }
7852
7853 if (stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_BOUNDALL) {
7854 /*
7855 * bound all case: go through all ifns on the vrf
7856 */
7857 LIST_FOREACH(sctp_ifn, &vrf->ifnlist, next_ifn) {
7858 if ((loopback_scope == 0) &&
7859 SCTP_IFN_IS_IFT_LOOP(sctp_ifn)) {
7860 continue;
7861 }
7862 LIST_FOREACH(sctp_ifa, &sctp_ifn->ifalist, next_ifa) {
7863 if (sctp_is_addr_restricted(stcb, sctp_ifa))
7864 continue;
7865 switch (sctp_ifa->address.sa.sa_family) {
7866#ifdef INET
7867 case AF_INET:
7868 if (ipv4_addr_legal) {
7869 struct sockaddr_in *sin;
7870
7871 sin = &sctp_ifa->address.sin;
7872 if (sin->sin_addr.s_addr == 0) {
7873 /* skip unspecified addrs */
7874 continue;
7875 }
7876#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
7877 if (prison_check_ip4(stcb->sctp_ep->ip_inp.inp.inp_cred,
7878 &sin->sin_addr) != 0) {
7879 continue;
7880 }
7881#endif
7882 if ((ipv4_local_scope == 0) &&
7883 (IN4_ISPRIVATE_ADDRESS(&sin->sin_addr))) {
7884 continue;
7885 }
7886 /* count this one */
7887 count++;
7888 } else {
7889 continue;
7890 }
7891 break;
7892#endif
7893#ifdef INET6
7894 case AF_INET6:
7895 if (ipv6_addr_legal) {
7896 struct sockaddr_in6 *sin6;
7897
7898#if defined(SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE) && !defined(SCTP_KAME)
7899 struct sockaddr_in6 lsa6;
7900#endif
7901 sin6 = &sctp_ifa->address.sin6;
7902 if (IN6_IS_ADDR_UNSPECIFIED(&sin6->sin6_addr)) {
7903 continue;
7904 }
7905#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
7906 if (prison_check_ip6(stcb->sctp_ep->ip_inp.inp.inp_cred,
7907 &sin6->sin6_addr) != 0) {
7908 continue;
7909 }
7910#endif
7911 if (IN6_IS_ADDR_LINKLOCAL(&sin6->sin6_addr)) {
7912 if (local_scope == 0)
7913 continue;
7914#if defined(SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE)
7915 if (sin6->sin6_scope_id == 0) {
7916#ifdef SCTP_KAME
7917 if (sa6_recoverscope(sin6) != 0)
7918 /*
7919 * bad link
7920 * local
7921 * address
7922 */
7923 continue;
7924#else
7925 lsa6 = *sin6;
7926 if (in6_recoverscope(&lsa6,
7927 &lsa6.sin6_addr,
7928 NULL))
7929 /*
7930 * bad link
7931 * local
7932 * address
7933 */
7934 continue;
7935 sin6 = &lsa6;
7936#endif /* SCTP_KAME */
7937 }
7938#endif /* SCTP_EMBEDDED_V6_SCOPE */
7939 }
7940 if ((site_scope == 0) &&
7941 (IN6_IS_ADDR_SITELOCAL(&sin6->sin6_addr))) {
7942 continue;
7943 }
7944 /* count this one */
7945 count++;
7946 }
7947 break;
7948#endif
7949#if defined(__Userspace__)
7950 case AF_CONN:
7951 if (conn_addr_legal) {
7952 count++;
7953 }
7954 break;
7955#endif
7956 default:
7957 /* TSNH */
7958 break;
7959 }
7960 }
7961 }
7962 } else {
7963 /*
7964 * subset bound case
7965 */
7966 struct sctp_laddr *laddr;
7967 LIST_FOREACH(laddr, &stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_addr_list,
7968 sctp_nxt_addr) {
7969 if (sctp_is_addr_restricted(stcb, laddr->ifa)) {
7970 continue;
7971 }
7972 /* count this one */
7973 count++;
7974 }
7975 }
7976 SCTP_IPI_ADDR_RUNLOCK();
7977 return (count);
7978}
7979
7980#if defined(SCTP_LOCAL_TRACE_BUF)
7981
7982void
7983sctp_log_trace(uint32_t subsys, const char *str SCTP_UNUSED, uint32_t a, uint32_t b, uint32_t c, uint32_t d, uint32_t e, uint32_t f)
7984{
7985 uint32_t saveindex, newindex;
7986
7987#if defined(_WIN32) && !defined(__Userspace__)
7988 if (SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_log) == NULL) {
7989 return;
7990 }
7991 do {
7992 saveindex = SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_log)->index;
7993 if (saveindex >= SCTP_MAX_LOGGING_SIZE) {
7994 newindex = 1;
7995 } else {
7996 newindex = saveindex + 1;
7997 }
7998 } while (atomic_cmpset_int(&SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_log)->index, saveindex, newindex) == 0);
7999 if (saveindex >= SCTP_MAX_LOGGING_SIZE) {
8000 saveindex = 0;
8001 }
8002 SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_log)->entry[saveindex].timestamp = SCTP_GET_CYCLECOUNT;
8003 SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_log)->entry[saveindex].subsys = subsys;
8004 SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_log)->entry[saveindex].params[0] = a;
8005 SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_log)->entry[saveindex].params[1] = b;
8006 SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_log)->entry[saveindex].params[2] = c;
8007 SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_log)->entry[saveindex].params[3] = d;
8008 SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_log)->entry[saveindex].params[4] = e;
8009 SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_log)->entry[saveindex].params[5] = f;
8010#else
8011 do {
8012 saveindex = SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_log).index;
8013 if (saveindex >= SCTP_MAX_LOGGING_SIZE) {
8014 newindex = 1;
8015 } else {
8016 newindex = saveindex + 1;
8017 }
8018 } while (atomic_cmpset_int(&SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_log).index, saveindex, newindex) == 0);
8019 if (saveindex >= SCTP_MAX_LOGGING_SIZE) {
8020 saveindex = 0;
8021 }
8022 SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_log).entry[saveindex].timestamp = SCTP_GET_CYCLECOUNT;
8023 SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_log).entry[saveindex].subsys = subsys;
8024 SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_log).entry[saveindex].params[0] = a;
8025 SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_log).entry[saveindex].params[1] = b;
8026 SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_log).entry[saveindex].params[2] = c;
8027 SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_log).entry[saveindex].params[3] = d;
8028 SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_log).entry[saveindex].params[4] = e;
8029 SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_log).entry[saveindex].params[5] = f;
8030#endif
8031}
8032
8033#endif
8034#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
8035static void
8036sctp_recv_udp_tunneled_packet(struct mbuf *m, int off, struct inpcb *inp,
8037 const struct sockaddr *sa SCTP_UNUSED, void *ctx SCTP_UNUSED)
8038{
8039 struct ip *iph;
8040#ifdef INET6
8041 struct ip6_hdr *ip6;
8042#endif
8043 struct mbuf *sp, *last;
8044 struct udphdr *uhdr;
8045 uint16_t port;
8046
8047 if ((m->m_flags & M_PKTHDR) == 0) {
8048 /* Can't handle one that is not a pkt hdr */
8049 goto out;
8050 }
8051 /* Pull the src port */
8052 iph = mtod(m, struct ip *);
8053 uhdr = (struct udphdr *)((caddr_t)iph + off);
8054 port = uhdr->uh_sport;
8055 /* Split out the mbuf chain. Leave the
8056 * IP header in m, place the
8057 * rest in the sp.
8058 */
8059 sp = m_split(m, off, M_NOWAIT);
8060 if (sp == NULL) {
8061 /* Gak, drop packet, we can't do a split */
8062 goto out;
8063 }
8064 if (sp->m_pkthdr.len < sizeof(struct udphdr) + sizeof(struct sctphdr)) {
8065 /* Gak, packet can't have an SCTP header in it - too small */
8066 m_freem(sp);
8067 goto out;
8068 }
8069 /* Now pull up the UDP header and SCTP header together */
8070 sp = m_pullup(sp, sizeof(struct udphdr) + sizeof(struct sctphdr));
8071 if (sp == NULL) {
8072 /* Gak pullup failed */
8073 goto out;
8074 }
8075 /* Trim out the UDP header */
8076 m_adj(sp, sizeof(struct udphdr));
8077
8078 /* Now reconstruct the mbuf chain */
8079 for (last = m; last->m_next; last = last->m_next);
8080 last->m_next = sp;
8081 m->m_pkthdr.len += sp->m_pkthdr.len;
8082 /*
8083 * The CSUM_DATA_VALID flags indicates that the HW checked the
8084 * UDP checksum and it was valid.
8085 * Since CSUM_DATA_VALID == CSUM_SCTP_VALID this would imply that
8086 * the HW also verified the SCTP checksum. Therefore, clear the bit.
8087 */
8088 SCTPDBG(SCTP_DEBUG_CRCOFFLOAD,
8089 "sctp_recv_udp_tunneled_packet(): Packet of length %d received on %s with csum_flags 0x%b.\n",
8090 m->m_pkthdr.len,
8091 if_name(m->m_pkthdr.rcvif),
8092 (int)m->m_pkthdr.csum_flags, CSUM_BITS);
8093 m->m_pkthdr.csum_flags &= ~CSUM_DATA_VALID;
8094 iph = mtod(m, struct ip *);
8095 switch (iph->ip_v) {
8096#ifdef INET
8097 case IPVERSION:
8098 iph->ip_len = htons(ntohs(iph->ip_len) - sizeof(struct udphdr));
8099 sctp_input_with_port(m, off, port);
8100 break;
8101#endif
8102#ifdef INET6
8103 case IPV6_VERSION >> 4:
8104 ip6 = mtod(m, struct ip6_hdr *);
8105 ip6->ip6_plen = htons(ntohs(ip6->ip6_plen) - sizeof(struct udphdr));
8106 sctp6_input_with_port(&m, &off, port);
8107 break;
8108#endif
8109 default:
8110 goto out;
8111 break;
8112 }
8113 return;
8114 out:
8115 m_freem(m);
8116}
8117
8118#ifdef INET
8119static void
8120sctp_recv_icmp_tunneled_packet(int cmd, struct sockaddr *sa, void *vip, void *ctx SCTP_UNUSED)
8121{
8122 struct ip *outer_ip, *inner_ip;
8123 struct sctphdr *sh;
8124 struct icmp *icmp;
8125 struct udphdr *udp;
8126 struct sctp_inpcb *inp;
8127 struct sctp_tcb *stcb;
8128 struct sctp_nets *net;
8129 struct sctp_init_chunk *ch;
8130 struct sockaddr_in src, dst;
8131 uint8_t type, code;
8132
8133 inner_ip = (struct ip *)vip;
8134 icmp = (struct icmp *)((caddr_t)inner_ip -
8135 (sizeof(struct icmp) - sizeof(struct ip)));
8136 outer_ip = (struct ip *)((caddr_t)icmp - sizeof(struct ip));
8137 if (ntohs(outer_ip->ip_len) <
8138 sizeof(struct ip) + 8 + (inner_ip->ip_hl << 2) + sizeof(struct udphdr) + 8) {
8139 return;
8140 }
8141 udp = (struct udphdr *)((caddr_t)inner_ip + (inner_ip->ip_hl << 2));
8142 sh = (struct sctphdr *)(udp + 1);
8143 memset(&src, 0, sizeof(struct sockaddr_in));
8144 src.sin_family = AF_INET;
8145#ifdef HAVE_SIN_LEN
8146 src.sin_len = sizeof(struct sockaddr_in);
8147#endif
8148 src.sin_port = sh->src_port;
8149 src.sin_addr = inner_ip->ip_src;
8150 memset(&dst, 0, sizeof(struct sockaddr_in));
8151 dst.sin_family = AF_INET;
8152#ifdef HAVE_SIN_LEN
8153 dst.sin_len = sizeof(struct sockaddr_in);
8154#endif
8155 dst.sin_port = sh->dest_port;
8156 dst.sin_addr = inner_ip->ip_dst;
8157 /*
8158 * 'dst' holds the dest of the packet that failed to be sent.
8159 * 'src' holds our local endpoint address. Thus we reverse
8160 * the dst and the src in the lookup.
8161 */
8162 inp = NULL;
8163 net = NULL;
8164 stcb = sctp_findassociation_addr_sa((struct sockaddr *)&dst,
8165 (struct sockaddr *)&src,
8166 &inp, &net, 1,
8167 SCTP_DEFAULT_VRFID);
8168 if ((stcb != NULL) &&
8169 (net != NULL) &&
8170 (inp != NULL)) {
8171 /* Check the UDP port numbers */
8172 if ((udp->uh_dport != net->port) ||
8173 (udp->uh_sport != htons(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_udp_tunneling_port)))) {
8174 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
8175 return;
8176 }
8177 /* Check the verification tag */
8178 if (ntohl(sh->v_tag) != 0) {
8179 /*
8180 * This must be the verification tag used
8181 * for sending out packets. We don't
8182 * consider packets reflecting the
8183 * verification tag.
8184 */
8185 if (ntohl(sh->v_tag) != stcb->asoc.peer_vtag) {
8186 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
8187 return;
8188 }
8189 } else {
8190 if (ntohs(outer_ip->ip_len) >=
8191 sizeof(struct ip) +
8192 8 + (inner_ip->ip_hl << 2) + 8 + 20) {
8193 /*
8194 * In this case we can check if we
8195 * got an INIT chunk and if the
8196 * initiate tag matches.
8197 */
8198 ch = (struct sctp_init_chunk *)(sh + 1);
8199 if ((ch->ch.chunk_type != SCTP_INITIATION) ||
8200 (ntohl(ch->init.initiate_tag) != stcb->asoc.my_vtag)) {
8201 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
8202 return;
8203 }
8204 } else {
8205 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
8206 return;
8207 }
8208 }
8209 type = icmp->icmp_type;
8210 code = icmp->icmp_code;
8211 if ((type == ICMP_UNREACH) &&
8212 (code == ICMP_UNREACH_PORT)) {
8213 code = ICMP_UNREACH_PROTOCOL;
8214 }
8215 sctp_notify(inp, stcb, net, type, code,
8216 ntohs(inner_ip->ip_len),
8217 (uint32_t)ntohs(icmp->icmp_nextmtu));
8218#if defined(__Userspace__)
8219 if (!(stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE) &&
8220 (stcb->sctp_socket != NULL)) {
8221 struct socket *upcall_socket;
8222
8223 upcall_socket = stcb->sctp_socket;
8224 SOCK_LOCK(upcall_socket);
8225 soref(upcall_socket);
8226 SOCK_UNLOCK(upcall_socket);
8227 if ((upcall_socket->so_upcall != NULL) &&
8228 (upcall_socket->so_error != 0)) {
8229 (*upcall_socket->so_upcall)(upcall_socket, upcall_socket->so_upcallarg, M_NOWAIT);
8230 }
8231 ACCEPT_LOCK();
8232 SOCK_LOCK(upcall_socket);
8233 sorele(upcall_socket);
8234 }
8235#endif
8236 } else {
8237 if ((stcb == NULL) && (inp != NULL)) {
8238 /* reduce ref-count */
8239 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
8240 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
8241 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
8242 }
8243 if (stcb) {
8244 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
8245 }
8246 }
8247 return;
8248}
8249#endif
8250
8251#ifdef INET6
8252static void
8253sctp_recv_icmp6_tunneled_packet(int cmd, struct sockaddr *sa, void *d, void *ctx SCTP_UNUSED)
8254{
8255 struct ip6ctlparam *ip6cp;
8256 struct sctp_inpcb *inp;
8257 struct sctp_tcb *stcb;
8258 struct sctp_nets *net;
8259 struct sctphdr sh;
8260 struct udphdr udp;
8261 struct sockaddr_in6 src, dst;
8262 uint8_t type, code;
8263
8264 ip6cp = (struct ip6ctlparam *)d;
8265 /*
8266 * XXX: We assume that when IPV6 is non NULL, M and OFF are
8267 * valid.
8268 */
8269 if (ip6cp->ip6c_m == NULL) {
8270 return;
8271 }
8272 /* Check if we can safely examine the ports and the
8273 * verification tag of the SCTP common header.
8274 */
8275 if (ip6cp->ip6c_m->m_pkthdr.len <
8276 ip6cp->ip6c_off + sizeof(struct udphdr)+ offsetof(struct sctphdr, checksum)) {
8277 return;
8278 }
8279 /* Copy out the UDP header. */
8280 memset(&udp, 0, sizeof(struct udphdr));
8281 m_copydata(ip6cp->ip6c_m,
8282 ip6cp->ip6c_off,
8283 sizeof(struct udphdr),
8284 (caddr_t)&udp);
8285 /* Copy out the port numbers and the verification tag. */
8286 memset(&sh, 0, sizeof(struct sctphdr));
8287 m_copydata(ip6cp->ip6c_m,
8288 ip6cp->ip6c_off + sizeof(struct udphdr),
8289 sizeof(uint16_t) + sizeof(uint16_t) + sizeof(uint32_t),
8290 (caddr_t)&sh);
8291 memset(&src, 0, sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6));
8292 src.sin6_family = AF_INET6;
8293#ifdef HAVE_SIN6_LEN
8294 src.sin6_len = sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6);
8295#endif
8296 src.sin6_port = sh.src_port;
8297 src.sin6_addr = ip6cp->ip6c_ip6->ip6_src;
8298#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
8299 if (in6_setscope(&src.sin6_addr, ip6cp->ip6c_m->m_pkthdr.rcvif, NULL) != 0) {
8300 return;
8301 }
8302#endif
8303 memset(&dst, 0, sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6));
8304 dst.sin6_family = AF_INET6;
8305#ifdef HAVE_SIN6_LEN
8306 dst.sin6_len = sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6);
8307#endif
8308 dst.sin6_port = sh.dest_port;
8309 dst.sin6_addr = ip6cp->ip6c_ip6->ip6_dst;
8310#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
8311 if (in6_setscope(&dst.sin6_addr, ip6cp->ip6c_m->m_pkthdr.rcvif, NULL) != 0) {
8312 return;
8313 }
8314#endif
8315 inp = NULL;
8316 net = NULL;
8317 stcb = sctp_findassociation_addr_sa((struct sockaddr *)&dst,
8318 (struct sockaddr *)&src,
8319 &inp, &net, 1, SCTP_DEFAULT_VRFID);
8320 if ((stcb != NULL) &&
8321 (net != NULL) &&
8322 (inp != NULL)) {
8323 /* Check the UDP port numbers */
8324 if ((udp.uh_dport != net->port) ||
8325 (udp.uh_sport != htons(SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_udp_tunneling_port)))) {
8326 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
8327 return;
8328 }
8329 /* Check the verification tag */
8330 if (ntohl(sh.v_tag) != 0) {
8331 /*
8332 * This must be the verification tag used for
8333 * sending out packets. We don't consider
8334 * packets reflecting the verification tag.
8335 */
8336 if (ntohl(sh.v_tag) != stcb->asoc.peer_vtag) {
8337 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
8338 return;
8339 }
8340 } else {
8341#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
8342 if (ip6cp->ip6c_m->m_pkthdr.len >=
8343 ip6cp->ip6c_off + sizeof(struct udphdr) +
8344 sizeof(struct sctphdr) +
8345 sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr) +
8346 offsetof(struct sctp_init, a_rwnd)) {
8347 /*
8348 * In this case we can check if we
8349 * got an INIT chunk and if the
8350 * initiate tag matches.
8351 */
8352 uint32_t initiate_tag;
8353 uint8_t chunk_type;
8354
8355 m_copydata(ip6cp->ip6c_m,
8356 ip6cp->ip6c_off +
8357 sizeof(struct udphdr) +
8358 sizeof(struct sctphdr),
8359 sizeof(uint8_t),
8360 (caddr_t)&chunk_type);
8361 m_copydata(ip6cp->ip6c_m,
8362 ip6cp->ip6c_off +
8363 sizeof(struct udphdr) +
8364 sizeof(struct sctphdr) +
8365 sizeof(struct sctp_chunkhdr),
8366 sizeof(uint32_t),
8367 (caddr_t)&initiate_tag);
8368 if ((chunk_type != SCTP_INITIATION) ||
8369 (ntohl(initiate_tag) != stcb->asoc.my_vtag)) {
8370 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
8371 return;
8372 }
8373 } else {
8374 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
8375 return;
8376 }
8377#else
8378 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
8379 return;
8380#endif
8381 }
8382 type = ip6cp->ip6c_icmp6->icmp6_type;
8383 code = ip6cp->ip6c_icmp6->icmp6_code;
8384 if ((type == ICMP6_DST_UNREACH) &&
8385 (code == ICMP6_DST_UNREACH_NOPORT)) {
8386 type = ICMP6_PARAM_PROB;
8387 code = ICMP6_PARAMPROB_NEXTHEADER;
8388 }
8389 sctp6_notify(inp, stcb, net, type, code,
8390 ntohl(ip6cp->ip6c_icmp6->icmp6_mtu));
8391#if defined(__Userspace__)
8392 if (!(stcb->sctp_ep->sctp_flags & SCTP_PCB_FLAGS_SOCKET_GONE) &&
8393 (stcb->sctp_socket != NULL)) {
8394 struct socket *upcall_socket;
8395
8396 upcall_socket = stcb->sctp_socket;
8397 SOCK_LOCK(upcall_socket);
8398 soref(upcall_socket);
8399 SOCK_UNLOCK(upcall_socket);
8400 if ((upcall_socket->so_upcall != NULL) &&
8401 (upcall_socket->so_error != 0)) {
8402 (*upcall_socket->so_upcall)(upcall_socket, upcall_socket->so_upcallarg, M_NOWAIT);
8403 }
8404 ACCEPT_LOCK();
8405 SOCK_LOCK(upcall_socket);
8406 sorele(upcall_socket);
8407 }
8408#endif
8409 } else {
8410 if ((stcb == NULL) && (inp != NULL)) {
8411 /* reduce inp's ref-count */
8412 SCTP_INP_WLOCK(inp);
8413 SCTP_INP_DECR_REF(inp);
8414 SCTP_INP_WUNLOCK(inp);
8415 }
8416 if (stcb) {
8417 SCTP_TCB_UNLOCK(stcb);
8418 }
8419 }
8420}
8421#endif
8422
8423void
8424sctp_over_udp_stop(void)
8425{
8426 /*
8427 * This function assumes sysctl caller holds sctp_sysctl_info_lock() for writting!
8428 */
8429#ifdef INET
8430 if (SCTP_BASE_INFO(udp4_tun_socket) != NULL) {
8431 soclose(SCTP_BASE_INFO(udp4_tun_socket));
8432 SCTP_BASE_INFO(udp4_tun_socket) = NULL;
8433 }
8434#endif
8435#ifdef INET6
8436 if (SCTP_BASE_INFO(udp6_tun_socket) != NULL) {
8437 soclose(SCTP_BASE_INFO(udp6_tun_socket));
8438 SCTP_BASE_INFO(udp6_tun_socket) = NULL;
8439 }
8440#endif
8441}
8442
8443int
8444sctp_over_udp_start(void)
8445{
8446 uint16_t port;
8447 int ret;
8448#ifdef INET
8449 struct sockaddr_in sin;
8450#endif
8451#ifdef INET6
8452 struct sockaddr_in6 sin6;
8453#endif
8454 /*
8455 * This function assumes sysctl caller holds sctp_sysctl_info_lock() for writting!
8456 */
8457 port = SCTP_BASE_SYSCTL(sctp_udp_tunneling_port);
8458 if (ntohs(port) == 0) {
8459 /* Must have a port set */
8460 return (EINVAL);
8461 }
8462#ifdef INET
8463 if (SCTP_BASE_INFO(udp4_tun_socket) != NULL) {
8464 /* Already running -- must stop first */
8465 return (EALREADY);
8466 }
8467#endif
8468#ifdef INET6
8469 if (SCTP_BASE_INFO(udp6_tun_socket) != NULL) {
8470 /* Already running -- must stop first */
8471 return (EALREADY);
8472 }
8473#endif
8474#ifdef INET
8475 if ((ret = socreate(PF_INET, &SCTP_BASE_INFO(udp4_tun_socket),
8476 SOCK_DGRAM, IPPROTO_UDP,
8477 curthread->td_ucred, curthread))) {
8478 sctp_over_udp_stop();
8479 return (ret);
8480 }
8481 /* Call the special UDP hook. */
8482 if ((ret = udp_set_kernel_tunneling(SCTP_BASE_INFO(udp4_tun_socket),
8483 sctp_recv_udp_tunneled_packet,
8484 sctp_recv_icmp_tunneled_packet,
8485 NULL))) {
8486 sctp_over_udp_stop();
8487 return (ret);
8488 }
8489 /* Ok, we have a socket, bind it to the port. */
8490 memset(&sin, 0, sizeof(struct sockaddr_in));
8491 sin.sin_len = sizeof(struct sockaddr_in);
8492 sin.sin_family = AF_INET;
8493 sin.sin_port = htons(port);
8494 if ((ret = sobind(SCTP_BASE_INFO(udp4_tun_socket),
8495 (struct sockaddr *)&sin, curthread))) {
8496 sctp_over_udp_stop();
8497 return (ret);
8498 }
8499#endif
8500#ifdef INET6
8501 if ((ret = socreate(PF_INET6, &SCTP_BASE_INFO(udp6_tun_socket),
8502 SOCK_DGRAM, IPPROTO_UDP,
8503 curthread->td_ucred, curthread))) {
8504 sctp_over_udp_stop();
8505 return (ret);
8506 }
8507 /* Call the special UDP hook. */
8508 if ((ret = udp_set_kernel_tunneling(SCTP_BASE_INFO(udp6_tun_socket),
8509 sctp_recv_udp_tunneled_packet,
8510 sctp_recv_icmp6_tunneled_packet,
8511 NULL))) {
8512 sctp_over_udp_stop();
8513 return (ret);
8514 }
8515 /* Ok, we have a socket, bind it to the port. */
8516 memset(&sin6, 0, sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6));
8517 sin6.sin6_len = sizeof(struct sockaddr_in6);
8518 sin6.sin6_family = AF_INET6;
8519 sin6.sin6_port = htons(port);
8520 if ((ret = sobind(SCTP_BASE_INFO(udp6_tun_socket),
8521 (struct sockaddr *)&sin6, curthread))) {
8522 sctp_over_udp_stop();
8523 return (ret);
8524 }
8525#endif
8526 return (0);
8527}
8528#endif
8529
8530/*
8531 * sctp_min_mtu ()returns the minimum of all non-zero arguments.
8532 * If all arguments are zero, zero is returned.
8533 */
8534uint32_t
8535sctp_min_mtu(uint32_t mtu1, uint32_t mtu2, uint32_t mtu3)
8536{
8537 if (mtu1 > 0) {
8538 if (mtu2 > 0) {
8539 if (mtu3 > 0) {
8540 return (min(mtu1, min(mtu2, mtu3)));
8541 } else {
8542 return (min(mtu1, mtu2));
8543 }
8544 } else {
8545 if (mtu3 > 0) {
8546 return (min(mtu1, mtu3));
8547 } else {
8548 return (mtu1);
8549 }
8550 }
8551 } else {
8552 if (mtu2 > 0) {
8553 if (mtu3 > 0) {
8554 return (min(mtu2, mtu3));
8555 } else {
8556 return (mtu2);
8557 }
8558 } else {
8559 return (mtu3);
8560 }
8561 }
8562}
8563
8564#if defined(__FreeBSD__) && !defined(__Userspace__)
8565void
8566sctp_hc_set_mtu(union sctp_sockstore *addr, uint16_t fibnum, uint32_t mtu)
8567{
8568 struct in_conninfo inc;
8569
8570 memset(&inc, 0, sizeof(struct in_conninfo));
8571 inc.inc_fibnum = fibnum;
8572 switch (addr->sa.sa_family) {
8573#ifdef INET
8574 case AF_INET:
8575 inc.inc_faddr = addr->sin.sin_addr;
8576 break;
8577#endif
8578#ifdef INET6
8579 case AF_INET6:
8580 inc.inc_flags |= INC_ISIPV6;
8581 inc.inc6_faddr = addr->sin6.sin6_addr;
8582 break;
8583#endif
8584 default:
8585 return;
8586 }
8587 tcp_hc_updatemtu(&inc, (u_long)mtu);
8588}
8589
8590uint32_t
8591sctp_hc_get_mtu(union sctp_sockstore *addr, uint16_t fibnum)
8592{
8593 struct in_conninfo inc;
8594
8595 memset(&inc, 0, sizeof(struct in_conninfo));
8596 inc.inc_fibnum = fibnum;
8597 switch (addr->sa.sa_family) {
8598#ifdef INET
8599 case AF_INET:
8600 inc.inc_faddr = addr->sin.sin_addr;
8601 break;
8602#endif
8603#ifdef INET6
8604 case AF_INET6:
8605 inc.inc_flags |= INC_ISIPV6;
8606 inc.inc6_faddr = addr->sin6.sin6_addr;
8607 break;
8608#endif
8609 default:
8610 return (0);
8611 }
8612 return ((uint32_t)tcp_hc_getmtu(&inc));
8613}
8614#endif

8616void
8617sctp_set_state(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, int new_state)
8618{
8619#if defined(KDTRACE_HOOKS)
8620 int old_state = stcb->asoc.state;
8621#endif
8622
8623 KASSERT((new_state & ~SCTP_STATE_MASK) == 0,
8624 ("sctp_set_state: Can't set substate (new_state = %x)",
8625 new_state));
8626 stcb->asoc.state = (stcb->asoc.state & ~SCTP_STATE_MASK) | new_state;
8627 if ((new_state == SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_RECEIVED) ||
8628 (new_state == SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_SENT) ||
8629 (new_state == SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_ACK_SENT)) {
8630 SCTP_CLEAR_SUBSTATE(stcb, SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_PENDING);
8631 }
8632#if defined(KDTRACE_HOOKS)
8633 if (((old_state & SCTP_STATE_MASK) != new_state) &&
8634 !(((old_state & SCTP_STATE_MASK) == SCTP_STATE_EMPTY) &&
8635 (new_state == SCTP_STATE_INUSE))) {
8636 SCTP_PROBE6(state__change, NULL, stcb, NULL, stcb, NULL, old_state);
8637 }
8638#endif
8639}
8640
8641void
8642sctp_add_substate(struct sctp_tcb *stcb, int substate)
8643{
8644#if defined(KDTRACE_HOOKS)
8645 int old_state = stcb->asoc.state;
8646#endif
8647
8648 KASSERT((substate & SCTP_STATE_MASK) == 0,
8649 ("sctp_add_substate: Can't set state (substate = %x)",
8650 substate));
8651 stcb->asoc.state |= substate;
8652#if defined(KDTRACE_HOOKS)
8653 if (((substate & SCTP_STATE_ABOUT_TO_BE_FREED) &&
8654 ((old_state & SCTP_STATE_ABOUT_TO_BE_FREED) == 0)) ||
8655 ((substate & SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_PENDING) &&
8656 ((old_state & SCTP_STATE_SHUTDOWN_PENDING) == 0))) {
8657 SCTP_PROBE6(state__change, NULL, stcb, NULL, stcb, NULL, old_state);
8658 }
8659#endif
8660}
